75
00:11:34,990 --> 00:11:41,120
爱德华·布莱克，67岁，6尺2寸，重225磅
GALLAGHER: Edward Blake. Sixty-seven years old. Six-two, a solid 225.

76
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:43,490
这家伙就像橄榄球后卫一样结实
Guy was built like a linebacker.

77
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:45,560
是啊，我看过尸体了
FINE: Yeah, I saw the body.

78
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:47,790
以他这样的年纪，这体型很完美
For a guy his age, he was in terrific shape.

79
00:11:47,970 --> 00:11:50,630
除了一点：那就是他死了
GALLAGHER: You mean apart from being dead?

80
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:53,360
那是厚玻璃板
That's plate glass.

81
00:11:53,540 --> 00:11:56,440
你就算加速撞上去，也只能弄条裂缝
You'd have to step on the gas just to put a crack in it.

82
00:11:56,610 --> 00:11:58,670
他一定被扔上来的
Had to have been thrown.

83
00:11:58,850 --> 00:12:00,040
检察过卧室了吗？
Check the bedroom?

84
00:12:00,210 --> 00:12:03,150
是的，抽屉都被打开了，翻了个底朝天
Yeah. Drawers opened, tossed through.

85
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:06,380
床垫被翻过。大概是入室抢劫
Mattress flipped. Probably robbery.

86
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:08,020
或者做成入室抢劫一样
Or made to look like one.

87
00:12:08,190 --> 00:12:09,950
看看这个
See this?

88
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:13,490
- 和总统握手 - 哇
- Shaking hands with the president. FINE: Whoa.

89
00:12:13,660 --> 00:12:15,890
觉得布莱克是密探？
Think Blake was a spook?

90
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:19,730
政府密探或者秘密行动组的？
Government or black ops?

91
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,930
我觉得…
GALLAGHER: I think...

92
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:25,540
这件事牵扯的比你我都要大的多
...this is way bigger than both of us.

93
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:33,940
罗夏日记，10月12日，1985年
RORSCHACH: Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.

94
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:39,210
今早巷子里有具狗尸体 车子碾得它肚皮开花
Dog carcass in alley this morning. Tire tread on burst stomach.

95
00:12:39,490 --> 00:12:41,720
这座城市害怕我
This city's afraid of me.

96
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:45,830
我见识过它的真面目 这些街道就像无尽的臭水沟…
I've seen its true face. The streets are extended gutters...

97
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:48,890
充满鲜血的臭水沟
... and the gutters are full of blood.

98
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,530
当这些臭水沟的血完全结痂之后…
And when the drains finally scab over...

99
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,830
所有的寄生虫都会窒息而死
... all the vermin will drown.

100
00:12:55,470 --> 00:12:57,870
它们的色情和谋杀所沉积的污秽…
The accumulated filth of all their sex and murder...

101
00:12:58,040 --> 00:13:00,340
会淹没它们的腰部…
... will foam up around their waists...

102
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:05,970
这时所有的婊子和政客们就会仰起头哭喊： “救救我们！”
... and all the whores and politicians will look up and shout, "Save us."

103
00:13:06,950 --> 00:13:10,580
而我轻声说：“不。”
And I'll whisper, "No."

104
00:13:12,090 --> 00:13:14,950
现在全世界都已处在悬崖边…
Now the whole world stands on the brink...

105
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:17,610
人们向下直视着血腥的地狱
... staring down into bloody hell.

106
00:13:17,790 --> 00:13:21,320
那些自由主义者、学者…
All those liberals and intellectuals...

107
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,490
还有圆滑的演讲家们…
... and smooth talkers...

108
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:27,120
全都在一瞬间变得哑口无言
... and all of a sudden, nobody can think of anything to say.

109
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:30,460
在我脚下，这座威严的城市…
Beneath me, this awful city.

110
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:34,400
发出了好像在屠宰场里 任人宰割的弱智儿童的惨叫
It screams like an abattoir full of retarded children...

111
00:13:34,570 --> 00:13:39,200
夜晚则充满着道德沦丧的乌烟瘴气
... and the night reeks of fornication and bad consciences.

112
00:14:35,510 --> 00:14:36,870
（剪报：血腥的暴乱被制止）

113
00:14:42,830 --> 00:14:44,440
（笑匠笑到了最后：罪犯头目死神 在戏剧性的决斗中受到了正义的制裁）

114
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:52,250
哈
Huh.

115
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:59,070
（民兵）

116
00:14:59,790 --> 00:15:03,920
今晚，一位笑匠死在了纽约
Tonight, a comedian died in New York.

117
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,460
总有人知道原因
Somebody knows why.

118
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,030
总有人知道
Somebody knows.

119
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:15,800
不，我肯定听到了些动静
No, I definitely heard something.

120
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:20,440
守着门
Watch the door.

121
00:15:45,740 --> 00:15:47,300
嘘
Shh.

122
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,740
一定是风吹的，下次你…
Must've been the wind. Next time you...

123
00:16:04,260 --> 00:16:10,490
这一切都是从小混混开始的，人们想忘记这点
MAN: It all started with the gangs. You know, people tend to forget that.

124
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:14,260
海盗、鬼魂装扮
Pirate outfits, ghosts.

125
00:16:14,430 --> 00:16:17,030
他们觉得那样很有趣：精心打扮去抢劫
They thought it was funny: Dress up and pull heists.

126
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:21,430
我们逮捕他们之后，却马上又被放出来
As soon as we'd arrest them, they'd be back on the street.

127
00:16:21,610 --> 00:16:25,440
没人能够指证他们，正是因为那些该死的面具
Nobody could pick them out of a lineup because of the damn masks.

128
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:27,880
所以，我们几个警察，聚在一起…
So a few of us cops, we get together...

129
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:31,420
然后得出结论： 去他妈的，我们也蒙面
...and we figure, what the heck, we'll mask up, too.

130
00:16:31,590 --> 00:16:34,280
我们要做法律做不到的事情
We'll finish what the law couldn't.

131
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:39,120
很快，报纸也收到风声，他们也跟风…
Pretty soon, the papers get wind of it. They ran with it...

132
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:42,960
噢，老天，我们是整个国家的消遣啊
...and oh, boy, we're a national pastime.

133
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:46,620
那时有我、账单、飞蛾侠…
It was me, Dollar Bill, Mothman...

134
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:50,170
都会队长、正义头罩…
...Captain Metropolis, Hooded Justice...

135
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:53,530
丝鬼还有笑匠
...Silk Spectre and the Comedian.

136
00:16:53,710 --> 00:16:57,230
噢，别让我提到他
Oh, don't get me started on him.

137
00:16:59,380 --> 00:17:03,440
我一定喝多了，居然又向你说起这件伤心事
I must be drunk already, telling you this sob story again.

138
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:05,480
我想你应该开始说到重点了
I think you were trying to make a point.

139
00:17:06,390 --> 00:17:12,550
好吧，重点是，我们起头太容易了 后来发生在你们身上的事情是不公平的
Well, my point is that we had it too easy. It wasn't fair what happened to you guys...

140
00:17:12,730 --> 00:17:16,860
你们接手的是我们留下的烂摊子 还有尼克松强迫你们引退
You guys who picked up where we left off. - With Nixon forcing you out.

141
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:22,360
尼克松，噢，那个变态 想起来我还投票给这家伙5次
Nixon, oh, that prick. To think I voted for that prick five times.

142
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:25,270
嘿，不选他就只有共产党了，不是吗？
Hey, it was him or the commies, right?

143
00:17:28,070 --> 00:17:31,870
噢，差不多到午夜了，该走了
Oh, wow, it's almost midnight. Gotta go.

144
00:17:33,410 --> 00:17:35,040
想听真话吗？
Truth?

145
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:39,450
你是个我永远比不上的夜枭，丹尼小子
You were a better Nite Owl than I ever was, Danny boy.

146
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:43,350
- 霍利斯，我们都知道这是屁话 - 嘿！
- Hollis, we both know that's bullshit. - Hey.

147
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:44,790
说这话注意点
Watch it with the language.

148
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:47,590
这仍然是那只曾让艾克西斯队长趴下的左拳 还记得吗？
This is the left hook that floored Captain Axis, remember?

149
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:49,130
- 当然 - 最新报道
- Yeah. WOMAN [ON TV]: This just in:

150
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,230
那位被称作“罗夏”的蒙面义警…
The masked vigilante known as Rorschach...

151
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:54,230
在凌晨时分袭击了一位警察
... has assaulted a police officer in the early-morning hours.

152
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:58,090
他由于违反了6年前 用于驱逐蒙面英雄的“基恩法案”…
Rorschach is on the FBI's Ten Most Wanted list...

153
00:17:58,270 --> 00:18:02,070
而成为了联邦调查局的头号通缉犯
... for violation of the Keene Act, which banned masked heroes six years ago.

154
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:04,510
罗夏不断地使…
Rorschach reportedly incapacitated...

155
00:18:05,050 --> 00:18:07,450
他们驱逐了所有人却留下他
Forced everyone out except him.

156
00:18:07,610 --> 00:18:09,140
噢，他会退出的
Oh, he'll quit.

157
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,650
在他死的时候
When he's dead.

158
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:13,380
