DAN: Next week? HOLLIS: Well...

159
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:18,150
你没必要一直地讨我欢心
...you know, you don't have to keep humoring me like this.

160
00:18:18,330 --> 00:18:20,490
如果你有个热辣的约会对象之类的…
If you got a hot date or something...

161
00:18:20,660 --> 00:18:23,460
嘿，我们这些退休人员应该常聚，不是吗？
Hey, us retired guys have to stick together, right?

162
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:27,100
你怀念过那些日子吗？
You ever miss it?

163
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,390
没，你呢？
No. You?

164
00:18:30,970 --> 00:18:32,770
噢，去它的，没
Oh, heck, no.

165
00:18:34,070 --> 00:18:35,840
回见了
Be seeing you.

166
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,700
（梅森汽修）

167
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:47,330
（专修老车）

168
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:54,660
（乡愁：由维特公司献上）

169
00:19:49,620 --> 00:19:50,910
你好，丹尼尔
Hello, Daniel.

170
00:19:51,650 --> 00:19:52,740
罗夏
Rorschach.

171
00:19:53,820 --> 00:19:58,120
我用些豆子招呼了自己，希望你别介意
Helped myself to some beans. Hope you don't mind.

172
00:19:58,290 --> 00:20:00,730
不，不，当然不介意
No, no. Course not.

173
00:20:02,330 --> 00:20:04,890
你要我给你热热吗？
You want me to heat those up for you?

174
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:06,590
这样就好
Fine like this.

175
00:20:08,170 --> 00:20:09,360
最近都在忙些什么？
How have you been keeping?

176
00:20:13,740 --> 00:20:15,540
流亡
RORSCHACH: Out of prison.

177
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:19,470
我听了新闻
Heard about you on the news.

178
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:22,310
据说你袭击了一位警察
Say you attacked a cop.

179
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:25,250
轻伤，连医院都不用去
RORSCHACH: Minor wound. Won't need hospitalization.

180
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,280
丹尼尔…
Daniel...

181
00:20:27,450 --> 00:20:28,750
看看这个
...Iook at this.

182
00:20:34,530 --> 00:20:37,160
- 这是豆汁吗？ - 这是“人汁”
DAN: Is this bean juice? RORSCHACH: Human bean juice.

183
00:20:37,860 --> 00:20:42,360
这是笑匠的胸章，血也是，他死了
Badge belonged to the Comedian. Blood too. He's dead.

184
00:20:44,370 --> 00:20:45,840
我们到下面谈吧
Let's talk downstairs.

185
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,510
可能是入室行窃
DAN: It could have been a burglary.

186
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:59,380
或许凶手不知道他是笑匠
Maybe the killer didn't know who the Comedian was.

187
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:04,290
普通的偷盗犯？杀了笑匠？荒谬
RORSCHACH: An ordinary burglar? Kill the Comedian? Ridiculous.

188
00:21:05,860 --> 00:21:09,300
我听说他自从1977年后一直为政府做些…
I heard he'd been working for the government since '77...

189
00:21:09,460 --> 00:21:12,630
推翻南美洲的某些马克思主义共和政府的工作
...knocking over Marxist republics in South America.

190
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:15,730
或许这只是一起政治谋杀什么的
Maybe it was a political killing or something.

191
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,160
或许
Maybe.

192
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:20,600
或许有人正在铲除变装英雄们
Maybe someone's picking off costumed heroes.

193
00:21:20,770 --> 00:21:22,870
你不觉得有点神经质了吗？
DAN: You don't think that's a little paranoid?

194
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:25,600
这就是他们用来形容我的？
That what they say about me now?

195
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:27,110
神经质？
Paranoid?

196
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:30,110
听着，笑匠在那些日子里得罪了不少人…
DAN: Look, Comedian made a lot of enemies over the years...

197
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,770
甚至得罪了些朋友
...even among his friends.

198
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:34,110
说起朋友，霍利斯·梅森还好吗？ （一，二代夜枭是好朋友，就是刚刚喝酒的两位）
RORSCHACH: Speaking of friends, how's Hollis Mason?

199
00:21:34,990 --> 00:21:38,950
他写了本书，书里有些关于笑匠的坏话
He wrote that book. Said some bad things about the Comedian in it.

200
00:21:39,130 --> 00:21:43,190
我不喜欢你暗示的东西 也不喜欢被跟踪
I don't like what you're implying, and I like being followed even less.

201
00:21:43,730 --> 00:21:48,190
或许我只是照看着你 免得有蒙面英雄杀手找上门
Maybe I was keeping an eye on you, in case someone's gunning for masks.

202
00:21:48,370 --> 00:21:53,030
- 你不是多愁善感的人 - 袭击我们中的一个，就等于袭击我们全部
- You were never that sentimental. - Attack on one is attack on all of us.

203
00:21:53,470 --> 00:21:55,910
那你建议我们该干些什么？
What do you suggest we do about it?

204
00:21:56,810 --> 00:21:57,970
报偿笑匠
Retribution.

205
00:21:59,380 --> 00:22:02,680
- 守望者已经完了 - 狡猾迪克（对尼克松的蔑称）说的
- Watchmen are over. - Says Tricky Dick.

206
00:22:02,850 --> 00:22:04,610
我说的
Says me.

207
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:08,850
你的真实身份还没有被公开
Nobody knows who you are.

208
00:22:09,020 --> 00:22:11,990
你可以放弃追查，过上正常的生活
You can give it up, try and have a normal life.

209
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:16,060
就像你过的生活？正常的？
That what you have now? A normal life?

210
00:22:17,060 --> 00:22:20,430
当你走过这座好像快死的疯狗一样的城市…
When you walk down the street in a city dying of rabies...

211
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:22,070
走过那些谈论着…
...past the human cockroaches...

212
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:25,000
毒品和儿童色情电影的人类毒虫时…
...talking about their heroin and child pornography...

213
00:22:25,170 --> 00:22:26,700
你真觉得很正常？
...do you really feel normal?

214
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:30,610
至少我不是那个至今还活在面具之后的人
Least I'm not the one still hiding behind a mask.

215
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,740
不
No.

216
00:22:35,420 --> 00:22:37,540
你躲藏在大众这副面具之后
You're hiding in plain sight.

217
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:41,080
回头见，丹
Be seeing you, Dan.

218
00:22:41,590 --> 00:22:44,060
有个维护用的天井会带你到 离这里两个街区的北边
A maintenance hatch will let you out two blocks north.

219
00:22:44,220 --> 00:22:45,950
嗯，我还记得
Yeah, I remember.

220
00:22:46,130 --> 00:22:50,190
我常来这，当我们还是搭档的时候
Came here often, when we were partners.

221
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,260
那的确是段好时光，罗夏…
DAN: Those were great times, huh, Rorschach?

222
00:22:52,770 --> 00:22:56,000
- 到底怎么了？ - 你退出了
- What happened? - You quit.

223
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:03,650
（1965年，罗夏曾和夜枭2代携手对抗黑手党

224
00:23:03,650 --> 00:23:11,520
后来尼克松出台“基恩法案” 要求蒙面英雄
要么为政府工作要么退休

225
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:16,930
夜枭2代选择了退休，而罗夏选择了一个人战斗）

226
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:20,650
罗夏日记
Rorschach's journal.

227
00:23:20,830 --> 00:23:23,160
这毫无成果的夜晚，拜访的第一个人…
First visit of evening fruitless.

228
00:23:23,330 --> 00:23:25,420
让我有些失望
Feel slightly depressed.

229
00:23:25,970 --> 00:23:27,870
战争很快就会爆发了
Soon there will be war.

230
00:23:28,030 --> 00:23:31,600
上百万的人会疾病和痛苦中死去
Millions will perish in sickness and misery.

231
00:23:31,770 --> 00:23:34,300
为什么一个人的死还比这百万人重要？
Why does one death matter against so many?

232
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:39,840
因为当中有好人有坏人，而坏人必须被惩罚
Because there is good and evil, and evil must be punished.

233
00:23:40,010 --> 00:23:42,850
即使面对世界末日…
Even in the face of armageddon...

234
00:23:43,020 --> 00:23:45,810
在这点上我也不会妥协
... I will not compromise in this.

235
00:23:46,290 --> 00:23:49,880
但是有那么多人的值得被报偿…
But there are so many deserving of retribution...

236
00:23:50,090 --> 00:23:52,350
…而时间却那么少
... and so little time.

237
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:27,520
船长
MAN: Captain.

238
00:24:27,690 --> 00:24:30,160
- 船长 - 瑞德里
- Captain. - Ridley.

239
00:24:30,330 --> 00:24:33,320
瑞德里，你看到其他的生还者了吗？
Ridley, have you seen any other survivors?

240
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:34,520
没有，长官
No, sir.

241
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:39,160
船长，我的脚被些残骸卡住了
Captain, my foot is caught in some of the wreckage.

242
00:24:39,340 --> 00:24:42,710
- 我要沉下去了 - 撑住
- It's pulling me under. - Hold on.

243
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,910
瑞德里
Ridley.

244
00:24:57,990 --> 00:25:00,460
瑞德里
Ridley. Ridley.

245
00:25:01,090 --> 00:25:02,390
不
No.

246
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:04,050
不
No.

247
00:25:04,430 --> 00:25:06,690
更多血，更多血，更多血
VOICES [CHANTING]: More blood, more blood, more blood.

248
00:25:06,870 --> 00:25:09,360
在近乎溺亡的迷乱中，我看见了它
MARINER: Delirious from nearly drowning, I saw it.

249
00:25:10,940 --> 00:25:12,910
黑货船
The Black Freighter.

250
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:18,510
这驶向地狱的船的黑色船帆 正对着东印度群岛那片黄色的天空
The hell-bound ship's black sails against the yellow Indies sky.

251
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:25,020
我再次见识了火药、人类脑浆和战争的恶臭
I knew again the stench of powder and men's brains and war.

252
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:29,920
更多血，更多血，更多血
VOICES [CHANTING]: More blood, more blood, more blood.

253
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:40,060
更多血，更多血，更多血
More blood, more blood, more blood.

254
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:48,000
我身边的海浪是血红的…
MARINER: The waves about me were scarlet...

255
00:25:48,170 --> 00:25:51,170
…它们冒着泡 在黑货船号驶过之后透着可怕的温暖
... foaming, horribly warm in the Freighter's wake.

256
00:25:51,340 --> 00:25:54,510
绝望中，我将自己苦难的灵魂 祭献给全能的上帝…
In despair, I offered my weathered soul to almighty God...

257
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:58,170
…他的慈爱和他的审判
... his mercy and his judgment.

258
00:25:58,460 --> 00:25:59,720
（黑货船传奇）

259
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,310
嗨，你觉得如何，小子？
MAN: Heh. What do you think, kid?

260
00:26:01,490 --> 00:26:04,580
我们该向苏联发射核弹 剩下的让上帝去解决
We ought to nuke Russia and let God sort it out.

261
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:07,820
或者最低限度，让曼哈顿博士过去走一遭
Or at the very least, send Dr. Manhattan over for a visit.

262
00:26:07,990 --> 00:26:09,480
知道我的意思吗？
You know what I'm saying?

263
00:26:09,660 --> 00:26:12,560
我是说，我不是想做一个混球之类的 但的确是他们…
I mean, I ain't trying to be an asshole or anything, but they're the ones...

264
00:26:12,730 --> 00:26:15,220
…先惹火我们的 这只是我的个人意见
...who are agitating us. Now this is just my opinion.

265
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:18,840
但我是一个卖报纸的，知道吗 我消息灵通
But I'm a news vendor, you know, so I am informed.

266
00:26:19,610 --> 00:26:22,970
对，我知道，新边缘人报 呃，还没送到
Yeah, I know. The New Frontiersman. Well, it's not here yet.

267
00:26:23,140 --> 00:26:24,970
如果你不在这瞎等的话 我会很感激的…
I'd appreciate if you didn't stand around waiting...

268
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:27,670
…因为我不知道什么时候会送到
...because I don't know when it's going to be here.

269
00:26:27,910 --> 00:26:29,850
我想你刚刚才说你消息灵通的
I thought you said you was informed.

270
00:26:31,980 --> 00:26:34,950
- 你打算买下这个吗？ - 不
- Are you gonna buy that? - No.

271
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:40,660
噢，上帝 明天再来看看，好吗？
Oh, Jesus. Just try again tomorrow, okay?

272
00:26:51,100 --> 00:26:52,130
维特先生
MAN: Mr. Veidt...

273
00:26:52,310 --> 00:26:54,430
迄今为止，你是守望者当中唯一两位…
...to date, you're one of only two Watchmen...

274
00:26:54,610 --> 00:26:57,040
向大众公开身份的成员之一
...ever to reveal their true identity to the world...

275
00:26:57,210 --> 00:26:59,010
第一位公开身份的是霍利斯·梅森 （一代夜枭，写过关于守望者的书，前文已提）
...the first being Hollis Mason.

276
00:26:59,180 --> 00:27:02,170
将自己从一位超级英雄奥兹曼迪斯…
And you've certainly profited greatly by it...

277
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:07,620
转变成拥有价值过亿产业的商人 你一定从中获益良多
...turning your superhero alter ego, Ozymandias, into a billion-dollar industry:

278
00:27:07,790 --> 00:27:10,850
玩具、午餐盒，基因工程
Toys, lunchboxes, genetic engineering.

279
00:27:11,020 --> 00:27:13,080
我还听说一部相关的电影正在制作中
I understand there's a movie in the works.

280
00:27:13,260 --> 00:27:17,460
- 你好像不是在问问题，罗斯先生 - 抱歉，你有想过…
- I'm not hearing a question, Mr. Roth. ROTH: I'm sorry. Do you think...

281
00:27:17,630 --> 00:27:20,190
我贩卖着守望者们与邪恶争斗的事迹 他们会不会因此而憎恨我？
The Watchmen resent me for prostituting their struggle?

282
00:27:20,370 --> 00:27:23,100
（时事杂志：超人们为和平而联手） 这是个合理的问题，是的，我曾这样想过
It's a fair question. Yes, it's crossed my mind...

283
00:27:23,270 --> 00:27:26,300
某些过往的同僚们或许会这样看待我
...some of my old colleagues might see it that way...

284
00:27:26,470 --> 00:27:29,460
但同时你也明白…
...just as you're clearly aware that biased journalism...

285
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:32,240
偏激的文章好卖
...sells more magazines.

286
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:37,510
维特产业的商业资助已投入到 曼哈顿博士和我们合作的研究工作中
The merchandising arm of Veidt Industries is funding our work with Dr. Manhattan.

287
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:40,620
最近我们扩大了在南极洲的研究室
We recently expanded our research facility in Antarctica...

288
00:27:40,790 --> 00:27:44,020
希望研发出廉价、可再生的能源
...in the hope of developing cheap, renewable sources of energy...

289
00:27:44,190 --> 00:27:47,180
并由此结束全球对于矿物燃料的依赖
...that we might eliminate the world's reliance on fossil fuels.

290
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,790
看，我们并不需要借助任何的政治学者…
Now, it doesn't take a political scientist...

291
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:53,360
都能理解，我们与苏联之间的冷战 并不是因为意识形态的不合
...to see that our Cold War with the Russians isn't ideological...

292
00:27:53,530 --> 00:27:57,030
这是因为畏惧，畏惧于不能满足
...it's based upon fear. Fear of not having enough.

293
00:27:57,400 --> 00:28:01,100
但如果我们能让能源永不枯竭…
But if we make resources infinite...

294
00:28:01,270 --> 00:28:03,370
啊…
...ah...

295
00:28:03,540 --> 00:28:05,640
那么战争将永远不会发生
...we make war obsolete.

296
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:10,310
我希望其他的守望者们能明白这点
I would hope the other Watchmen understand that...

297
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:13,180
不管他们现在身处何方
...wherever they may be.

298
00:28:15,290 --> 00:28:16,650
感谢你们抽空到来
Thanks for your time.

299
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:25,560
- 你看起来不错啊，阿德里安 - 丹
- You look good, Adrian. - Dan.

300
00:28:25,730 --> 00:28:27,960
好久不见了
It's been too long.

301
00:28:28,170 --> 00:28:29,700
（纽约报：“末日时钟” 指向差5分钟到午夜）

302
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:29,720
就是说罗夏认为有人在捕杀守望者成员，哈？
ADRIAN: So Rorschach thinks someone's hunting the Watchmen, huh?
（纽约报：“末日时钟” 指向差5分钟到午夜）

303
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:33,760
就是说罗夏认为有人在捕杀守望者成员，哈？
ADRIAN: So Rorschach thinks someone's hunting the Watchmen, huh?

304
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:36,310
你认为可能吗？
You think it's possible?

305
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:39,210
统计学来讲 一宗谋杀不代表对我们的捕杀
Statistically, one murder doesn't equal a trend.

306
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:42,310
罗夏是个反社会的人，丹
Rorschach's a sociopath, Dan.

307
00:28:42,950 --> 00:28:46,320
笑匠也是，他简直就是个纳粹
And so was the Comedian. He was practically a Nazi.

308
00:28:47,150 --> 00:28:49,180
你比任何人都清楚这点
You know that better than anyone.

309
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,550
我来这里并不是因为我怀念他
I'm not here because I miss him.

310
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:53,060
这件事让罗夏想到…
It's occurred to Rorschach...

311
00:28:53,230 --> 00:28:56,200
就只有我们几个人知道彼此的身份
...that we're the only ones who know each other's identities.

312
00:28:56,700 --> 00:28:58,790
而实际上，全世界的人都知道你的
Actually, the whole world knows yours.

313
00:28:59,570 --> 00:29:02,030
所以我要提醒的第一个人是你
That's why I'm warning you first.

314
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,630
谢谢你，丹
Thank you, Dan...

315
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:13,040
但现在让我害怕的是一个更现实的事情…
...but I fear there's something much more real to worry about...

316
00:29:13,210 --> 00:29:15,810
比罗夏的蒙面英雄杀手更可怕
...than Rorschach's mask killer.

317
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:21,840
如果苏联人果然发射了核弹 乔真的可以拦截它们吗？
If the Russians do launch their nukes, can Jon really stop them?

318
00:29:22,020 --> 00:29:25,650
苏联储备了5万1千枚核弹头
The Soviets have 51,000 warheads stockpiled.

319
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:29,020
就算乔拦截了其中的99%…
Even if Jon stops 99 percent of them...

320
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:33,390
那漏网的1%也足够杀死地球上的所有生灵
...the 1 percent that get through could still kill every living thing on Earth.

321
00:29:36,140 --> 00:29:38,500
就算是曼哈顿博士也不能同时身处各方
Even Dr. Manhattan can't be everywhere at once.

322
00:29:46,170 --> 00:29:50,170
（美国陆军洛克菲勒军事研究中心）

323
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:58,380
罗夏日记，10月13日，1985年
Rorschach's journal, October 13th, 1985...

324
00:29:58,560 --> 00:30:00,890
晚上8:30
... 8:30 p.m.

325
00:30:01,590 --> 00:30:05,500
与夜枭会面之后，嘴里残留着不好的味道
Meeting with Dreiberg left bad taste in mouth.

326
00:30:05,700 --> 00:30:09,760
那个在自己地下室啜泣的软弱失败者
A flabby failure who sits whimpering in his basement.

327
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:13,910
为什么我们当中只剩下那么少人…
Why are so few of us left active...

328
00:30:14,070 --> 00:30:18,940
能身体、心智都健康地活跃着
... healthy and without personality disorders?

329
00:30:19,110 --> 00:30:22,340
第一任夜枭在经营一家汽车修理店
The first Nite Owl runs an auto-repair shop.

330
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:25,920
丝鬼一世则成了一个发福的老妓女
The first Silk Spectre is a bloated, aging whore...

331
00:30:26,090 --> 00:30:28,950
在加州的一处疗养胜地等死
... dying in a California rest resort.

332
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:31,720
帐单被一座旋转门夹住了斗篷…
Dollar Bill got his cape stuck in a revolving door...

333
00:30:31,890 --> 00:30:33,420
然后在那里被枪杀了
... where he got gunned down.

334
00:30:34,030 --> 00:30:36,460
侧影，被害…
Silhouette, murdered...

335
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:39,730
被自己那下流的生活所害
... a victim of her own indecent lifestyle.

336
00:30:40,300 --> 00:30:43,290
飞蛾侠在缅因州的一所精神病院里
Mothman's in an asylum in Maine.

337
00:30:47,310 --> 00:30:51,500
甚至连阿德里安·维特，他可能是同性恋
Even Adrian Veidt, possible homosexual.

338
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:54,170
也需要深入地调查
Must investigate further.

339
00:30:54,350 --> 00:30:57,110
就剩下两个人在我的名单里了
Only two names remain on my list.

340
00:30:57,650 --> 00:31:02,750
他们都住在洛克菲勒军事研究中心提供的 私人宿舍里
Both share private quarters at Rockefeller Military Research Center.

341
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:05,250
我该去找他们
I shall go to them.

342
00:31:05,590 --> 00:31:10,960
我该告诉那个坚不可摧的人 说有人想要杀了他
I shall go tell the indestructible man that someone plans to murder him.

343
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:13,560
晚上好，罗夏
JON: Good evening, Rorschach.

344
00:31:13,730 --> 00:31:17,230
曼哈顿博士，知道我为什么来吗？
RORSCHACH: Dr. Manhattan, you know why I'm here.

345
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:18,840
是的…
JON: Yes...

346
00:31:20,110 --> 00:31:22,070
但你将会失望地离开
...but you're going to leave disappointed.

347
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:25,970
罗夏，你不该来这，你是个通缉犯
Rorschach. You shouldn't be here. You're a wanted man.

348
00:31:26,150 --> 00:31:28,340
我也很高兴见到你，丝鬼
RORSCHACH: Nice to see you too, Silk Spectre.

349
00:31:28,510 --> 00:31:30,570
我有个一直在用的真名
I have a real name I've been using.

350
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:31,770
说说看
Try it.

351
00:31:31,950 --> 00:31:34,040
如你所愿，劳丽
Whatever you say, Laurie.

352
00:31:34,220 --> 00:31:35,450
你来这做什么？
What are you doing here?

353
00:31:35,620 --> 00:31:37,950
笑匠死了
JON: The Comedian is dead.

354
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:40,220
罗夏希望我能进入我的未来…
Rorschach wants me to look into my future...

355
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:43,030
去看看那杀手会不会被公开指认
...see if the killer is ever publicly identified.

356
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:46,290
我已经警告过夜枭了，现在来警告你
Already warned Dreiberg. Came to warn you too.

357
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:51,370
就算我愿意帮忙…
Even if I wanted to help...

358
00:31:51,970 --> 00:31:55,870
我的未来已经被某种不连续的干扰遮住了
...my future is blocked by some kind of temporal interference.

359
00:31:56,280 --> 00:32:00,340
- 我无法看清了 - 干扰？什么引起的？
- I cannot see it clearly. - Interference? Caused by what?

360
00:32:00,510 --> 00:32:03,910
十有八九，是因为核子灾难
In all likelihood, nuclear holocaust.

361
00:32:04,650 --> 00:32:08,750
如果美国和苏联全面开战…
If the United States and Soviet Union engage in all-out war...

362
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:12,910
由核武器引发的冲击波 会产生一场突然的超光速粒子大爆发
...the resulting blast wave would produce a sudden burst of tachyons...

363
00:32:13,090 --> 00:32:18,050
这些粒子会沿着时光穴逆向飞行
...particles which travel backward through what you perceive as time...

364
00:32:18,700 --> 00:32:22,030
从而模糊了我现在能看到的影像
...therefore obscuring my vision of the present.

365
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:24,230
我要回去工作了
I must return to my work.

366
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:25,530
等一等
RORSCHACH: Wait a minute.

367
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:28,200
如果这正是某人不希望我们干涉的计划呢？
What if that's why someone wants us out of the way?

368
00:32:28,370 --> 00:32:30,600
我们不能做些什么来阻止它吗？
So we can't do anything to stop it?

369
00:32:30,780 --> 00:32:32,610
再会了，罗夏
Goodbye, Rorschach.

370
00:32:32,780 --> 00:32:35,040
我辛辛苦苦进来找你们…
RORSCHACH: Took a lot of effort to get in here to see you.

371
00:32:35,210 --> 00:32:36,550
决不会在…
I'm not leaving...

372
00:32:37,820 --> 00:32:40,150
说完话之前离开
- till I've had my say.

373
00:32:47,660 --> 00:32:50,600
看起来这些日子发生的事情你都瞒着我
Seems like there's a lot of things you don't tell me these days.

374
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:53,460
我并不想让你过早地担心
I didn't wanna worry you prematurely.

375
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:58,060
如果阿德里安和我能解决这场能源危机 战争形势将被逆转
If Adrian and I can solve the energy crisis, war may be averted.

376
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:00,300
但你总是说时间是不可逆转的
LAURIE: But you always say time is simultaneous.

377
00:33:01,010 --> 00:33:03,870
如果你看到的未来是真的 你怎么能够改变它？
If that's true, then how can you change the future?

378
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:09,040
只要你能和我一样感知时间就能
If only you could perceive time as I do.

379
00:33:09,220 --> 00:33:10,480
请允许我向你展示
Please let me show you.

380
00:33:16,460 --> 00:33:21,390
魔法、梦想，我曾拥有这些 我曾是个英雄啊，他妈的
Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before. I was a hero, goddamn it!

381
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:24,620
你变老也不是我的错啊，你在抱怨些什么？
It's not my fault you got old. What do you have to complain about?

382
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:27,230
在餐桌上为你和你的孩子准备食物的人是我啊
I'm putting food on the table for you and your child.

383
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:30,160
给你的朋友艾迪电话吧 或许他能给你更好的生活
Call your friend Eddie. Maybe he can give you a better life.

384
00:33:30,340 --> 00:33:34,500
- 那是个错误，就那一次！ - 那家伙曾经要强奸你啊！
- It was a mistake. One time. - Man tries to rape you...

385
00:33:34,810 --> 00:33:36,170
停手！
Stop!

386
00:33:36,940 --> 00:33:38,410
你的心智也有着阴暗的角落…
Your mind goes to dark places...

387
00:33:38,580 --> 00:33:40,910
而你不理解我为什么把最坏的事情瞒着你
...and you wonder why I keep the worst from you.

388
00:33:44,850 --> 00:33:48,290
- 替我向丹问好 - 什么？
- Say hello to Dan for me. - What?

389
00:33:50,060 --> 00:33:52,850
你想请我和你共进晚餐…
You wanna ask me to go to dinner with you...

390
00:33:54,560 --> 00:33:56,720
就像以前一样…
...like we used to...

391
00:33:58,160 --> 00:33:59,290
但这次不行
...but you won't.

392
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:02,330
你明白我不能去的
You know I can't.

393
00:34:04,970 --> 00:34:07,230
所以你会给丹电话…
So you'll call Dan...

394
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:09,870
这样很正常
...which is only natural.

395
00:34:10,210 --> 00:34:12,800
你应该得到一位老朋友的慰籍
You deserve the comfort of an old friend.

396
00:34:47,110 --> 00:34:48,640
丹·德雷伯格的桌位
LAURIE: Dan Dreiberg's table.

397
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:13,570
- 你知道他和H·J是… - 完全不知道
DAN: Did you know that he and H.J. Were...? I had no idea.

398
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:17,130
你还记得那个疯子吗？他怎么称呼自己来着？
You remember that crazy guy? What'd he call himself?

399
00:35:17,310 --> 00:35:18,800
屠夫队长
Captain Carnage.

400
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:22,180
他总是假装是个超级恶棍 好让自己被暴打一顿
Used to pretend he was a supervillain just so he could get beat up?

401
00:35:22,350 --> 00:35:24,750
是啊，他找我试过一次，我没理睬他
Yeah, he tried that on me once. I just walked away.

402
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:27,940
于是他大白天跟着我走了整条街…
He starts following me down the street in broad daylight...

403
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:30,920
一边走一边喊：“惩罚我吧！惩罚我吧！”
...yelling, "Punish me! Punish me!"

404
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:33,680
我回了一句：“不，滚开。”
I'm just saying, "No, get lost."

405
00:35:34,830 --> 00:35:37,300
天啊，后来他怎么了？
God, whatever happened to him?

406
00:35:37,460 --> 00:35:39,620
噢，嗯，后来他去惹罗夏了…
Oh. Um... He pulled that on Rorschach...

407
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:42,200
罗夏就把他扔下了电梯井
...and Rorschach dropped him down an elevator shaft.

408
00:35:48,670 --> 00:35:51,070
哦，天啊，这就没趣了
Oh, my God. That's not even funny.

409
00:35:51,780 --> 00:35:54,270
- 还是有点趣的 - 嗯
- It's a little funny. - Yep.

410
00:35:56,180 --> 00:35:58,150
很庆幸我点了四腿鸡
WOMAN: I'm glad I ordered the four-legged chicken.

411
00:35:58,320 --> 00:36:00,290
能再见到你真的很高兴
It's really good to see you again.

412
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:03,040
我也一样
It's great seeing you too.

413
00:36:03,860 --> 00:36:06,380
我们为什么会那样做，丹？像那样子的变装
Why'd we do it, Dan? Dress up like that?

414
00:36:07,530 --> 00:36:10,860
- 因为其他人不愿意做 - 是啊，你还记得我的衣服吗？
- No one else would. - Yeah, but do you remember my costume?

415
00:36:11,030 --> 00:36:14,120
全身的束身橡胶，我说，那真糟糕
All that tight latex? I mean, it was awful.

416
00:36:14,300 --> 00:36:17,270
啊，是啊，糟糕
Uh... Yeah, yeah, awful.

417
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:19,870
但我那时不想让妈妈失望
But didn't wanna disappoint Mother.

418
00:36:20,040 --> 00:36:24,030
她想我成为像她一样的人，打击坏人
Wanted her little girl to be just like her and fight bad guys.

419
00:36:24,710 --> 00:36:28,310
我想 “基恩法案”是发生在我们身上最好的事情了
I think the Keene Act was the best thing that ever happened to us.

420
00:36:29,380 --> 00:36:31,750
其实，不论怎样我们都会活得久些的
Well, we'll live longer anyway.

421
00:36:35,050 --> 00:36:36,580
怎么了？
What?

422
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:42,050
乔觉得，如果他不为此挺身而出的话…
Jon thinks, unless he can do something about it...

423
00:36:42,900 --> 00:36:44,920
一场核战争就会爆发
...that there's gonna be nuclear war.

424
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:46,890
很快就会
Soon.

425
00:36:47,770 --> 00:36:51,100
但我跟不上他的思维，我是说…
But I don't know what to think. I mean, it's all...

426
00:36:51,270 --> 00:36:54,330
他的世界都是量子力学、平行实体之类的
...quantum mechanics and parallel realities with him.

427
00:36:54,510 --> 00:36:57,270
我无法了解他眼中的宇宙
I never even know what universe he's actually seeing.

428
00:36:58,580 --> 00:37:01,710
他和我越来越疏远了…
He just keeps getting further away from me.

429
00:37:02,410 --> 00:37:04,080
和其他人也一样
Everyone.

430
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:07,850
我甚至不能确定他是否还在乎我…
I can't even tell if he actually cares about me anymore...

431
00:37:08,020 --> 00:37:10,050
或者都只是他假装的
...or if he's just pretending.

432
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:13,690
如果他假装的话，那说明他还在乎
If he's pretending, it means he cares.

433
00:37:18,430 --> 00:37:20,420
等等，我给你开门
Hold on, I'll get the door.

434
00:37:21,770 --> 00:37:23,560
谢谢，丹
Thanks, Dan.

435
00:37:23,940 --> 00:37:25,960
- 坐好了？ - 嗯
- Got it? - Yeah.

436
00:37:31,380 --> 00:37:34,370
你总是带着官方陪同人员吃晚餐的吗？
You always get a government escort to dinner?

437
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:39,140
他们是要确定我不会做任何 让这个国家最强大的武器伤心的事
They're making sure I don't do anything to upset the country's most powerful weapon.

438
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:42,150
我很抱歉
I'm sorry.

439
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:46,220
我约你出来吃饭，叙旧，说说笑…
I invite you out to dinner to catch up and have a few laughs...

440
00:37:46,590 --> 00:37:49,960
但看起来我们大家最近都过得不怎样
...but there don't seem to be many laughs around these days.

441
00:37:50,130 --> 00:37:53,930
还能期待些什么呢？笑匠都死了
What do you expect? The Comedian's dead.

442
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:59,540
（电影“毕业生”主题曲：The Sound Of Silence）

443
00:38:16,210 --> 00:38:19,260
（墓园）

444
00:38:44,070 --> 00:38:54,890
（注意，这个流浪汉手里的牌子上写着“末日临近” 他就是罗夏，即使守望者也认不出不戴面具的他）

445
00:39:36,300 --> 00:39:37,470
（棕榈泉报：苏联提高核弹头产量）

446
00:39:37,470 --> 00:39:37,480
劳丽，是你吗？
Laurie? Is that you?
（棕榈泉报：苏联提高核弹头产量）

447
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:41,030
劳丽，是你吗？
Laurie? Is that you?

448
00:39:43,740 --> 00:39:46,710
我以为你已经习惯这种旅行方式了
Thought you'd be used to traveling that way by now.

449
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:51,370
还没，我讨厌乔传送我
Well, I'm not. I hate it when Jon teleports me.

450
00:39:51,550 --> 00:39:54,420
那也比经济舱好的多
Well, it beats flying coach.

451
00:39:54,790 --> 00:39:56,780
来点玛格丽塔？
Margarita?

452
00:39:57,020 --> 00:39:59,180
妈，现在是下午2点
Mother, it's 2:00 in the afternoon.

453
00:40:01,890 --> 00:40:03,360
嗯
Mm.

454
00:40:04,030 --> 00:40:06,330
还记得那个一直给我写信的家伙吗？
Remember that guy that writes me letters?

455
00:40:06,700 --> 00:40:10,000
他给我寄来了一件大礼物 这在提华纳（墨西哥）就像圣经一样
He sent me an item of memorabilia. It's a Tijuana bible.

456
00:40:10,170 --> 00:40:14,330
这本8页的色情小漫画，是30、40年代出版的 （漫画名：丝鬼，是以丝鬼一代为主角的色情漫画 丝鬼一代居然很喜欢，可见罗夏说她像妓女没错）
This little eight-page porno comic they did in the '30s and '40s.

457
00:40:14,510 --> 00:40:18,530
- 他给你寄来了这个？ - 是啊，这东西很值钱，就像古董
- He sent you this? - Sure. They're very valuable, like antiques.

458
00:40:19,340 --> 00:40:21,040
妈，这东西太恶心了
Mother, this is gross.

459
00:40:21,210 --> 00:40:23,480
我觉得这样挺讨人喜欢啊
I think it's kind of flattering.

460
00:40:23,650 --> 00:40:25,910
为什么你生气的时候总是用这种语气说话
Why do you always call me Mother when you're mad?

461
00:40:27,290 --> 00:40:31,350
我知道你为什么来，我还能认字，知道吗？
I know why you're here. I can still read, you know.

462
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:34,350
我看过报纸了
I saw it in the paper.

463
00:40:35,030 --> 00:40:37,930
艾迪·布莱克的葬礼就在今天
Eddie Blake's funeral is today.

464
00:40:39,730 --> 00:40:42,720
我想，他终于让人发笑了
Finally got his punchline, I guess.

465
00:40:43,200 --> 00:40:46,030
- 可怜的艾迪 - 可怜？他那样对你还可怜？
- Poor Eddie. - Poor Eddie? After what he did to you?

466
00:40:46,740 --> 00:40:48,260
噢，劳丽，你还年轻
Oh, Laurie, you're still young.

467
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:50,980
你不了解
You don't know.

468
00:40:51,140 --> 00:40:52,910
世事无常
Things change.

469
00:40:53,750 --> 00:40:56,510
发生了什么也是40年前的事了
What happened happened 40 years ago.

470
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:59,950
我已经67岁
I'm 67 years old.

471
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:04,320
每一天，眼前的未来都在慢慢变暗
Every day, the future looks a little bit darker.

472
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:07,320
但是过去…
But the past...

473
00:41:07,830 --> 00:41:10,820
即使最肮脏的过去…
...even the grimy parts of it...

474
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:13,990
