慢着，他们送来了
Hold up. Here they come.

808
01:09:51,240 --> 01:09:54,880
（新边缘人报： 荣耀如同雄鹰：有时它也需要蒙上脸）

809
01:09:55,020 --> 01:09:57,540
- 西摩尔 - 伯尼，近来可好？
- Seymour. - Bernie, how's tricks?

810
01:09:57,720 --> 01:09:58,750
不错，不错
BERNIE: Fine, fine.

811
01:09:58,920 --> 01:10:02,220
看到我身后那个男人吗？ 这个星期他一直在跟踪我
See this guy behind me? Been bugging me all week.

812
01:10:05,130 --> 01:10:09,330
或许我们该坐车来，这里治安不好
Maybe we should get a cab. These are bad neighborhoods.

813
01:10:09,500 --> 01:10:13,130
管它呢，我正好心情坏
Yeah, well, I'm in a bad mood.

814
01:10:25,720 --> 01:10:27,980
- 小妞 - 看看谁来了
MAN 1: Girl. MAN 2: What we got here?

815
01:10:28,150 --> 01:10:31,020
这个是五角大楼开出的禁谈话题清单
Here's a list of Pentagon-approved no-go areas.

816
01:10:31,190 --> 01:10:33,990
他们一定会问起阿富汗的，一笔带过就好…
Afghanistan will obviously come up, but just play it cool...

817
01:10:34,160 --> 01:10:36,520
还有别被逼进死胡同
...and try not to get into any tight corners.

818
01:10:36,690 --> 01:10:40,390
一位著名的核子物理学家 他在经过一场可怕的意外后…
- A renowned nuclear physicist, who, through a terrible accident...

819
01:10:40,560 --> 01:10:46,330
得到了异常的天赋，能够随意改变物体的外形
...was gifted with extraordinary powers, capable of bending matter to his will.

820
01:10:46,500 --> 01:10:50,770
今天，全世界都知道他的名字：曼哈顿博士
Today, the world knows him as Dr. Manhattan.

821
01:10:50,940 --> 01:10:52,270
欢迎你
Welcome.

822
01:10:57,280 --> 01:10:58,510
谢谢
JON: Thank you.

823
01:10:58,680 --> 01:11:00,620
这就对了
MAN 3: That's right.

824
01:11:07,160 --> 01:11:09,960
布雷克女士，你来问第一个问题
Ms. Black, you have the first question.

825
01:11:10,130 --> 01:11:11,560
曼哈顿博士，你知道…
Dr. Manhattan, as you know...

826
01:11:11,730 --> 01:11:14,420
“末日时钟”是用来象征性地…
...the Doomsday Clock is a symbolic clock face...

827
01:11:14,600 --> 01:11:18,160
推断人类的灭绝时刻的
...analogizing humankind's proximity to extinction...

828
01:11:18,500 --> 01:11:21,490
午夜代表着核战爆发的威胁
...midnight representing the threat of nuclear war.

829
01:11:21,670 --> 01:11:24,830
而现在，它指向差4分钟到午夜的时刻
As of now, it stands at four minutes to midnight.

830
01:11:25,480 --> 01:11:27,940
你同意我们人类即将灭绝了吗？
Would you agree that we're that close to annihilation?

831
01:11:29,180 --> 01:11:31,520
我父亲是一个钟表匠
My father was a watchmaker.

832
01:11:32,350 --> 01:11:36,690
在爱因斯坦发现时间是相对的之后 他不再接触钟表
He abandoned it when Einstein discovered that time is relative.

833
01:11:37,860 --> 01:11:39,850
我只能同意，这仅仅是一个对于谍报人员…
I would only agree that a symbolic clock...

834
01:11:40,030 --> 01:11:42,020
才有象征性意义的时钟
...is as nourishing to the intellect...

835
01:11:42,200 --> 01:11:45,460
如同给溺水的人一张氧气的照片一样
...as a photograph of oxygen to a drowning man.

836
01:11:47,800 --> 01:11:49,530
你的意思是完全没有危险？
So you're saying there is no danger.

837
01:11:49,700 --> 01:11:53,700
就算是这世上没有核武器，危险一样存在
JON: Even in a world without nuclear weapons, there would still be danger.

838
01:11:58,650 --> 01:12:01,550
你是否同意，是神…
MAN: And would you say, as so many claim...

839
01:12:01,720 --> 01:12:03,480
当然他们也称你“神”…
...that you are, in fact, a god...

840
01:12:03,650 --> 01:12:06,490
是神让你能够同时看到过去和未来？
...given you see the past and future simultaneously?

841
01:12:06,660 --> 01:12:08,950
我只能看到我自己的过去…
I can only see my own past...

842
01:12:09,390 --> 01:12:13,290
和我自己的未来，我并非无所不知
... my own future. I am not omniscient.

843
01:12:13,900 --> 01:12:15,260
道格·罗斯，该你问了
KOPPEL: Doug Roth, your question?

844
01:12:15,430 --> 01:12:18,160
说起你的过去，曼哈顿博士…
Speaking of your past, Dr. Manhattan...

845
01:12:18,330 --> 01:12:21,100
你还记得一个叫沃利·维沃的男人吗？
...do you remember a man named Wally Weaver?

846
01:12:21,270 --> 01:12:26,400
是的，我们在吉拉·弗莱茨研究基地共事过
Yes. We were both physicists together at the Gila Flats Research Base.

847
01:12:26,910 --> 01:12:28,470
他死于癌症
He died of cancer.

848
01:12:29,340 --> 01:12:31,610
- 他是一个好人 - 那么埃德加·雅各比呢？
- He was a good man. ROTH: How about Edgar Jacobi...

849
01:12:31,780 --> 01:12:34,680
也就是被称作“死神”的超级恶棍
... also known as the supervillain Moloch?

850
01:12:35,650 --> 01:12:39,750
你和他在60年代的战斗、冲突中相遇过几次
You encountered him several times in the '60s: Battles, conflicts.

851
01:12:39,950 --> 01:12:42,420
你知道他也得了癌症吗？
Did you know that he has cancer as well?

852
01:12:43,360 --> 01:12:44,590
我并未被告知
I wasn't told.

853
01:12:44,760 --> 01:12:46,990
那么安东尼·兰道夫将军呢？
ROTH: And what about General Anthony Randolph?

854
01:12:47,160 --> 01:12:50,600
他是你在为政府工作时的联系人
He was your handler when you first started working for the government.

855
01:12:51,000 --> 01:12:52,020
也是癌症
Cancer.

856
01:12:52,200 --> 01:12:54,860
你是说我导致了他们患病？
You're suggesting I was the cause.

857
01:12:55,270 --> 01:12:58,260
就我来看，结论看起来十分明显
ROTH: From where I'm standing, it's starting to look pretty conclusive.

858
01:12:58,440 --> 01:13:00,470
就算这些都是事实，它们之间也没有关联
JON: Even if that's the case, it's irrelevant.

859
01:13:00,640 --> 01:13:03,440
一个活着的人类和患病的人类…
A live human body and a deceased human body...

860
01:13:03,610 --> 01:13:05,700
拥有着同样的身体构成
... have the same number of particles.

861
01:13:08,450 --> 01:13:10,350
从结构上说，二者没有区别
Structurally, there's no difference.

862
01:13:11,490 --> 01:13:13,750
好了，请安静
All right. Let's settle down, please.

863
01:13:19,630 --> 01:13:20,860
那么珍妮·斯莱特呢？
What about Janey Slater?

864
01:13:21,630 --> 01:13:23,960
你觉得她有不同吗？
You think it makes a difference to her?

865
01:13:25,030 --> 01:13:26,360
珍妮？
Janey?

866
01:13:26,700 --> 01:13:28,260
你的前女友
ROTH: Your ex-girlfriend?

867
01:13:28,440 --> 01:13:32,070
她也是一个物理学家，你们交往了11年
She was a physicist too. You saw each other for 11 years.

868
01:13:32,240 --> 01:13:33,760
道格，一次问一个问题
Doug, one question at a time.

869
01:13:33,940 --> 01:13:37,310
她也得了癌症，医生说她只有半年命
She has cancer as well. Doctors have given her six months.

870
01:13:37,480 --> 01:13:39,310
我说的对吗？斯莱特女士
Isn't that right, Miss Slater?

871
01:13:54,830 --> 01:13:56,630
你是我的全部，乔
You were the world to me, Jon.

872
01:13:57,230 --> 01:13:59,460
你是我的生命
You were my whole life.

873
01:14:00,400 --> 01:14:03,000
还记得你说过多少次你爱我吗？
Do you remember how many times you said you loved me?

874
01:14:03,170 --> 01:14:04,870
珍妮，这事我不知道
Janey, I wasn't told.

875
01:14:05,340 --> 01:14:10,710
意外发生后我一直对你不离不弃 我把一切都给了你
I stuck by you after the accident. I gave you everything.

876
01:14:15,750 --> 01:14:17,410
这就是你给我的回报吗？
This is how you repay me?

877
01:14:17,850 --> 01:14:22,760
- 珍妮，没人告诉过我，我不知道这事 - 诅咒你，乔，愿上帝诅咒你
- Janey, I wasn't told. I didn't know. - Damn you, Jon. Goddamn you.

878
01:14:22,920 --> 01:14:24,920
珍妮，等等
Janey, wait.

879
01:14:26,330 --> 01:14:28,760
够了，采访结束了，来人
- That's it. This interview is over. MAN: Get up there.

880
01:14:28,930 --> 01:14:31,300
把相机都拿走，所有人后退
Get those cameras off. Everybody back off.

881
01:14:31,470 --> 01:14:35,160
所有人后退，我需要支援，别再烦他
Everybody back off. I need some backup here. Leave him alone.

882
01:14:35,340 --> 01:14:41,430
请你们大家，都走开…
Please, if everyone would just go away...

883
01:14:41,610 --> 01:14:44,510
别再烦我…
...and leave me alone...

884
01:14:44,680 --> 01:14:46,080
你愿意发表评论吗？
Do you care to comment?

885
01:14:46,250 --> 01:14:49,270
我说过，别烦我！
I said, leave me alone!

886
01:15:14,910 --> 01:15:16,810
上帝
Jesus.

887
01:15:17,910 --> 01:15:19,500
我们…
Us...

888
01:15:20,420 --> 01:15:22,250
被打劫了
...getting mugged.

889
01:15:24,590 --> 01:15:26,180
走吧
Let's go.

890
01:15:31,930 --> 01:15:33,720
我在发抖
I'm shaking.

891
01:15:37,930 --> 01:15:39,700
你知道吗？
You know what?

892
01:15:40,070 --> 01:15:43,560
我心情好了，我会记住今晚的
I'm wiped. I'm just gonna call it a night.

893
01:15:43,740 --> 01:15:46,970
噢，你真的不和我一起去霍利斯家…
Oh, are you sure you don't wanna come by Hollis' with me...

894
01:15:47,140 --> 01:15:49,370
然后冷静一下吗？
...and shake off the adrenaline?

895
01:15:50,180 --> 01:15:53,310
我想这样一晚就够一个英雄受的了
LAURIE: I think I've had enough hero stuff for one night.

896
01:15:54,450 --> 01:15:56,820
你能听我诉苦帮了很大忙
It helped having you listen.

897
01:15:57,120 --> 01:15:58,850
随时欢迎
DAN: Any time.

898
01:15:59,550 --> 01:16:01,450
保重，丹
LAURIE: Take care, Dan.

899
01:16:02,260 --> 01:16:04,560
这世道不太平
It's a rough world out there.

900
01:16:06,030 --> 01:16:07,220
回见
DAN: Be seeing you.

901
01:16:13,570 --> 01:16:14,900
我想到了家人…
MARINER: I thought of my family...

902
01:16:15,840 --> 01:16:18,100
…我的妻子，我的女儿们
... my wife, my daughters.

903
01:16:18,270 --> 01:16:20,260
她们毫无防备，毫无怀疑
Vulnerable, unsuspecting.

904
01:16:20,980 --> 01:16:24,410
等待着我的归来 而等到的只有迎面而来的…
Awaiting my return, only to be met by damnation...

905
01:16:24,580 --> 01:16:27,010
…无尽的诅咒
... bearing down upon them.

906
01:16:33,490 --> 01:16:34,580
嘿！
Hey!

907
01:16:34,760 --> 01:16:36,220
我在这儿！
Over here!

908
01:16:36,820 --> 01:16:38,350
这儿！
Here!

909
01:16:44,170 --> 01:16:45,600
瑞德里
Ridley.

910
01:17:01,980 --> 01:17:03,250
船帆
A sail.

911
01:17:03,690 --> 01:17:06,180
瑞德里给我带来了一片船帆
Ridley had brought me a sail.

912
01:17:06,490 --> 01:17:09,620
或许这可以带我回到戴维斯敦
Perhaps this could be my route back to Davidstown.

913
01:17:10,990 --> 01:17:15,220
我爱的一切，我为之而活的一切 都仰仗着我的归来…
Everything I loved, everything I lived for, depended on my reaching home...

914
01:17:15,400 --> 01:17:18,700
…仰仗着我能比那可怕的黑货船早到
... in advance of that terrible Freighter.

915
01:17:28,280 --> 01:17:30,800
直到早晨，我依然有着不少麻烦
The morning sun found me no less troubled.

916
01:17:32,480 --> 01:17:33,640
在更远的海岸上…
Further down the shore...

917
01:17:33,820 --> 01:17:37,310
…我的一些船员因臭气而膨胀
... some of my crew had become inflated with gas.

918
01:17:37,750 --> 01:17:39,190
啊！
Ugh!

919
01:17:42,790 --> 01:17:48,350
我为自己的这个想法而颤抖 尝试着去赶走这令人厌恶的念头
I shuddered at my own idea, attempting to banish this repulsive notion.

920
01:17:55,770 --> 01:18:00,070
即便已死，他们依然努力履行他们的职责…
Even in death, they sought to fulfill their duty...

921
01:18:00,240 --> 01:18:02,840
…去让我们的这艘船更有浮力
... making our vessel more buoyant.

922
01:18:03,240 --> 01:18:06,340
而我会履行我那将他们带回家的职责
And I would do my duty to them in returning them home.

923
01:18:08,050 --> 01:18:13,320
粗鲁地搅扰着我那些长眠的船员 并把他们放进我为之准备的尸床
Rudely jarring my men from eternal rest, and laying them in the bed I prepared...

924
01:18:13,490 --> 01:18:17,950
当我的妻子和女儿们逝世后 我希望她们能被…
... I hoped my wife and daughters might be tucked in by gentler hands...

925
01:18:18,130 --> 01:18:19,820
…更温柔的手安放好
... when their turn came.

926
01:18:37,180 --> 01:18:39,540
我们会一起回家的，我的朋友
We shall get home together, my friend.

927
01:18:42,520 --> 01:18:43,950
我等待着涨潮
I waited for the tide.

928
01:18:44,790 --> 01:18:48,780
然后，坐上船，向东航行
Then, embarking, headed east.

929
01:18:49,320 --> 01:18:51,950
东方，穿过黑夜海洋
East, across the night seas.

930
01:18:52,130 --> 01:18:56,590
东方，乘在被虐杀的人的尸体上
East, borne on the bodies of murdered men.

931
01:18:57,530 --> 01:19:00,020
人的希望可以变成可怕的事情
Hope can be a horrible thing.

932
01:20:04,800 --> 01:20:09,100
找寻早餐的海鸥伴随着黎明的到来
With the dawn came the gulls looking for breakfast.

933
01:20:09,270 --> 01:20:10,400
瑞德里
Ridley.

934
01:20:13,610 --> 01:20:14,630
滚开
Get out.

935
01:20:20,820 --> 01:20:24,110
我才想起我自己没有吃东西
I was reminded that I, myself, had not eaten.

936
01:20:26,050 --> 01:20:30,180
我知道这并不好吃，但这是我们仅有的
I know it is unappetizing, but it is all we have.

937
01:20:32,460 --> 01:20:34,280
（黑货船传奇）

938
01:20:35,760 --> 01:20:37,530
他走了
MAN: He's gone.

939
01:20:38,030 --> 01:20:39,500
- 他走了 - 谁走了？
- He's gone! BERNIE: Who's gone?

940
01:20:39,670 --> 01:20:41,730
- 曼哈顿博士 - 什么？你说什么？
- Dr. Manhattan. BERNIE: What? What'd you say?

941
01:20:41,900 --> 01:20:45,170
曼哈顿博士走了，离开我们了
Dr. Manhattan's gone. He's left us.

942
01:20:45,340 --> 01:20:47,860
什么？去哪儿了？
What? Gone where?

943
01:20:53,980 --> 01:20:55,110
你比平时晚了
You're late.

944
01:20:55,280 --> 01:20:58,380
啊，我知道 你不会相信刚才发生的事的
Ah, I know. I know. You won't believe what happened.

945
01:20:58,550 --> 01:21:01,350
曼哈顿博士在直播的电视节目中消失了
Dr. Manhattan just lost it on live TV.

946
01:21:01,520 --> 01:21:03,220
等等，什么？
Wait, what?

947
01:21:08,800 --> 01:21:10,730
刚才劳丽和我一起，她不知道这事
I was just with Laurie. She doesn't know.

948
01:21:11,530 --> 01:21:15,130
她很快就会知道的，全世界也会知道的
HOLLIS: She's gonna know soon enough. The whole world will know.

949
01:21:15,300 --> 01:21:18,030
我说过，别烦我！
I said, leave me alone!

950
01:21:27,880 --> 01:21:30,080
我看着星空
JON: I am looking at the stars.

951
01:21:30,590 --> 01:21:32,580
它们是那么遥远…
They're so far away...

952
01:21:33,020 --> 01:21:35,680
它们的光芒要很久才能到我们这里…
... and their light takes so long to reach us...

953
01:21:38,430 --> 01:21:42,620
而我们看到的只是他们过去的光影
... all we ever see of stars are their old photographs.

954
01:21:46,230 --> 01:21:50,070
在1959年7月，我恋爱了
It is July, 1959, and I am in love.

955
01:21:50,910 --> 01:21:52,570
照得不错
MAN: That's great.

956
01:21:52,740 --> 01:21:54,370
- 你明天就能来取相片 - 好的
- You can pick it up tomorrow. - Okay.

957
01:21:54,540 --> 01:21:56,270
- 75美分 - 好，谢谢你
- Seventy-five cents. - Okay, thank you.

958
01:21:56,440 --> 01:21:57,470
谢谢
Thank you.

959
01:21:57,650 --> 01:22:01,840
天啊，乔，真希望他刚才能给我们时间准备 我一定照得很丑
Gosh, Jon, I wish he gave us a little notice. I'm sure I made a face.

960
01:22:02,020 --> 01:22:07,010
噢，不会，我保证你一定很上镜
Oh, no, no. I'm sure that you'll look beautiful.

961
01:22:10,930 --> 01:22:13,260
她的名字是珍妮·斯莱特
Her name is Janey Slater.

962
01:22:14,100 --> 01:22:16,760
她是一个物理学家，和我一样
She is a physicist, like me.

963
01:22:18,030 --> 01:22:19,800
我那时30岁
I am 30 years old.

964
01:22:24,510 --> 01:22:28,440
我们是通过我一位大学同学 沃利·维勒，认识的
We were introduced by a good friend of mine from college, Wally Weaver.

965
01:22:32,610 --> 01:22:35,170
那是在1981年2月12日
It is February 12th, 1981.

966
01:22:35,350 --> 01:22:39,120
沃利死于癌症 死于他们现在说是我导致的癌症
Wally dies of cancer, of which they now say I am the cause.

967
01:22:56,100 --> 01:22:59,500
那一晚，珍妮和我第一次做爱
That night, Janey and I make love for the first time.

968
01:23:07,350 --> 01:23:10,340
一个月之后，那意外在等着我
A month from now, the accident awaits me.

969
01:23:17,830 --> 01:23:21,320
噢，我一会儿就赶上你们 我好像把手表留在了里面
Oh, I'll catch up with you guys. I think I left my watch inside.

970
01:23:22,000 --> 01:23:24,230
嘿，我们等等他吧
Hey. Let's just wait a second.

971
01:23:27,640 --> 01:23:32,040
我穿过房间，到了本征力场发生器中心 我找到了我的手表
I cross the room to the Intrinsic Field Center. I find my watch.

972
01:23:38,750 --> 01:23:39,910
当我走到门前时…
When I get to the door...

973
01:23:41,680 --> 01:23:42,880
沃利脸色都白了
... Wally is turning white.

974
01:23:43,050 --> 01:23:47,110
程序被锁死了，我们无法让计时器停下来
The program's locked in. We can't override the time lock.

975
01:23:48,490 --> 01:23:50,420
我被吓坏了
I am terrified.

976
01:23:50,590 --> 01:23:51,720
乔？
JANEY: Jon?

977
01:23:56,960 --> 01:23:58,730
对不起，乔…
I'm sorry, Jon...

978
01:24:00,670 --> 01:24:02,230
我不能眼睁睁看着…
...but I can't...

979
01:24:04,510 --> 01:24:06,030
珍妮，别离开我！
Janey, don't leave me!

980
01:24:06,570 --> 01:24:08,570
别离开我！
Don't leave me!

981
01:24:40,610 --> 01:24:45,380
那是在1959年5月12日，我和珍妮相见的时候
It is May 12th, 1959, when I'm introduced to Janey.

982
01:24:45,810 --> 01:24:48,010
她给我买了杯啤酒…
She buys me a beer...

983
01:24:48,220 --> 01:24:51,050
那是第一次有女人为我做这样的事
... the first time a woman has done this for me.

984
01:24:52,420 --> 01:24:56,250
当她递给我那冰冷、溢满的酒杯时…
As she passes me the cold, perspiring glass...

985
01:24:56,890 --> 01:24:58,120
我们的手指相碰了
... our fingers touch.

986
01:25:11,010 --> 01:25:13,170
好的，乔，干得不错
Yes, Jon, good.

987
01:25:13,340 --> 01:25:18,840
现在的问题只是 按照正确的顺序重新组装这些零件
Now it's just a question of reassembling the components in the correct sequence.

988
01:25:22,680 --> 01:25:23,780
我最后一次…
I feel fear...

989
01:25:25,020 --> 01:25:27,150
感觉到了恐惧
... for the last time.

990
01:25:43,970 --> 01:25:46,410
他们举行了一次象征性的葬礼
A token funeral is held.

991
01:25:46,570 --> 01:25:48,740
没有尸体可以埋葬
There is nothing to bury.

992
01:25:48,910 --> 01:25:51,500
珍妮把那张快照装裱了起来
Janey frames the snapshot.

993
01:25:51,710 --> 01:25:54,840
那是我留下来的唯一一张照片
It's the only photograph of me anyone has.

994
01:25:56,150 --> 01:26:01,020
有人在墙外看到了一副人体循环系统
A circulatory system is seen by the perimeter fence.

995
01:26:01,420 --> 01:26:02,890
几天后…
A few days later...

996
01:26:03,060 --> 01:26:06,290
人们在走廊 看到了一具覆盖了部分肌肉的人体骨骼
... a partially muscled skeleton stands in a hallway...

997
01:26:06,460 --> 01:26:10,290
在它消失之前，还尖叫了一阵
... and screams for a moment before vanishing.

998
01:26:35,660 --> 01:26:37,680
噢，上帝
Oh, God.

999
01:26:37,860 --> 01:26:39,380
乔？
Jon?

1000
01:26:40,430 --> 01:26:42,260
是你吗？
Is that you?

1001
01:26:42,930 --> 01:26:45,960
（NSB台晚间新闻） 全世界都震惊于今早发布的声明…
Nations around the world reeling from this morning's announcement...

1002
01:26:46,130 --> 01:26:48,760
这可能会是当代历史上最重大的事件
...possibly the most significant event in recent history.

1003
01:26:48,940 --> 01:26:53,000
我重复一次，超人存在着，而且他是美国人
We repeat, the superman exists, and he is American.

1004
01:26:59,380 --> 01:27:01,970
他们叫我曼哈顿博士…
They call me Dr. Manhattan.

1005
01:27:04,320 --> 01:27:06,250
他们解释说选这名字…
They explain the name has been chosen...

1006
01:27:06,420 --> 01:27:10,650
是要让美国的敌人们联想到噩兆 （曼哈顿计划让美国在二战时率先造出原子弹）
... for the ominous associations it will raise in America's enemies.

1007
01:27:15,260 --> 01:27:18,600
搞宣传的一位年轻人说我需要一个徽记
The marketing boys say I need a logo.

1008
01:27:27,410 --> 01:27:29,770
如果我要有个徽记…
If I'm to have a symbol...

1009
01:27:31,750 --> 01:27:34,370
就只能是我所敬仰的那个 （原子）
... it shall be one I respect.

1010
01:27:44,430 --> 01:27:47,450
他们把我塑造成了华而不实…
They are shaping me into something gaudy...

1011
01:27:48,530 --> 01:27:50,660
致命的东西
... something lethal.

1012
01:27:55,470 --> 01:27:57,990
在1971年1月…
In January, 1971...

1013
01:27:58,170 --> 01:28:02,130
尼克松总统要我出面干涉越战…
... President Nixon asks me to intervene in Vietnam...

1014
01:28:02,310 --> 01:28:05,070
一件他的前任不会要求我干的事
... something that his predecessors would not ask.

1015
01:28:06,380 --> 01:28:09,210
一周之后，战火结束了
A week later, the conflict ends.

1016
01:28:09,380 --> 01:28:13,820
其中一些越共士兵还向我个人投降
Some of the Vietcong forces wanna surrender to me personally.

1017
01:28:17,260 --> 01:28:20,850
霍利斯·梅森 一位退休的变装英雄，写了本书
Hollis Mason, a retired costume hero, writes a book.

1018
01:28:21,030 --> 01:28:25,860
书里，他说我的到来，象征着超级英雄的黎明
In it, he calls my arrival the dawn of the superhero.

1019
01:28:26,700 --> 01:28:29,430
我不确定我是否明白这句话的意思
I am not sure if I know what that means.

1020
01:28:45,920 --> 01:28:49,010
你看，当时，我引用错了词
WALLY: You see, at the time, I was misquoted.

1021
01:28:49,290 --> 01:28:52,350
我不应该说：“超人存在着，他是美国人”
I never said, "The superman exists and he is American."

1022
01:28:52,530 --> 01:28:58,490
我想说的是：“神存在着，他是美国人”
What I said was, "God exists, and he is American."

1023
01:28:59,000 --> 01:29:01,470
如果觉得这种说辞让你感到了…
Now, if you begin to feel an intense...

1024
01:29:01,640 --> 01:29:05,540
一种把你推向对个人狂热崇拜的信仰恐惧
...and crushing feeling of religious terror at the concept...

1025
01:29:05,970 --> 01:29:08,000
别恐慌
...don't be alarmed.

1026
01:29:08,640 --> 01:29:12,670
那说明你们的头脑依然清醒
That indicates only that you are still sane.

1027
01:29:15,150 --> 01:29:18,280
那是1963年的圣诞节
It is Christmas, 1963.

1028
01:29:18,620 --> 01:29:22,320
珍妮说她既害怕又担心
Janey tells me she is afraid, and worried.

1029
01:29:22,960 --> 01:29:25,750
她说我现在就像一个神
She says I am like a god now.

1030
01:29:26,460 --> 01:29:28,620
我告诉她神是不存在的
I tell her I don't think there is a God.

1031
01:29:28,800 --> 01:29:31,420
如果神真的存在，我和他绝不一样
And if there is, I'm nothing like him.

1032
01:29:36,200 --> 01:29:38,640
我告诉她我依然想拥有她…
I tell her I still want her...

1033
01:29:39,410 --> 01:29:41,400
永远想要拥有她
... and that I always will.

1034
01:29:44,480 --> 01:29:49,140
在1970年9月4日，我向她说了谎
As I lie to her, it is September 4th, 1970.

1035
01:29:49,980 --> 01:29:52,850
在变装英雄的聚会上
I am in a room full of people wearing disguises.

1036
01:29:54,320 --> 01:29:58,590
一个很年轻的女孩对着我笑
A very young girl looks at me and smiles.

1037
01:30:00,460 --> 01:30:02,450
她很美
She's beautiful.

1038
01:30:06,000 --> 01:30:11,900
在每次的热吻后 她都在我唇上留下一个小小的温柔的吻…
After each long kiss, she plants a smaller, gentler one upon my lips...

1039
01:30:12,070 --> 01:30:13,630
就像是一个签名
... like a signature.

1040
01:30:15,010 --> 01:30:18,170
珍妮指责我四处寻欢
Janey accuses me of chasing jailbait.

1041
01:30:18,680 --> 01:30:23,950
她突然愤怒地哭泣，问我是不是因为她变老了
She bursts into angry tears, asking if it's because she's getting older.

1042
01:30:24,120 --> 01:30:25,950
她说的对
It's true.

1043
01:30:28,020 --> 01:30:31,050
她每天都在明显地老去
She's aging more noticeably every day...

1044
01:30:37,630 --> 01:30:40,460
而我却不会变化
... while I am standing still.

1045
01:30:41,400 --> 01:30:44,060
我更喜欢这近乎静止的空间
I prefer the stillness here.

1046
01:30:45,040 --> 01:30:47,130
我厌倦了地球
I am tired of Earth.

1047
01:30:47,310 --> 01:30:48,970
地球上的人
These people.

1048
01:30:49,540 --> 01:30:53,240
我讨厌进入人类混乱的生活
I'm tired of being caught in the tangle of their lives.

1049
01:31:16,070 --> 01:31:19,400
他们声称自己在努力打造天堂…
They claim their labors are to build a heaven...

1050
01:31:19,970 --> 01:31:23,430
但他们的天堂仍充满着可怕的事
... yet their heaven is populated with horrors.

1051
01:31:23,910 --> 01:31:26,570
或许世界不是创造出来的
Perhaps the world is not made.

1052
01:31:27,580 --> 01:31:29,570
或许没有什么东西能够被创造
Perhaps nothing is made.

1053
01:31:30,420 --> 01:31:33,980
就像没有调校的钟表
A clock without a craftsman.

1054
01:31:34,920 --> 01:31:36,910
太晚了
It's too late.

1055
01:31:37,360 --> 01:31:39,260
从来都是…
Always has been...

1056
01:31:39,890 --> 01:31:43,330
永远都是…太晚了
... always will be too late.

1057
01:31:45,750 --> 01:31:48,450
而你不知道他会去哪里？
FORBES: And you have no idea where he would've gone.

1058
01:31:48,620 --> 01:31:49,920
我怎么会知道？
LAURIE: How would I know?

1059
01:31:50,090 --> 01:31:52,820
大概他只是在世界的另一端研究那些分子
Probably on the other side of the world studying molecules.

1060
01:31:52,990 --> 01:31:55,520
我们的卫星已经对地球作了一次扫荡式搜索
FORBES: Our satellites have done a sweep of the planet.

1061
01:31:55,690 --> 01:31:57,990
哪里都没有他能量信号的迹象
There's no trace of his energy signature anywhere.

1062
01:31:58,160 --> 01:31:59,460
真的？
Really?

1063
01:31:59,630 --> 01:32:03,030
朱庇特女士，今天你和曼哈顿博士吵架了吗？
Miss Jupiter, did you and Dr. Manhattan have a fight today?

1064
01:32:03,200 --> 01:32:04,690
这他妈不关你的事
None of your fucking business.

1065
01:32:04,870 --> 01:32:08,200
当你拿政府的薪水但却没干活的时候 就关我的事了
It is when you're on government payroll and you're not doing your job.

1066
01:32:09,040 --> 01:32:12,840
你说的话就相当于直接叫我“妓女” 佛比斯探员
That's as close to the word "whore" as you're gonna get with me, Agent Forbes.

1067
01:32:20,990 --> 01:32:22,480
来根烟吗？
Smoke?

1068
01:32:23,020 --> 01:32:25,250
向你致歉，朱庇特女士
My apologies, Miss Jupiter.

1069
01:32:25,420 --> 01:32:28,790
你了解曼哈顿博士对于我国国防来说有多重要
You know how important Dr. Manhattan is to our national security.

1070
01:32:29,690 --> 01:32:31,630
你能想象到我们很关心你们
You can imagine our concern.

1071
01:32:31,800 --> 01:32:33,320
我只能想象
I can only imagine.

1072
01:32:39,570 --> 01:32:43,560
当那些核弹开始飞舞，什么东西都没意义了 我们都会变成焦土
EDDIE: Ain't nothing gonna matter once those nukes start flying. We'll all be dust.

1073
01:32:44,010 --> 01:32:46,570
而后这位奥兹曼迪斯…
Then Ozymandias here...

1074
01:32:47,010 --> 01:32:49,780
将会成为废墟里最聪明的人
...will be the smartest man on the cinder.

1075
01:33:07,970 --> 01:33:11,060
劳丽？劳丽·简？
EDDIE: Laurel? Laurel Jane?

1076
01:33:12,600 --> 01:33:14,400
你是沙莉·朱庇特的女儿
You're Sally Jupiter's kid.

1077
01:33:15,310 --> 01:33:17,540
你是笑匠，对吧？
You're the Comedian, right?

1078
01:33:17,740 --> 01:33:19,210
你说那些话时很酷
You were pretty cool in there.

1079
01:33:20,010 --> 01:33:23,740
知道吗？你妈妈，她去到哪都是个选美冠军
You know, your mom, she was one of the all-time champion beauties.

1080
01:33:24,920 --> 01:33:29,250
你有她的眼睛，还有她那颗有趣的小胎记
You got her eyes, you know. You even have that same funny little mole.

1081
01:33:29,720 --> 01:33:31,620
别用你的手碰她！
Take your hands off her.

1082
01:33:31,790 --> 01:33:33,880
嘿，宝贝，好久不见
Hey, doll. Long time no see.

1083
01:33:34,060 --> 01:33:37,650
对我来说还不够久 上车
Not long enough in my book, Eddie. Get in the car.

1084
01:33:39,230 --> 01:33:41,220
你觉得沉沦的还不够彻底吗？
Are there no depths you won't sink to?

1085
01:33:41,400 --> 01:33:45,230
上帝啊，我就不能和我的…
Jesus Christ, Sally. Can't a guy talk to his...

1086
01:33:45,940 --> 01:33:47,630
老朋友的女儿说话？
...you know, old friend's daughter?

1087
01:33:47,810 --> 01:33:49,930
我说，你认为我是个什么样的人？
I mean, what the hell do you think I am?

1088
01:33:50,110 --> 01:33:51,770
找到他了
MAN: We found him!

1089
01:33:54,810 --> 01:33:56,910
- 找到他了 - 在哪儿？
- We found him. FORBES: Where is he?

1090
01:34:00,320 --> 01:34:01,650
火星
Mars.

1091
01:34:07,690 --> 01:34:09,680
总统先生…
Mr. President...

1092
01:34:09,860 --> 01:34:14,490
苏联军队已经把他们的坦克 开动到很接近阿富汗边界的地方
...the Soviets have moved their tanks just short of the Afghan border.

1093
01:34:16,070 --> 01:34:17,300
他们在测试我们…
They are testing us...

1094
01:34:17,470 --> 01:34:21,870
以求证是不是我们捏造了曼哈顿博士的失踪…
...to see if we manufactured Dr. Manhattan's disappearance...

1095
01:34:22,040 --> 01:34:25,130
由此引诱他们出击
...to coax a move out of them.

1096
01:34:25,310 --> 01:34:29,270
如果他们意识到这不是假的 他们首先大概会发动空中袭击
GENERAL 1: If they realize it's not a hoax, they'll probably start with air strikes.

1097
01:34:29,450 --> 01:34:33,510
他们如果这样做了 就会在几天之内控制阿富汗全境
If they do, they'll have Afghanistan under control in a matter of days.

1098
01:34:33,920 --> 01:34:38,620
那组核战争观察员已经把“末日时钟”…
A watchdog group of nuclear scientists has moved the Doomsday Clock...

1099
01:34:38,790 --> 01:34:41,020
拨到了差2分钟到午夜
...to two minutes until midnight.

1100
01:34:41,190 --> 01:34:44,360
把这鬼东西从屏幕上撤下来
NIXON: Get this shit off the screen.

1101
01:34:44,530 --> 01:34:47,560
这些混蛋们凭什么说末日临近了？
Who are these assholes to say when doomsday approaches?

1102
01:34:47,730 --> 01:34:50,200
应该由我说了算
I say when doomsday is approaching.

1103
01:34:55,870 --> 01:34:57,470
那么
Now, then.

1104
01:34:58,510 --> 01:35:01,000
华沙条约的其他成员国呢？
What about the rest of the Warsaw Pact countries?

1105
01:35:01,180 --> 01:35:05,380
捷克斯洛伐克、波兰和东德 已经动员他们的部队
Czechoslovakia, Poland and East Germany have mobilized their forces.

1106
01:35:05,550 --> 01:35:08,710
但是还没有动作，他们只是在观望
But no movement yet. They're playing a wait-and-see.

1107
01:35:08,890 --> 01:35:10,510
让俄罗斯领头
Letting the Russians take the lead.

1108
01:35:14,860 --> 01:35:18,060
果断地行动，亨利（亨利·基辛格，国务卿） 这才是我们现在需要的
Bold moves, Henry. That's what's needed right now.

1109
01:35:18,230 --> 01:35:20,990
不能让这些混蛋觉得我们很怯弱
We can't let these fuckers think we're weak.

1110
01:35:21,170 --> 01:35:25,430
是啊，他们一定怕“疯子尼克松”怕的要死
Yes. They must fear the madman Richard Nixon.

1111
01:35:30,510 --> 01:35:33,970
要多久我们才能准备好率先攻击？
How soon can we be ready for a preemptive strike?

1112
01:35:35,150 --> 01:35:36,170
两天之后
Two days.

1113
01:35:36,580 --> 01:35:40,450
我们有54%的几率在苏军的导弹击中目标之前…
We have a 54 percent chance of wiping out the entire U.S.S. R...

1114
01:35:40,620 --> 01:35:42,680
全歼他们
...before they get their missiles airborne.

1115
01:35:44,290 --> 01:35:45,880
那我们会损失什么？
What would our losses be?

1116
01:35:46,060 --> 01:35:47,920
在保守地估算…
Assuming conservative projections...

1117
01:35:48,090 --> 01:35:51,460
我们能预先摧毁的苏军核弹头数量之后
...of how many Soviet warheads are destroyed beforehand...

1118
01:35:51,630 --> 01:35:53,490
我们的东海岸会被摧毁
...we'll lose all of the East Coast.

1119
01:35:53,930 --> 01:35:55,460
这将是…
The last gasp...

1120
01:35:56,330 --> 01:35:58,800
哈佛校园的最后喘息了
...of the Harvard establishment.

1121
01:35:59,240 --> 01:36:02,500
让我们看看他们怎么走上绝路的
Let's see them think their way out of fission.

1122
01:36:02,670 --> 01:36:06,270
在预算了风向后，辐射云会飘往南方
With anticipated wind patterns, the fallout drift would head south.

1123
01:36:06,440 --> 01:36:08,640
墨西哥会遭受最大的影响
Mexico would catch the worst of it.

1124
01:36:08,810 --> 01:36:10,910
绝大部分的农场带不会受到污染
Most of the farm belt might remain unaffected.

1125
01:36:11,080 --> 01:36:12,780
不太坏…
Not so bad...

1126
01:36:13,590 --> 01:36:15,710
所有的可能都算到了
...all things considered.

1127
01:36:18,290 --> 01:36:20,120
总统先生…
GENERAL 2: Mr. President...

1128
01:36:20,290 --> 01:36:21,920
您打算怎么做？
...what would you like to do?

1129
01:36:30,270 --> 01:36:32,570
把国防等级提升到2级吧
Take us to DEFCON two.

1130
01:36:32,740 --> 01:36:34,730
开始给导弹加燃料
Begin fueling the bombers.

1131
01:36:35,340 --> 01:36:38,240
曼哈顿博士有两天时间回来
Dr. Manhattan has two days.

1132
01:36:38,680 --> 01:36:40,470
两天之后…
After that...

1133
01:36:40,650 --> 01:36:44,270
人类的命运就掌握在比我更高层的人手里了
...humanity is in the hands of a higher authority than mine.

1134
01:36:44,880 --> 01:36:47,850
让我们期待他站在我们这边吧
Let's just hope he's on our side.

1135
01:36:49,090 --> 01:36:51,180
- 肯定有办法接近他的 - 打搅了
FORBES: There must be a way to reach him. LAURIE: Excuse me.

1136
01:36:51,360 --> 01:36:53,020
无线电广播、太空飞船
FORBES: Radio transmission, space shuttles...

1137
01:36:53,190 --> 01:36:54,420
- 请问 - 什么事？
LAURIE: Excuse me. FORBES: What?

1138
01:36:54,590 --> 01:36:56,890
我要去趟洗手间
LAURIE: I need to use the restroom.

1139
01:37:18,480 --> 01:37:20,080
你还不明白吗？
Don't you understand?

1140
01:37:20,250 --> 01:37:22,880
能把乔带回地球的人只有他自己
The only thing that can bring Jon back is Jon.

1141
01:37:23,050 --> 01:37:25,020
如果他想找到我，他会做到的
If he wants to find me, he will.

1142
01:37:25,190 --> 01:37:27,660
我受够了好像囚犯一样的生活
I've been a prisoner in my life long enough.

1143
01:37:28,030 --> 01:37:29,720
缺少曼哈顿博士…
MAN: Without Dr. Manhattan around...

1144
01:37:29,890 --> 01:37:32,800
来迫使苏联甘守和平，维特先生…
...to bully the Russians into peace, Mr. Veidt...

1145
01:37:32,960 --> 01:37:37,370
人们将会需要依赖那些过时但实用的能源
...people are going to need good, old-fashioned energy to rely on.

1146
01:37:37,540 --> 01:37:39,200
你能明白的
You can understand.

1147
01:37:39,370 --> 01:37:44,470
全世界不能突然放弃使用原油和核子能
The world can't just quit on oil and nuclear power cold turkey.

1148
01:37:44,640 --> 01:37:46,870
你这样做会让经济在一夜之间崩溃的
You'll dismantle our entire economy overnight.

1149
01:37:47,050 --> 01:37:49,810
说的对，李，为什么要免费能源？
You're right, Lee. And why free energy?

1150
01:37:49,980 --> 01:37:52,880
看，“免费”其实就是“社会主义”的代名词
Well, "free" is just another word for "socialist."

1151
01:37:53,050 --> 01:37:55,020
我们将被迫开展一项关于…
We might have to make a public inquiry...

1152
01:37:55,190 --> 01:37:58,450
你和某些老共产主义分子有否关联的公开调查
...into any past communist affiliations you might have had.

1153
01:37:58,860 --> 01:38:01,720
拉科卡先生，各位…
ADRIAN: Mr. Lacocca, gentlemen...

1154
01:38:02,890 --> 01:38:05,120
作为企业的首脑们…
...I respect your position...

1155
01:38:05,300 --> 01:38:09,200
我的的确确尊重你们的立场和以往的功绩
...and what you've accomplished as captains of industry. I do.

1156
01:38:09,600 --> 01:38:12,090
你们想了解我的过去？嗯？
You wanna know my past? Hm?

1157
01:38:12,900 --> 01:38:15,630
好吧，愉快之至
Okay. Happily.

1158
01:38:15,810 --> 01:38:19,270
众所周知，我的双亲在我17岁时同时过世了…
It's a matter of public record that by 17, both my parents were dead...

1159
01:38:19,440 --> 01:38:21,280
留下了孤独的我
...leaving me alone.

1160
01:38:22,280 --> 01:38:25,650
我猜你们会说，我总是很孤僻
I guess you could say I've always been alone.

1161
01:38:25,820 --> 01:38:30,720
他们说我是这世上最聪明的人 但我时常觉得自己很愚蠢…
They say I'm the smartest man in the world, but the truth is I've often felt stupid...

1162
01:38:30,890 --> 01:38:34,380
因为我不懂得与其他人相处…
...at being unable to relate to anyone.

1163
01:38:34,560 --> 01:38:37,960
与其他活着的人
Well, anyone living, that is.

1164
01:38:38,130 --> 01:38:40,100
唯一一位我认为和我有血亲的人…
The only person with whom I felt kinship...

1165
01:38:40,270 --> 01:38:43,390
在耶稣降世300年之前就死了
...died 300 years before the birth of Christ.

1166
01:38:43,570 --> 01:38:48,940
马其顿的亚历山大 或者你们熟知的：伟大的亚历山大大帝 （那位把疆土从希腊打到印度的马其顿国王）
Alexander of Macedonia, or Alexander the Great, as you know him.

1167
01:38:49,110 --> 01:38:52,130
他对于世界大团结的瞩望…
His vision of a united world was...

1168
01:38:55,450 --> 01:38:57,140
其实，是史无前例的
Well, it was unprecedented.

1169
01:38:57,320 --> 01:38:59,010
我希望…
I wanted...

1170
01:38:59,180 --> 01:39:01,480
我必须要达到他的功绩…
...needed to match his accomplishments...

1171
01:39:01,650 --> 01:39:04,850
所以我决定用这古训教谕现世
...so I resolved to apply antiquity's teachings to our world today.

1172
01:39:05,020 --> 01:39:08,520
于是开始了我的征服之路
And so began my path to conquest.

1173
01:39:08,690 --> 01:39:11,920
不单只是征服人类…
Conquest not of men...

1174
01:39:12,100 --> 01:39:14,930
连同那些侵扰人类的罪恶
...but of the evils that beset them.

1175
01:39:15,170 --> 01:39:20,070
矿物燃料、原油、核子能…
Fossil fuels, oil, nuclear power...

1176
01:39:20,240 --> 01:39:23,070
如同毒品，而你们，还有那些国外投资者…
...are like a drug, and you, along with foreign interests...

1177
01:39:23,240 --> 01:39:24,870
- 就是这些毒品的推销者 - 好了，听着
...are the pushers. - Now, listen.

1178
01:39:25,440 --> 01:39:27,070
不
ADRIAN: No.

1179
01:39:29,410 --> 01:39:31,210
你们听着
You listen.

1180
01:39:32,450 --> 01:39:34,940
这世界会存活下来…
The world will survive...

1181
01:39:35,150 --> 01:39:38,590
并且值得拥有比你们所能提供的更好的东西
...and it deserves more than you've been able to provide.

1182
01:39:38,760 --> 01:39:41,350
让我们直切主题，好吧？
So let's cut to it, shall we?

1183
01:39:41,630 --> 01:39:44,090
我比你们所有的公司加起来还有价值
I'm worth more than all of your corporations combined.

1184
01:39:44,260 --> 01:39:47,860
我可以收购并出售你们 这点你们可以在作决定时考虑进去
I could buy and sell you, something you should factor into your decision...

1185
01:39:48,030 --> 01:39:54,340
或者选择把我们之间的不和公布于众
...should you choose to make our disagreement public.

1186
01:39:55,810 --> 01:39:58,240
我想你知道该怎么做了
I think you know the way out.

1187
01:39:59,980 --> 01:40:01,710
失陪了
Gentlemen.

1188
01:40:04,220 --> 01:40:07,710
玩具公司的人想和你商讨 关于这版奥兹曼迪斯系列玩具中的新坏人造型
The toy people wanna talk to you about new villains for the Ozymandias line.

1189
01:40:07,890 --> 01:40:11,340
- 貌似老敌人都死光了 - 维特先生？
- Seems all the old villains are dead. - Mr. Veidt?

1190
01:40:11,520 --> 01:40:15,080
- 我想我有些建议 - 维特先生？
- I think I have some ideas. - Mr. Veidt?

1191
01:40:15,260 --> 01:40:18,060
我想我们起步就走错了
I think we got off on the wrong foot.

1192
01:40:57,070 --> 01:40:58,760
他嘴里有剧毒胶囊
He's got a poison capsule.

1193
01:40:59,440 --> 01:41:03,900
不准吞下去，你这混蛋！ 谁派你来的？说！
Don't bite down, you son of a bitch. Who sent you? I want a name.

1194
01:41:04,080 --> 01:41:05,170
给我说！
Give me a name!

1195
01:41:17,290 --> 01:41:18,590
自杀胶囊
LAURIE: Suicide pill.

1196
01:41:19,690 --> 01:41:22,630
剧毒氰化物，入口既亡
Potassium cyanide. Guy was dead before he hit the ground.

1197
01:41:22,790 --> 01:41:24,630
谢谢，侯
WAITRESS: Thanks, hon.

1198
01:41:25,130 --> 01:41:27,150
罗夏说对了
Then Rorschach was right.

1199
01:41:27,330 --> 01:41:29,490
这不是个别人的单打独斗
This wasn't some Ione nut.

1200
01:41:29,670 --> 01:41:33,800
他们是有组织的，而且资金充足，装备精良
It's an organization: Well-funded, well-equipped.

1201
01:41:34,770 --> 01:41:36,710
但现在这时候谁会想要杀我们？
But who'd wanna kill us now?

1202
01:41:38,010 --> 01:41:41,140
我不知道，但是外面已经不安全了
I don't know, but it's not safe out here.

1203
01:41:46,680 --> 01:41:48,650
有乔的消息吗？
So no word from Jon?

1204
01:41:49,620 --> 01:41:51,250
没有
No.

1205
01:41:51,620 --> 01:41:53,520
是这样
Well, listen...

1206
01:41:54,030 --> 01:41:55,720
为什么你不过来和我一起住呢？
...why don't you come stay with me?

1207
01:41:57,060 --> 01:42:00,050
不了，谢谢你的好意，但我不想去打扰你
Oh, no. That's sweet, but I wouldn't wanna impose.

1208
01:42:00,530 --> 01:42:03,900
哦，不，你就当帮我个忙好了
Oh, no. No. Think of it as doing me a favor.

1209
01:42:05,740 --> 01:42:08,070
这样我就不用担心你一人在外了
I wouldn't have to worry about you being out there.

1210
01:42:11,480 --> 01:42:12,700
好吧
Okay.

1211
01:42:15,780 --> 01:42:21,220
罗夏日记，1985年10月21日
Rorschach's journal, October 21 st, 1985.

1212
01:42:21,390 --> 01:42:25,480
在第43街和第3街交叉口，看见德雷伯格和朱庇特 吃完晚餐出来
On 43rd and 7th, saw Dreiberg and Jupiter leaving diner.

1213
01:42:26,160 --> 01:42:28,820
我不戴面具他们就不认识我
They didn't know me without my mask.

1214
01:42:29,660 --> 01:42:31,320
难道是红杏出墙？
An affair?

1215
01:42:31,500 --> 01:42:34,360
难道她想伤曼哈顿博士的心来报复他的离去？
Did she break Manhattan's heart to engineer his exile...

1216
01:42:34,530 --> 01:42:37,520
让德雷伯格有机可乘？
... to make room for Dreiberg?

1217
01:42:37,700 --> 01:42:41,160
曼哈顿有没有一颗心来为她碎呢？
Does Manhattan even have a heart to break?

1218
01:42:42,410 --> 01:42:45,200
小巷阴冷而又荒凉
The alley was cold, deserted.

1219
01:42:45,380 --> 01:42:49,970
我的宝贝们静静地等着我
My things were where I left them, waiting for me.

1220
01:42:50,150 --> 01:42:54,520
我的大衣，鞋子，干净的手套
My coat, my shoes, my spotless gloves.

1221
01:42:56,050 --> 01:42:57,990
还有我的面具
My face.

1222
01:42:58,220 --> 01:43:02,160
穿上他们，我就卸下了伪装
Putting them on, I abandoned my disguise...

1223
01:43:02,330 --> 01:43:04,450
变回真正的自己
... became myself.

1224
01:43:04,960 --> 01:43:08,060
不再恐惧和软弱
Free from fear or weakness...

1225
01:43:08,230 --> 01:43:09,320
或有欲念
... or lust.

1226
01:43:10,900 --> 01:43:12,770
小巷深处
Down alley...

1227
01:43:12,940 --> 01:43:14,800
女人呼救声
... heard woman scream.

1228
01:43:14,970 --> 01:43:18,970
奏响了城市夜曲的第一章
First bubbling note of city's evening chorus.

1229
01:43:19,140 --> 01:43:20,940
是强奸？
Attempted rape.

1230
01:43:21,110 --> 01:43:22,270
抢劫？
Mugging.

1231
01:43:22,450 --> 01:43:23,910
或都是？
Both.

1232
01:43:25,420 --> 01:43:27,110
那人转过身来
The man turned...

1233
01:43:27,290 --> 01:43:30,470
从他的眼神里我得到了满足
... and there was something rewarding in his eyes.

1234
01:43:31,470 --> 01:43:33,940
有时候夜晚对我很慷慨
Sometimes the night is generous to me.

1235
01:43:40,050 --> 01:43:44,380
去杀维特的是个当地人 身份不明，只知道他叫罗伊·切丝
Veidt's assassin was a local lowlife named Roy Chess.

1236
01:43:44,950 --> 01:43:47,710
在他的住处我找到了些线索
At his apartment, I found clues.

1237
01:43:48,920 --> 01:43:51,980
貌似他在金字塔跨国公司工作
Seems he worked at Pyramid Transnational.

1238
01:43:52,160 --> 01:43:54,720
我以前就见过这个标志
I've seen the logo before...

1239
01:43:55,130 --> 01:43:57,190
在死神家里
... at Moloch's.

1240
01:44:27,560 --> 01:44:30,390
今天有人想谋杀天下第一聪明人，死神
Someone tried to shoot the world's smartest man today, Moloch.

1241
01:44:31,330 --> 01:44:34,130
金字塔跨国公司的人
Guy worked for Pyramid Transnational.

1242
01:44:34,300 --> 01:44:36,430
我觉得这应该不仅仅是送货服务吧
More than a just delivery service, I take it.

1243
01:44:36,600 --> 01:44:40,540
我上次来的时候 见到同一个公司签发的抚恤金支票
Last time I was here, I saw a pension check written from the same company.

1244
01:44:40,710 --> 01:44:44,200
我觉得这是个幌子 有人想让别人都以为我们死了
I'm guessing it's a front set up by whoever wants us masks dead.

1245
01:44:44,380 --> 01:44:47,970
别再撒谎了，死神 谁开的金字塔公司？
Now, no more lies, Moloch. Who runs Pyramid?

1246
01:44:52,850 --> 01:44:54,480
罗夏
FINE [O VER BULLHORN]: Rorschach.

1247
01:44:54,650 --> 01:44:57,020
警察，我们知道你们在里面
This is the police. We know you're in there.

1248
01:44:57,190 --> 01:44:59,050
不，不！
No. No!

1249
01:44:59,220 --> 01:45:02,350
如果有人和你在一起，请让他们安全地出来
If there's anybody in there with you, send them out unharmed.

1250
01:45:02,530 --> 01:45:05,460
不，不，不，不
No. No, no, no!

1251
01:45:05,630 --> 01:45:10,030
我被陷害了，如此容易就上当了 我真是太蠢了，蠢到家了
Framed. Walked right into it. Stupid, stupid, stupid!

1252
01:45:10,200 --> 01:45:11,830
永远，永远不要投降
Never, never surrender.

1253
01:45:12,000 --> 01:45:15,000
好吧，我希望你已经准备好了，大英雄
All right. I hope you're ready, hero.

1254
01:45:15,170 --> 01:45:16,200
随时奉陪
When you are.

1255
01:45:38,900 --> 01:45:39,920
一
One...

1256
01:45:44,940 --> 01:45:45,990
二
...two...

1257
01:45:50,010 --> 01:45:51,070
三
...three.

1258
01:46:43,060 --> 01:46:44,820
加把劲
Come on.

1259
01:46:55,640 --> 01:46:57,070
这个混蛋
MAN: Son of a bitch.

1260
01:46:58,040 --> 01:47:00,440
- 天，这家伙臭死了 - 把他的面具拿掉
- Christ, he stinks. - Get that mask off him.

1261
01:47:00,610 --> 01:47:03,450
- 拿下了 - 不，不！
- I got it. - No. No!

1262
01:47:03,620 --> 01:47:06,310
我的面具，把我面具还我
My face! Give me back my face!

1263
01:47:07,150 --> 01:47:09,780
蒙面孤胆英雄罗夏已被逮捕
The masked vigilante Rorschach was apprehended...

1264
01:47:09,950 --> 01:47:13,790
证实他是一位35岁的白人男性 名叫沃特·科瓦克斯
... and identified as Walter Kovacs, a 35-year-old white male.

1265
01:47:13,960 --> 01:47:17,020
大家对沃特的情况不甚了解 不过他已因为涉嫌
Little's known about Kovacs, but he was charged with the murder...

1266
01:47:17,200 --> 01:47:21,030
谋杀埃德加·雅各比而被收监 后者在纽约布朗克斯区的家中额头中枪而死
... of Edgar Jacobi, found shot in the head in his home in the Bronx.

1267
01:47:21,200 --> 01:47:24,230
在艰难的抓捕行动中
Police officers were injured and Jacobi's home was set ablaze...

1268
01:47:24,400 --> 01:47:26,960
多名警员受伤，雅各比的家也被大火烧毁
... during the violent course of the capture.

1269
01:47:30,780 --> 01:47:32,070
罗夏
MAN 1: Rorschach!

1270
01:47:32,240 --> 01:47:35,970
我会像干你妈一样干死你
I'm gonna fuck you like I fucked your mother!

1271
01:47:42,620 --> 01:47:45,560
罗夏，出来
MAN 2: Come on out, Rorschach!

1272
01:47:48,460 --> 01:47:51,090
（头条：罗夏显露真面目） 我就知道这家伙是个疯子
BERNIE: I knew this guy was a kook.

1273
01:47:51,660 --> 01:47:53,060
但是罗夏…
But Rorschach...

1274
01:47:53,230 --> 01:47:56,000
通常我对这类事情都有一种直觉
Usually I got an intuition about these kind of things.

1275
01:47:56,170 --> 01:47:58,570
- 还以为这家伙块头会大些 - 如你所见，小鬼…
- Thought the dude would be bigger. - It goes to show you, kid...

1276
01:47:58,740 --> 01:48:00,570
- …总有想不到的 - 嘿，给我来份公报
...you never know. - Hey, let me get a Gazette.

1277
01:48:00,740 --> 01:48:04,570
好，嘿，看到这个了吗？ 他原来是我的一个老主顾
Yeah. Hey, you see this? He was a customer of mine.

1278
01:48:04,740 --> 01:48:07,710
- 经常来我这里 - 真的？
- Used to come here all the time. - No shit?

1279
01:48:09,580 --> 01:48:12,310
嘿，伯尼，有好消息吗？
Hey, Bernie. Any good news?

1280
01:48:22,090 --> 01:48:25,460
不管我们是谁，不管我们身处何方
MARINER: Whoever we are, wherever we reside...

1281
01:48:25,630 --> 01:48:28,460
我们依靠伤天害理的妄想而存活
... we exist on the whim of murderers.

1282
01:48:33,140 --> 01:48:36,110
我几乎认不出我的老朋友瑞德里
I hardly recognized my old friend Ridley.

1283
01:48:36,270 --> 01:48:39,400
我无法迫使自己去对他说 这只是原来的他的…
I could not bring myself to tell him he was a horrible reflection...

1284
01:48:39,580 --> 01:48:41,480
…一副可怕的倒影
... of his former self.

1285
01:48:41,780 --> 01:48:46,310
我必须要在…在他变得更糟之前 带他回家
I really must get him home before... Before he gets any worse.

1286
01:48:46,480 --> 01:48:48,610
在他死之前
Before he succumbs.

1287
01:48:49,090 --> 01:48:54,580
我在以前每天一起喝小酒的时候听说过 饮用咸水是不会死人的
I've heard that on less than a pint daily, a man might survive drinking saltwater.

1288
01:48:54,760 --> 01:48:56,090
船长?
RIDLEY: Captain?

1289
01:48:56,260 --> 01:48:57,730
你在干什么，船长？
What are you doing, captain?

1290
01:49:00,270 --> 01:49:03,100
我要去戴维斯敦，干这个
I'm headed for Davidstown. That's what.

1291
01:49:03,570 --> 01:49:06,260
我要去提醒大家
I need to warn everyone.

1292
01:49:08,740 --> 01:49:12,270
你以为你会在黑货船号之前赶到戴维斯敦？
You think you'll reach Davidstown in advance of the Black Freighter?

