02:03:55,870 --> 02:03:58,210
这肯定也是乔眼中的世界了
This must be the way Jon sees the world.

1452
02:04:00,710 --> 02:04:03,550
我们吃饭吧，都快凉了
We should probably head up. Food's getting cold.

1453
02:04:03,780 --> 02:04:05,880
看完了记得把它放回去
Put those away when you're done.

1454
02:04:14,860 --> 02:04:17,190
苏联大使和联合国都没有发表任何
MAN [ON TV]: Soviet ambassador to the U.N. Had no comment...

1455
02:04:17,360 --> 02:04:19,630
关于曼哈顿博士消失的评论
... when asked if Dr. Manhattan's disappearance...

1456
02:04:19,800 --> 02:04:22,130
加速了苏联在阿富汗的侵略
... has fueled Soviet aggression in Afghanistan.

1457
02:04:22,300 --> 02:04:24,000
丹
Dan.

1458
02:04:24,740 --> 02:04:26,470
乔能看见很多东西
Jon sees a lot of things...

1459
02:04:28,870 --> 02:04:31,170
但他看不见我
...but he doesn't see me.

1460
02:04:38,320 --> 02:04:39,840
这个，嗯...
Well, uh...

1461
02:04:58,070 --> 02:04:59,630
哦
Oh.

1462
02:05:33,470 --> 02:05:34,800
抱歉
Sorry.

1463
02:05:36,810 --> 02:05:38,140
过来
Come here.

1464
02:05:44,080 --> 02:05:45,340
怎么了？
What's the matter?

1465
02:05:45,520 --> 02:05:47,950
- 你能挪一下你的 - 好的
- Lf you could just move a little... - Okay.

1466
02:05:48,120 --> 02:05:50,350
嗯，好
Yeah. There you go.

1467
02:05:56,860 --> 02:05:59,490
丹，怎么了？
Dan, what's wrong?

1468
02:06:01,170 --> 02:06:02,290
抱歉，我
Sorry, I...

1469
02:06:04,440 --> 02:06:06,670
对，我要走开一下
Yeah, I just need a couple minutes.

1470
02:06:08,840 --> 02:06:10,770
哦，见鬼了
Oh, hell.

1471
02:06:12,540 --> 02:06:14,380
没事的
It's okay.

1472
02:06:15,780 --> 02:06:20,220
可能我们发展太快了
Maybe we were just moving too fast.

1473
02:06:23,790 --> 02:06:26,420
我们有大把的时间
We've got all the time in the world.

1474
02:06:27,930 --> 02:06:29,920
慢慢来
We'll take it slow.

1475
02:06:43,910 --> 02:06:46,240
好久不见，罗夏
It's been a long time, Rorschach.

1476
02:06:46,910 --> 02:06:48,400
大块头
RORSCHACH: Big Figure.

1477
02:06:48,750 --> 02:06:50,580
这世界真小
Small world.

1478
02:06:51,920 --> 02:06:53,410
我喜欢这样
I like that.

1479
02:06:54,190 --> 02:06:56,590
不过你得知道，冤家路窄
But you know, it is a small world in here.

1480
02:06:57,020 --> 02:06:59,790
我已经在这呆了多久了，李昂德？
And I've been in it for, how long now, Lloyd?

1481
02:06:59,960 --> 02:07:02,090
大概15年了，大块头先生
LLO YD: Almost 15 years, Mr. Figure.

1482
02:07:02,430 --> 02:07:03,760
对
That's right.

1483
02:07:04,760 --> 02:07:08,250
自从你和你的同伙把我抓进来已经15年了
Fifteen years since you and that Owl fella put me away.

1484
02:07:11,270 --> 02:07:12,430
那么
So...

1485
02:07:12,940 --> 02:07:17,700
罗夏，你烫伤的那个人已经不行 随时都可能死掉
...Rorschach, that guy you burned is dying. Could go any minute.

1486
02:07:17,880 --> 02:07:23,070
知道吗？我大概统计了一下 这里有50多号都是你抓进来的
You know, by my count, there are more than 50 people in here that you put away.

1487
02:07:23,250 --> 02:07:27,580
我和他们每个人都谈过了 大家都恨不得吃了你
I been talking to every one of them and they're all dying to get a piece of you.

1488
02:07:27,750 --> 02:07:31,050
这里将会爆炸！
This place is gonna explode!

1489
02:07:32,620 --> 02:07:35,290
你会被慢慢折磨死
Then, you die by inches.

1490
02:07:36,230 --> 02:07:37,890
离谱
Tall order.

1491
02:07:38,130 --> 02:07:40,620
我要把这家伙撕碎
I'm gonna tear this guy a new hole.

1492
02:07:41,300 --> 02:07:44,290
别激动，劳伦斯，快了
Relax, Lawrence. Soon.

1493
02:07:45,140 --> 02:07:46,470
走吧
Come on.

1494
02:09:20,370 --> 02:09:22,420
告诉你吧，朋友
MARINER: Know this, my friends.

1495
02:09:22,600 --> 02:09:23,690
死神是湿滑的
Hades is wet.

1496
02:09:25,040 --> 02:09:26,590
死神是孤独的
Hades is lonely.

1497
02:09:42,450 --> 02:09:46,220
在那一刻，我们认识了对方
And in that instant, we knew each other.

1498
02:10:22,630 --> 02:10:24,890
很抱歉，我的朋友
I'm sorry, my friend.

1499
02:10:45,120 --> 02:10:48,020
我的木筏已经变得越发离奇古怪
My raft had grown increasingly grotesque...

1500
02:10:48,620 --> 02:10:51,650
直接反映着我自身的变化
... reflecting my own transformation.

1501
02:11:05,240 --> 02:11:09,300
漂流中，我最黑暗的想象 在我脑海中自由地涌现
Adrift, my darkest imaginings welled up unchecked...

1502
02:11:09,470 --> 02:11:12,600
如同黑墨水般从脑中溢向心中
... spilling from brain to heart like black ink...

1503
02:11:12,780 --> 02:11:15,210
无法抹除
... impossible to remove.

1504
02:11:24,060 --> 02:11:27,050
那艘船肯定早已到达戴维斯敦
The vessel had surely reached Davidstown already.

1505
02:11:27,890 --> 02:11:32,300
我想象着宁静的街道被黑货船号下来的恶魔 占据的景象
I pictured quiet streets overrun by the fiends from the Black Freighter.

1506
02:11:32,460 --> 02:11:35,690
我的妻子，我的孩子，大概已经死了
My wife, my children, most certainly dead.

1507
02:11:35,870 --> 02:11:37,860
我的船员，死了
My crew, dead.

1508
02:11:38,040 --> 02:11:41,700
我乘坐的这头野兽，死了
The beast I ride on, dead.

1509
02:11:50,650 --> 02:11:53,580
更多血，更多血，更多血
VOICES [CHANTING]: More blood, more blood, more blood.

1510
02:12:07,900 --> 02:12:09,230
爸爸？
GIRL: Father?

1511
02:12:09,400 --> 02:12:11,870
这不可能，哦，上帝 这不可能
It can't be. Oh, Lord, it can't be.

1512
02:12:12,040 --> 02:12:15,270
爸爸，救救我们，求求你
Father, help us. Please.

1513
02:12:15,440 --> 02:12:16,460
等等
MARINER: Wait.

1514
02:12:18,180 --> 02:12:19,200
我就来
I'm coming.

1515
02:12:19,980 --> 02:12:21,310
快来，亲爱的
Hurry, my dear.

1516
02:12:22,080 --> 02:12:24,980
等等，除了她们谁都行
Wait. Anyone but them.

1517
02:12:25,150 --> 02:12:26,780
谁都行
Anyone.

1518
02:12:27,050 --> 02:12:28,610
谁都行
Anyone.

1519
02:12:32,890 --> 02:12:35,120
我吞下了太多的海水
I'd swallowed too much seawater.

1520
02:12:35,290 --> 02:12:38,130
我吞下了太多的恐怖
I'd swallowed too much horror.

1521
02:12:41,600 --> 02:12:42,860
上天对我下了诅咒
God has damned me.

1522
02:12:44,000 --> 02:12:46,630
上天对我们都下了诅咒
God has damned us all.

1523
02:12:46,800 --> 02:12:52,740
的确，生活就是地狱 而暴死是我们唯一的解脱
Truly, life is hell, and death's rough hand our only deliverance.

1524
02:12:53,480 --> 02:12:55,600
我不能再忍受了
I can endure no more.

1525
02:12:55,780 --> 02:12:59,680
我急切地想要追随我的家人
I want to join my family desperately.

1526
02:13:07,490 --> 02:13:09,320
嘿
MAN: Yo, man.

1527
02:13:09,860 --> 02:13:11,690
在看什么呢？
What you reading?

1528
02:13:12,900 --> 02:13:14,390
没什么，老兄
Nothing, man.

1529
02:13:15,770 --> 02:13:18,330
- 没什么，哈？ - 嘿，嘿，你别碰这个小鬼
- Nothing, huh? - Hey, hey! You leave that kid alone!

1530
02:13:18,500 --> 02:13:20,200
闭嘴，老家伙
Shut up, old man!

1531
02:13:29,010 --> 02:13:31,710
你在看的是漫画书？ 你怎么了，弱智吗？
You're reading a comic book? What are you, retarded?

1532
02:13:39,020 --> 02:13:42,050
嘿，你要到哪儿去，小弱智？
Aw, hey, where you going, short bus?

1533
02:13:52,340 --> 02:13:53,670
丹?
Dan?

1534
02:14:00,510 --> 02:14:02,170
你没事吧?
Is everything all right?

1535
02:14:04,520 --> 02:14:07,450
我厌倦了担惊受怕
I'm tired of being afraid.

1536
02:14:08,520 --> 02:14:10,890
害怕战争
Afraid of war...

1537
02:14:11,690 --> 02:14:15,250
害怕面具杀手
...afraid of the mask killer...

1538
02:14:16,860 --> 02:14:20,060
害怕这该死的衣服
...and afraid of this goddamn suit...

1539
02:14:20,230 --> 02:14:22,200
以及我是多么需要这一切
...and how much I need it.

1540
02:14:23,030 --> 02:14:24,700
我也是
Me too.

1541
02:14:26,200 --> 02:14:27,500
那就让他们见鬼去吧
So to hell with it.

1542
02:14:28,370 --> 02:14:29,700
我们开阿基米德出去吧
Let's take Archie out.

1543
02:14:35,650 --> 02:14:36,770
你是认真的吗？
You're serious.

1544
02:14:36,950 --> 02:14:39,470
我以前也是面具杀手，没忘吧？
I used to be a masked avenger too, remember?

1545
02:14:39,650 --> 02:14:42,880
我以前经常半夜3点出去，做一些傻事
I'm used to going out at 3 in the morning and doing something stupid.

1546
02:15:44,620 --> 02:15:46,710
紧急火情，所有单位，听候指示
MAN [O VER RADIO]: Rapid burner. Be advised, all units.

1547
02:15:46,880 --> 02:15:49,440
梧兰特大街和第五大街处失火
Tenement fire at 5th and Grand. Rapid burner.

1548
02:15:49,620 --> 02:15:50,950
走吧
Let's go.

1549
02:15:55,730 --> 02:15:58,090
- 我看到了 - 好的，抓紧了
LAURIE: I can see it. DAN: All right, hold on.

1550
02:16:08,940 --> 02:16:10,370
丹，里面有孩子
LAURIE: Dan, there are kids in there.

1551
02:16:10,540 --> 02:16:12,700
每个人都请待在原处，保持镇静
Everyone, stay where you are and remain calm.

1552
02:16:12,880 --> 02:16:15,070
我们会把你们救出去的
We're gonna get you out of there.

1553
02:16:15,250 --> 02:16:17,410
屋顶就快塌了，让我进去
The roof's starting to cave. Get me in there.

1554
02:16:17,580 --> 02:16:19,050
我再靠近一点
DAN: I'm gonna get you close.

1555
02:17:17,810 --> 02:17:19,170
快走
Let's go.

1556
02:17:19,340 --> 02:17:20,500
赶快
Come on.

1557
02:17:20,680 --> 02:17:22,270
来，都上去
All right, let's move it, people.

1558
02:17:29,020 --> 02:17:33,820
妈妈，那人坐的是火箭吗？
Mom, is that guy in the space rocket?

1559
02:17:34,260 --> 02:17:36,490
他是耶稣嘛？
Is that Jesus?

1560
02:17:36,660 --> 02:17:38,490
不，亲爱的
No, baby.

1561
02:17:39,400 --> 02:17:41,520
- 小心一点 - 好的
DAN: Watch your step. LAURIE: All right.

1562
02:17:43,870 --> 02:17:44,890
我们上来了
We're all set.

1563
02:17:45,940 --> 02:17:47,600
都到齐了吗？
Is that everyone?

1564
02:18:11,660 --> 02:18:13,960
再见！
MAN: Bye. GIRL: Bye!

1565
02:18:17,570 --> 02:18:19,130
不敢相信我们这么做了
LAURIE: I can't believe we did that.

1566
02:18:21,110 --> 02:18:23,570
- 他们会把我们和罗夏关在一起的 - 管他呢
- They'll lock us up with Rorschach. - Who cares?

1567
02:18:23,740 --> 02:18:25,710
可能明天第三次世界大战就开打了
World War III could start tomorrow.

1568
02:18:27,810 --> 02:18:29,140
对吧？
Right?

1569
02:18:30,810 --> 02:18:32,150
对
Right.

1570
02:20:57,260 --> 02:20:59,160
给我回来！
MAN: Come back here!

1571
02:21:01,770 --> 02:21:03,460
他死了，罗夏
He's dead, Rorschach.

1572
02:21:03,630 --> 02:21:07,830
当大家在暴乱的时候 我们却觉得应该给你份乔迁新居的礼物
While everyone's distracted, we thought we'd bring you a housewarming gift.

1573
02:21:08,010 --> 02:21:10,170
机械店买的
Something from the machine shop.

1574
02:21:11,810 --> 02:21:13,440
头儿，你注意到没有？
Hey, boss, you notice?

1575
02:21:13,610 --> 02:21:16,640
他不再说什么世界真小和离谱 那样的废话了
None of that "small world, tall order" crap.

1576
02:21:16,810 --> 02:21:20,050
他知道一旦我们切开他的门锁 他就完蛋了
He knows once we slice open his lock, he's next on the block.

1577
02:21:20,480 --> 02:21:21,610
没门
Fat chance.

1578
02:21:22,320 --> 02:21:23,450
你死定了，罗夏
You're dead, Rorschach!

1579
02:21:23,620 --> 02:21:27,280
我们有一整监狱想杀你的人，你有什么？
We got a prison full of killers out here. What do you got?

1580
02:21:30,230 --> 02:21:32,660
你的手，我很荣幸
Your hands, my pleasure.

1581
02:21:34,670 --> 02:21:36,660
我没法够到门锁，要把栏杆锯断吗？
LLO YD: Can't reach the lock. Should I cut the bars?

1582
02:21:36,830 --> 02:21:40,130
暴乱不会持续多久 我等了15年就等今天了
This riot won't last. I been waiting 15 years for this.

1583
02:21:41,270 --> 02:21:44,640
抱歉劳伦斯，你挡到我的复仇之路了
I'm sorry, Lawrence, but you're in the way of my revenge.

1584
02:21:48,350 --> 02:21:50,070
这不是针对你的，伙计
Nothing personal, big guy.

1585
02:21:51,520 --> 02:21:53,510
头儿！等等！
Boss! Wait!

1586
02:22:07,660 --> 02:22:09,460
你该清楚现在的比分了吧？
Now you find out what the score is.

1587
02:22:09,900 --> 02:22:13,030
1比O，有种就进来
One-nothing. Come and get me.

1588
02:22:19,080 --> 02:22:20,740
快点
Come on.

1589
02:22:20,910 --> 02:22:22,540
我一直在想
DAN: So I've been thinking.

1590
02:22:23,480 --> 02:22:27,640
我觉得我们要对我们的同伴负责
I feel that we have an obligation to our fraternity.

1591
02:22:28,490 --> 02:22:31,550
- 我觉得我们应该去救罗夏 - 什么？
- I think we ought to spring Rorschach. LAURIE: What?

1592
02:22:31,720 --> 02:22:33,490
有人陷害了他
DAN: Someone set him up.

1593
02:22:34,320 --> 02:22:37,920
还有关于乔使人患癌症的事情 都是一派胡言
And this whole cancer thing with Jon, it just doesn't make sense.

1594
02:22:38,100 --> 02:22:40,030
你还不明白
You didn't get it.

1595
02:22:40,330 --> 02:22:42,760
对，不过想从这么戒备森严的地方越狱
Yeah, but breaking into a maximum-security prison...

1596
02:22:42,930 --> 02:22:46,600
- 就和灭火有点不一样了 - 对，确实如此
...is a little different than putting out a fire. - Yeah, you're right.

1597
02:22:47,500 --> 02:22:49,340
会更有趣
It'll be more fun.

1598
02:22:52,620 --> 02:22:55,620
快点李昂德，我想闻闻他被烤熟的味道
Hurry, Lloyd. I wanna smell this son of a bitch cooking.

1599
02:23:00,900 --> 02:23:02,630
太棒了
Yes.

1600
02:23:07,370 --> 02:23:08,400
不妙
No.

1601
02:23:22,320 --> 02:23:27,160
之前还真没利用过马桶干掉过一个人 显然真的没有过
Never disposed of sewage with a toilet before. Obvious, really.

1602
02:23:27,990 --> 02:23:31,290
2比O，该你出招了
Two-nothing. Your move.

1603
02:23:34,630 --> 02:23:36,260
给我让开！
BIG FIGURE: Get out of the way!

1604
02:24:03,200 --> 02:24:05,060
你怎么知道他还活着？
How do we know he's still alive?

1605
02:24:07,300 --> 02:24:08,530
他还活着
DAN: He's alive.

1606
02:24:20,280 --> 02:24:21,840
不要，不
No. No.

1607
02:24:22,480 --> 02:24:23,880
我的面具呢？
Where's my face?

1608
02:24:26,420 --> 02:24:28,150
别杀我
Don't kill me.

1609
02:24:31,820 --> 02:24:33,220
到你了，医生
Your turn, doctor.

1610
02:24:33,390 --> 02:24:36,590
告诉我，你看见了什么？
Tell me, what do you see?

1611
02:26:02,750 --> 02:26:04,480
不许动
Don't move!

1612
02:26:12,760 --> 02:26:14,520
罗夏
Rorschach.

1613
02:26:15,030 --> 02:26:17,820
丹尼尔，朱庇特小姐
Daniel. Miss Jupiter.

1614
02:26:18,000 --> 02:26:21,400
抱歉，我得上个厕所
Excuse me. Have to visit men's room.

1615
02:26:21,930 --> 02:26:23,900
哦，看在上帝面子上
Oh, for chrissake.

1616
02:27:01,110 --> 02:27:03,230
看见你穿上制服真高兴，丹尼尔
RORSCHACH: Good to see you in uniform, Daniel.

1617
02:27:03,410 --> 02:27:06,840
早就该知道你只需要一对动人的双腿来激励
Should've known all you needed was nice pair of legs to motivate you.

1618
02:27:07,010 --> 02:27:11,240
- 你真是个混蛋，罗夏 - 请勿见怪
LAURIE: You're such an asshole, Rorschach. - Spare me indignation.

1619
02:27:12,480 --> 02:27:15,510
你挑了个好时间背叛乔
Picked hell of a time to be unfaithful to Jon.

1620
02:27:15,690 --> 02:27:18,490
是厌倦了爱国精神还是有人逼你那么做？
Get tired of being patriotic, or someone put you up to it?

1621
02:27:18,660 --> 02:27:21,320
你他妈的根本不知道自己在说什么！
You don't know what the fuck you're talking about!

1622
02:27:21,490 --> 02:27:25,360
嘿，先别说了，你们可以等下再吵
Hey! Would you two stop? You can argue later.

1623
02:27:25,530 --> 02:27:29,260
我不能让你们再吵了 我们得快点离开这儿
I had to turn the screechers off, so we'll be drawing fire soon.

1624
02:27:33,270 --> 02:27:35,640
站住！站住！不然开枪了！
Stop! Stop or we will shoot!

1625
02:28:14,510 --> 02:28:16,640
你还好吗？
Are you all right?

1626
02:28:18,080 --> 02:28:20,280
还好，只是
Yeah. Just...

1627
02:28:20,720 --> 02:28:21,980
感觉有点难过
...heavy, you know?

1628
02:28:22,790 --> 02:28:24,880
战争，越狱
War, jailbreak.

1629
02:28:25,420 --> 02:28:30,290
别太担心，好吗？ 一切都会好起来的
Don't worry about it. Okay? Everything's gonna be fine.

1630
02:28:35,300 --> 02:28:38,330
- 你好，劳丽 - 乔
- Hello, Laurie. - Jon.

1631
02:28:38,500 --> 02:28:42,130
- 电视上说你在火星 - 我是在那里
- TV said you were on Mars. - I am on Mars.

1632
02:28:42,710 --> 02:28:45,110
我要和你在那儿好好谈谈
You and I are about to have a conversation there.

1633
02:28:45,280 --> 02:28:46,740
你在说什么？
What are you talking about?

1634
02:28:46,910 --> 02:28:49,570
你得努力说服我去拯救这个世界
You're going to try to convince me to save the world.

1635
02:28:55,490 --> 02:28:58,480
- 劳丽，不要 - 丹，相信我
- Laurie, don't. - Dan, trust me.

1636
02:28:58,660 --> 02:29:00,320
我得走了
I have to go.

1637
02:29:06,000 --> 02:29:07,990
很美，不是吗？
Beautiful, isn't it?

1638
02:29:12,840 --> 02:29:15,770
原谅我，我又忘了这里没有氧气了
Forgive me. These things sometimes slip my mind.

1639
02:29:17,180 --> 02:29:19,010
不会有下次了
It won't happen again.

1640
02:29:20,680 --> 02:29:22,670
那就好
LAURIE: That's comforting.

1641
02:29:25,020 --> 02:29:26,680
哦，我的天啊
Oh, my God.

1642
02:29:27,350 --> 02:29:29,180
我在火星上
I'm on Mars.

1643
02:29:33,190 --> 02:29:37,060
- 嘿，靓妞 - 嘿，混蛋
MAN: Hey. Nice ass. WOMAN: Hey, asshole.

1644
02:29:37,230 --> 02:29:39,820
嘿，让我们找找那个 喜欢连环漫画的在不在这里
MAN: Hey, let's see if that comic-book retard's up here.

1645
02:29:40,630 --> 02:29:42,570
嘿嘿嘿，你们
Hey, hey, hey. Yo.

1646
02:29:42,730 --> 02:29:47,430
你们都听说了吗？ 有个开着大猫头鹰的家伙把罗夏救走了
You all hear? Some super-owl dude just busted Rorschach out of prison.

1647
02:29:47,610 --> 02:29:49,330
- 罗夏？ - 对
- Rorschach? - Yeah.

1648
02:29:49,510 --> 02:29:51,370
那个混蛋把我的侄子打得需要坐轮椅
That fool put my cousin in a wheelchair.

1649
02:29:51,540 --> 02:29:54,410
你是说夜枭 他之前和罗夏是搭档，记得吗？
You mean Nite Owl. Him and Rorschach used to be partners.

1650
02:29:54,580 --> 02:29:57,240
- 对 - 可能他也有掺合你侄子的事
- Yeah. - Maybe he messed your cousin up too.

1651
02:29:57,420 --> 02:29:59,650
- 他是不是写过一本书什么的？ - 对
- Didn't he write a book or something? - Yeah.

1652
02:29:59,820 --> 02:30:03,690
告诉你，他现在就住在这附近的一所加油站那边
You know, he lives over a garage right near here.

1653
02:30:03,860 --> 02:30:06,520
- 明白？ - 是吗？
- Yeah? - Does he, now?

1654
02:30:09,260 --> 02:30:10,420
喂？
SALLY [ON PHONE]: Hello?

1655
02:30:11,430 --> 02:30:13,420
莎莉？
HOLLIS: Sally?

1656
02:30:13,600 --> 02:30:16,500
- 霍利斯？ - 是我
- Hollis? - Yeah.

1657
02:30:16,770 --> 02:30:20,670
霍利斯·梅森，这太不可思议了 我的上帝
Yes, Hollis Mason. Jesus.

1658
02:30:21,470 --> 02:30:26,100
你一直都有我的电话号码 却非要等到我们都老了才打？
All this time you've had my number and you wait until our sunset years to use it?

1659
02:30:26,280 --> 02:30:29,080
是这样，现在情况有点特殊，小莎
HOLLIS: Well, it seemed like a special occasion, Sal.

1660
02:30:29,250 --> 02:30:30,370
怎么了？
What?

1661
02:30:30,550 --> 02:30:34,780
新闻报道昨晚有场火灾
The TV is reporting there was a tenement fire last night.

1662
02:30:35,650 --> 02:30:38,450
受困人群是被一艘飞船救出的
There were trapped people rescued by airship...

1663
02:30:38,620 --> 02:30:44,190
他们说驾驶者穿得像猫头鹰一样
... and they say the pilot was dressed like an owl.

1664
02:30:44,360 --> 02:30:46,560
好像还有个性感女人和他一起
And it seems he had a sexy woman with him.

1665
02:30:46,730 --> 02:30:49,330
劳丽？我的女儿，劳丽？
Laurie? My daughter, Laurie?

1666
02:30:50,940 --> 02:30:54,060
我说服不了她再穿上制服
I can't get over Laurie back in costume.

1667
02:30:54,240 --> 02:30:57,700
或许她以后会感激我一开始 把她带上这条路
Maybe she'll finally thank me for getting her started in the first place.

1668
02:30:57,880 --> 02:31:01,470
小莎，听你说话的声音
You know, Sal, by the sound of your voice...

1669
02:31:01,650 --> 02:31:03,380
我觉得你比以前还年轻
...you're sounding younger than ever.

1670
02:31:03,550 --> 02:31:05,850
哦，谢谢你，霍利斯
Oh. Why, bless you, Hollis.

1671
02:31:06,520 --> 02:31:08,540
不过我还是老了
But that's probably just senility.

1672
02:31:11,320 --> 02:31:14,260
能和你聊天很开心，小莎
Well, it's been great talking to you, Sal...

1673
02:31:14,430 --> 02:31:16,790
但是有人在敲门
...but someone's knocking.

1674
02:31:17,330 --> 02:31:22,320
好的，不要太沉迷于怀念过去了
SALLY: Well, don't get too misty-eyed thinking about old times.

1675
02:31:23,200 --> 02:31:25,030
保重，霍利斯
You take care now, Hollis.

1676
02:31:25,200 --> 02:31:26,500
你也是
Ah, you too.

1677
02:31:26,670 --> 02:31:27,900
拜
Bye.

1678
02:31:28,470 --> 02:31:29,960
拜
Bye.

1679
02:31:33,410 --> 02:31:35,710
我们想找猫头鹰先生
MAN 1: We're looking for Mr. Owl.

1680
02:31:36,580 --> 02:31:38,780
请稍等
Yeah. Hold your horses.

1681
02:31:38,950 --> 02:31:40,510
你在吗？
MAN 1: Mr. Owl, you there?

1682
02:31:41,090 --> 02:31:42,480
不请吃就捣乱 （万圣节孩子到别人家要糖说的话）
MAN 2: Trick or treat.

1683
02:31:44,090 --> 02:31:45,680
退休了就该老实点，猫头鹰先生
MAN 1: You should've stayed retired, Owl.

1684
02:32:50,920 --> 02:32:52,480
我恨这样
RORSCHACH: I hate this.

1685
02:32:52,660 --> 02:32:56,890
萎缩在地下，躲避着当局
Cowering in cave, hiding from authorities.

1686
02:32:57,130 --> 02:33:00,330
警察在外面追捕我们，除非你想回到监狱去
Cops are out there hunting us. Unless you wanna go back to prison...

1687
02:33:00,500 --> 02:33:02,970
不然随便外出都不是个好主意
...we'd be stupid to expose ourselves without a plan.

1688
02:33:03,130 --> 02:33:05,400
那要怎么样？
And what would that be?

1689
02:33:05,740 --> 02:33:09,430
只要我们能伪造这个图案
Once we've established a pattern...

1690
02:33:09,840 --> 02:33:11,970
我们就能入侵金字塔公司 看看能发现什么
...we can break into Pyramid, see what we find.

1691
02:33:12,140 --> 02:33:14,580
那样行不通
RORSCHACH: Did that. Dead end.

1692
02:33:14,750 --> 02:33:19,340
我觉得那只是个掩护幕后人用的公司 但是却证明不了这点
I think it's a front company for whoever's really behind it, but can't prove it.

1693
02:33:22,290 --> 02:33:26,620
我们只需要找找黑社会的线人 严刑逼供一下他们
We need to hit up underworld contacts, squeeze people.

1694
02:33:26,790 --> 02:33:29,520
也可以，还不如我们 直接从电话簿里挑人问
Sure, why don't we just pick names out of a phone book?

1695
02:33:29,690 --> 02:33:31,820
你忘了我们以前是怎么做事的，丹尼尔
You forgot how we do things, Daniel.

1696
02:33:32,000 --> 02:33:36,460
你变得软弱和盲目 尤其是面对女人的时候
You've gone too soft. Too trusting. Especially with women.

1697
02:33:36,630 --> 02:33:38,730
够了，住嘴，我不想再听
Okay, no. Listen, I've had it with that.

1698
02:33:38,900 --> 02:33:40,930
天哪，你以为你是谁？罗夏？
God, who do you think you are, Rorschach?

1699
02:33:41,110 --> 02:33:43,200
我救了你，你不感激反而诽谤我？
You live off people while insulting them...

1700
02:33:43,370 --> 02:33:47,170
没人会埋怨你，因为他们都觉得你是个疯子
...and no one complains because they think you're a goddamn lunatic.

1701
02:33:59,160 --> 02:34:00,990
抱歉
I'm sorry.

1702
02:34:03,660 --> 02:34:05,820
我不该那么说
I shouldn't have said that, man.

1703
02:34:07,830 --> 02:34:09,160
丹尼尔
Daniel...

1704
02:34:10,670 --> 02:34:13,140
你是我的好朋友
...you are a good friend.

1705
02:34:16,010 --> 02:34:19,170
我知道和我想处很难
I know it can be difficult with me sometimes.

1706
02:34:25,680 --> 02:34:27,170
别介意
Forget it.

1707
02:34:28,350 --> 02:34:30,010
没事的，伙计
It's okay, man.

1708
02:34:31,290 --> 02:34:32,880
就照你的办法做
Let's do it your way.

1709
02:34:51,940 --> 02:34:53,240
哦，上帝
Oh, God.

1710
02:34:53,410 --> 02:34:57,780
金字塔跨国公司，有人听说过吗？
Pyramid Transnational. Anyone heard of it?

1711
02:35:05,260 --> 02:35:06,750
哦，你们这些混蛋
Oh, you bastards.

1712
02:35:06,920 --> 02:35:10,020
我请这里每个人喝酒，你们就这样出卖我？
I buy everyone a round and you sell me out like this?

1713
02:35:11,230 --> 02:35:14,530
滚开，不然我就把这杯子 黏在你潮湿的脸上
Back off, or I'll stick this glass in your squidgy face.

1714
02:35:16,230 --> 02:35:19,170
大家保持镇静 我们会尽快完事的
Everybody stay calm. We'll try to keep this brief.

1715
02:35:21,270 --> 02:35:23,430
罗伊·切丝，金字塔的工资单上的人
Roy Chess. On Pyramid payroll.

1716
02:35:23,610 --> 02:35:28,100
试图谋杀阿德里安·维特，现在已经死了 你知道他吗？
Tried to kill Adrian Veidt. Dead now. Did you know him?

1717
02:35:28,280 --> 02:35:29,940
不
No.

1718
02:35:31,320 --> 02:35:32,580
知道，知道
Yeah, yeah!

1719
02:35:32,750 --> 02:35:35,690
- 我雇用了他，很了解他 - 你这个混蛋
- I hired him. I knew him from the inside. - You're a felon.

1720
02:35:35,850 --> 02:35:38,820
曾经是，但我出狱之后就改过自新了
I was. I've been straight ever since I got out, I swear.

1721
02:35:38,990 --> 02:35:42,720
我也不过是稍微知道点儿他 其实我也不过是接受命令雇用他而已
I barely knew Chess that well, but I was told to hire from the old life.

1722
02:35:42,890 --> 02:35:46,490
- 谁让你做的？ - 我的接头人，斯莱特
- Told by whom? - My contact, Miss Slater.

1723
02:35:46,660 --> 02:35:49,260
珍妮·斯莱特也为金字塔工作？
Janey Slater works for Pyramid too?

1724
02:35:49,430 --> 02:35:53,390
是的，她真是个好人 她说雇用有前科的人是公司政策的一部分
Yeah, she was real nice. She said hiring ex-cons was part of the company program.

1725
02:35:53,570 --> 02:35:57,270
给他们改过自新的机会 上帝，放过我吧，我说的都是实话
Give people a second chance. God, please let go! I'm telling the truth!

1726
02:36:01,410 --> 02:36:04,640
珍妮·斯莱特，曼哈顿的前女友
Janey Slater, Manhattan's old girlfriend.

1727
02:36:04,820 --> 02:36:07,510
阿德里安能帮我们查到谁在公司背后
Adrian might help us find out who's underwriting Pyramid.

1728
02:36:07,690 --> 02:36:08,740
顺着现金流查
Follow the money.

1729
02:36:08,920 --> 02:36:12,190
不到一个小时之前
WOMAN [ON TV]:former member of the Minutemen Hollis Mason found murdered...

1730
02:36:12,360 --> 02:36:14,690
前组织成员霍利斯·梅森被发现 在其公寓被谋杀
... in his apartment less than an hour ago.

1731
02:36:14,860 --> 02:36:18,960
目击者称当地一个叫结首帮的黑帮
Witnesses reported seeing members of a local gang known as the Knot-Tops...

1732
02:36:19,130 --> 02:36:22,400
在估计的案发时间离开了现场
... leaving the area right around the estimated time of death.

1733
02:36:22,570 --> 02:36:25,500
为您播报
Reporting live, Tiffany Burns...

1734
02:36:27,840 --> 02:36:30,830
- 是谁干的？ - 我就知道你要怀疑我，伙计
- Who did it? - I knew you were gonna victimize me, man.

1735
02:36:31,010 --> 02:36:33,140
我的公民权利呢？就因为我穿了件
What about my civil rights? Just because I'm wearing...

1736
02:36:33,310 --> 02:36:36,370
- 告诉我谁干的？ - 很多人都这么穿
- Tell me who did it! - A lot of people dress like this.

1737
02:36:37,720 --> 02:36:39,620
谁杀了霍利斯·梅森？
Who murdered Hollis Mason?

1738
02:36:45,290 --> 02:36:47,550
告诉你的朋友们，他们死定了
You tell your friends they're dead.

1739
02:36:47,730 --> 02:36:51,290
我要踏平你们的老巢！
I'm gonna take out this entire rathole neighborhood.

1740
02:36:51,460 --> 02:36:53,950
我要拧断你的脖子！
I'll break your neck!

1741
02:36:54,530 --> 02:36:57,520
丹尼尔，别在公众面前这样
Daniel, not in front of the civilians.

1742
02:36:58,140 --> 02:37:00,930
该死的，该死的，霍利斯
Oh, goddamn. Goddamn, Hollis.

1743
02:37:10,980 --> 02:37:14,150
这就是我们要谈话的地方
JON: This is where we hold our conversation.

1744
02:37:14,750 --> 02:37:18,650
在这里，你会告诉我 你和德雷伯格上床了
In it, you reveal to me that you and Dreiberg have been sleeping together.

1745
02:37:19,820 --> 02:37:23,190
- 你知道我和丹的事情？ - 暂时还不知道
- You know about me and Dan? - Not yet.

1746
02:37:23,490 --> 02:37:26,330
但是等一下你就会告诉我
But in a few moments you're going to tell me.

1747
02:37:28,670 --> 02:37:33,690
如果你能够预知未来的话 你为什么还会对我离开你表现得吃惊呢？
If you already know the future, then why were you surprised when I left you?

1748
02:37:33,870 --> 02:37:36,070
或当那个记者诽谤你的时候？
Or when that reporter ambushed you?

1749
02:37:36,240 --> 02:37:39,870
如果你一早知道结果为什么还要争论呢？
Why even argue about it if you already know how this is gonna end?

1750
02:37:41,050 --> 02:37:43,310
我没得选
I have no choice.

1751
02:37:44,620 --> 02:37:47,550
所有事都是事先注定的
Everything is preordained.

1752
02:37:47,720 --> 02:37:50,050
甚至我的回答也是
Even my responses.

1753
02:37:51,020 --> 02:37:54,620
所以你也就按着趋势走
And you're just going through the motions.

1754
02:37:54,790 --> 02:37:58,190
你这个宇宙里最强大的人 也不过是个傀儡？
The most powerful thing in the universe is still just a puppet.

1755
02:38:01,330 --> 02:38:03,990
我们都是的，劳丽
We are all puppets, Laurie.

1756
02:38:04,940 --> 02:38:07,430
我只是个能看清楚局势的傀儡
I'm just a puppet who can see the strings.

1757
02:38:07,610 --> 02:38:09,300
如果你是错的呢？
And what if you're wrong?

1758
02:38:09,470 --> 02:38:13,970
为什么我预测未来的能力 让你如此烦恼呢？
Why does my perception of time distress you so?

1759
02:38:14,150 --> 02:38:16,050
因为那让我感到你很冷漠
Because it's inhuman.

1760
02:38:16,210 --> 02:38:18,610
因为那是荒谬的
Because it makes me insane.

1761
02:38:18,780 --> 02:38:22,690
你总是说你要安慰我 但是都没有起作用
You always say you wanna comfort me. Well, it isn't working.

1762
02:38:30,090 --> 02:38:32,590
我不想和你争吵
Look, I don't wanna fight.

1763
02:38:34,100 --> 02:38:36,830
我为我和丹上床的事情道歉
I'm sorry I slept with Dan.

1764
02:38:37,400 --> 02:38:39,430
你和丹上床了？
You slept with Dan?

1765
02:38:41,140 --> 02:38:44,130
你刚才都说过自己已经知道了
You just said that you already knew about that.

1766
02:38:44,840 --> 02:38:48,840
我经常说
I said often...

1767
02:38:49,510 --> 02:38:53,850
你是我和这个人类社会最后的联系
...that you were my only remaining link to humanity.

1768
02:38:56,290 --> 02:38:57,780
为什么我要去拯救
Why would I save a world...

1769
02:38:57,960 --> 02:39:00,080
一个和我完全无关的世界呢？
...I no longer have any stake in?

1770
02:39:02,190 --> 02:39:04,250
那就为了我而做
Then do it for me.

1771
02:39:05,130 --> 02:39:06,530
如果你是真心的
If you really care.

1772
02:39:06,700 --> 02:39:10,130
当你离开了我，我离开了地球
When you left me, I left Earth.

1773
02:39:10,300 --> 02:39:13,200
那还不够表示我的真心吗？
Does that not show you that I care?

1774
02:39:16,410 --> 02:39:19,340
我在火星这里红色的世界
My red world here, now...

1775
02:39:20,340 --> 02:39:23,250
现在对我来说比你们 蓝色的地球还要有意义
...means more to me than your blue one.

1776
02:39:24,020 --> 02:39:25,740
我给你看看
Let me show you.

1777
02:39:43,870 --> 02:39:46,800
炸弹都准备好了，先生
KISSINGER: Bombers are fueled and ready, sir.

1778
02:39:56,150 --> 02:39:58,380
到时候了，各位
It's time, gentlemen.

1779
02:40:00,480 --> 02:40:02,880
把国防等级提到1级
Take us to DEFCON one.

1780
02:40:10,160 --> 02:40:13,260
不在家中，不在办公室
RORSCHACH: Not in penthouse. Not in office.

1781
02:40:13,430 --> 02:40:16,330
是什么诱惑了这个拥有了一切
What nocturnal proclivities entice a man with everything...

1782
02:40:16,500 --> 02:40:18,260
的男人在这么晚的时候外出？
...out into the night at this hour?

1783
02:40:20,340 --> 02:40:22,200
丹尼尔？
Daniel?

1784
02:40:23,440 --> 02:40:25,200
你和我一起去吗？
You with me?

1785
02:40:26,010 --> 02:40:29,140
- 是的 - 你在干什么？
- Yeah. - Then what are you doing?

1786
02:40:31,250 --> 02:40:33,010
我在找阿德里安的日程表
DAN: I'm gonna look for Adrian's itinerary.

1787
02:40:33,180 --> 02:40:35,950
可能他有存档
RORSCHACH: Maybe he keeps on file.

1788
02:40:40,460 --> 02:40:42,930
- 有点不对劲 - 我也觉得
- Something's not right. - Agreed.

1789
02:40:43,090 --> 02:40:47,860
珍妮·斯莱特, 死神, 罗伊·切丝 都为金字塔工作
Janey Slater, Moloch, Roy Chess all work for Pyramid.

1790
02:40:48,030 --> 02:40:52,660
死神说过笑匠提到的名单里 有他和斯莱特的名字在里面
Moloch said the Comedian mentioned list with his and Slater's name on it.

1791
02:40:52,840 --> 02:40:56,140
不管是谁是金字塔公司的幕后主使 都有可能使他们患上癌症
Whoever owns Pyramid could be giving these people cancer.

1792
02:40:56,310 --> 02:40:58,780
陷害曼哈顿
Setting Manhattan up.

1793
02:41:12,920 --> 02:41:14,080
有趣
Funny.

1794
02:41:14,260 --> 02:41:17,750
古代法老渴望世界末日的到来
Ancient pharaohs looked forward to the end of the world.

1795
02:41:17,930 --> 02:41:22,960
相信死人能复活 从金罐子里拿回自己的心脏
Believed cadavers would rise, reclaim hearts from golden jars.

1796
02:41:23,600 --> 02:41:26,230
现在他们一定在期待中屏住了呼吸
Must currently be holding breath in anticipation.

1797
02:41:26,400 --> 02:41:27,630
法老？
Pharaohs?

1798
02:41:34,510 --> 02:41:36,540
找到一份曼哈顿的心理资料
Got a psych profile on Manhattan.

1799
02:41:37,180 --> 02:41:39,650
看看他们怎么说
See what the corporate head-peepers say.

1800
02:41:41,690 --> 02:41:44,210
“对象的情感持续退化
"Subject continues to retreat emotionally.

1801
02:41:46,520 --> 02:41:49,580
如果失去最后的情感连接
If the only remaining ties were to be severed...

1802
02:41:50,190 --> 02:41:54,150
我们预测可能他会脱离人类本性”
...we predict total detachment from the human condition."

1803
02:41:58,270 --> 02:42:00,030
我进入了
DAN: I'm in.

1804
02:42:24,670 --> 02:42:28,030
(母公司：维特国际）

1805
02:42:28,900 --> 02:42:30,230
不
No.

1806
02:42:32,400 --> 02:42:38,170
恭喜，维特先生 曼哈顿博士的能量反应堆已经连上了
MAN: Congratulations, Mr. Veidt. Dr. Manhattan's energy reactor is online.

1807
02:42:38,340 --> 02:42:42,210
你的支持和热情
Your support and your enthusiasm...

1808
02:42:42,380 --> 02:42:44,680
促成了这次成功
...is what has led to this triumph.

1809
02:42:44,850 --> 02:42:48,880
我们代表整个研究团队感谢您
On behalf of the research team, we salute you.

1810
02:42:49,050 --> 02:42:51,490
- 干杯 - 干杯
- Cheers. - Cheers.

1811
02:42:52,260 --> 02:42:56,390
生命中的什么不值得庆祝？
ADRIAN: What in life does not deserve celebrating?

1812
02:42:57,330 --> 02:43:01,420
这就是新的卡纳克（古埃及的首都）
This is the new Karnak.

1813
02:43:01,600 --> 02:43:05,190
代表了过去两千年里人类梦想的顶峰
This represents the culmination of a dream more than 2000 years old...

1814
02:43:05,370 --> 02:43:11,640
一个因为你们无私奉献才达到的顶峰
...a dream now assured because of your unquestioning assistance.

1815
02:43:13,780 --> 02:43:15,440
为此
And for this...

1816
02:43:16,280 --> 02:43:18,610
我遗憾地宣布
...I am ashamed...

1817
02:43:19,780 --> 02:43:24,120
你们的奖励将与你们的努力不相衬
...ashamed that you must now share such inadequate a reward.

1818
02:43:25,790 --> 02:43:27,780
为法老们干杯
To the pharaohs...

1819
02:43:28,730 --> 02:43:31,720
他们的秘密和被他们所托负的 衷心仆人一起
...their greatest secrets entrusted to their servants...

1820
02:43:32,360 --> 02:43:36,700
被活埋在了黄沙覆盖的沙丘下面
...buried alive with them in sand-floored chambers.

1821
02:43:37,570 --> 02:43:39,970
好梦，先生们
Sleep well, gentlemen.

1822
02:43:40,640 --> 02:43:43,970
我们的新的和平世界将受惠于此
Our new, peaceful world will be indebted...

1823
02:43:44,310 --> 02:43:46,870
为了你们的牺牲干杯
...to your great sacrifice.

1824
02:43:47,810 --> 02:43:50,010
布巴斯提斯（古埃及的猫神）
Bubastis.

1825
02:43:54,180 --> 02:43:57,180
罗夏日记，最后的记录
Rorschach's journal. Final entry.

1826
02:43:57,520 --> 02:44:00,010
维特就是幕后主宰
Veidt's behind everything.

1827
02:44:00,190 --> 02:44:01,780
为什么？
Why?

1828
02:44:01,960 --> 02:44:04,020
他到底想要什么？
What's his endgame?

1829
02:44:04,190 --> 02:44:07,860
我想不出还有更可怕的对手
I cannot imagine a more dangerous opponent.

1830
02:44:08,070 --> 02:44:11,500
曾经开玩笑说他快到能抓住子弹
Used to joke he was fast enough to catch a bullet.

1831
02:44:11,670 --> 02:44:14,570
他自己就能够在雪地里干掉我们
He could kill us both alone in the snow.

1832
02:44:14,740 --> 02:44:18,440
那就是我们要去的地方：南极
That's where we're going now: Antarctica.

1833
02:44:18,610 --> 02:44:21,370
不管我今后是生是死
Whether I'm alive or dead upon this reading...

1834
02:44:21,550 --> 02:44:25,810
我希望这个世界能够坚持到 你们看到这本日记的时候
... I hope the world survives long enough for this journal to reach you.

1835
02:44:25,980 --> 02:44:28,540
我活的时候不妥协
I live my life free of compromise...

1836
02:44:28,720 --> 02:44:32,660
现在赴死的时候也不会后悔或抱怨
... and step into the shadow without complaint or regret.

1837
02:44:33,290 --> 02:44:36,280
罗夏，11月1号
Rorschach, November 1 st.

1838
02:44:38,130 --> 02:44:40,020
（纽约公报：苏联入侵阿富汗）

1839
02:44:42,070 --> 02:44:44,470
噢，愿上帝帮帮我们
Oh, God help us.

1840
02:44:47,540 --> 02:44:49,970
- 你今天是不是来早了，哈？ - 是啊
- It's a little early for you, huh? - Yeah.

1841
02:44:50,140 --> 02:44:52,370
我想上学之前看完那本书
I wanted to finish the story before school.

1842
02:44:57,850 --> 02:45:01,310
听着，这本书归你了，明白吗？
Listen, now you just keep it, okay?

1843
02:45:02,450 --> 02:45:05,050
- 哈？ - 归你了
- Huh? - It's yours.

1844
02:45:05,220 --> 02:45:08,160
我说，生命太短暂了，不是吗？
I mean, life's too short, right?

1845
02:45:08,430 --> 02:45:09,720
是啊
Yeah.

1846
02:45:10,060 --> 02:45:11,390
呃…
Uh...

1847
02:45:11,560 --> 02:45:13,150
谢了，老兄
Thanks, man.

1848
02:45:38,590 --> 02:45:40,920
为何死神弃我而去？
Why does death pass me by?

1849
02:45:44,030 --> 02:45:45,690
戴维斯敦？
Davidstown?

1850
02:45:46,960 --> 02:45:48,660
戴维斯敦
Davidstown.

1851
02:45:48,970 --> 02:45:51,370
我离那儿只有几里路
I was only miles away.

1852
02:45:51,540 --> 02:45:53,300
现在那镇子应该被占领了
By now the town was overrun.

1853
02:45:53,840 --> 02:45:56,860
那些恶魔们以为我已不是威胁
The fiends imagined themselves safe from me.

1854
02:45:57,040 --> 02:45:58,410
但现在我回家了
But now I was home.

1855
02:45:58,580 --> 02:46:00,980
我将要报仇雪恨
And revenge would be mine.

1856
02:46:08,650 --> 02:46:11,350
不，那不是黑货船上的强盗
No, not the brigands from the Black Freighter.

1857
02:46:11,520 --> 02:46:14,650
这认得这个人，戴维斯敦的一个放债人
The man I recognized, a moneylender from Davidstown.

1858
02:46:15,030 --> 02:46:17,150
既然戴维斯敦一定被占领了
With Davidstown certainly captured...

1859
02:46:17,330 --> 02:46:20,460
为什么这恶棍和他的婊子…
... why would this scoundrel and his wench be allowed free passage...

1860
02:46:20,630 --> 02:46:21,890
…能自由地幽会？
... for this midnight tryst?

1861
02:46:22,070 --> 02:46:23,290
他和他们勾结了？
Had he collaborated?

1862
02:46:23,470 --> 02:46:24,900
他背叛了他的人民？
Had he betrayed my people?

1863
02:46:25,340 --> 02:46:28,070
- 还有我的家人？ - 来抓我吧，宝贝
- My family? WOMAN: Come and get it, babe.

1864
02:46:28,540 --> 02:46:29,730
这儿
Here.

1865
02:46:38,820 --> 02:46:41,010
我的心变凉了
My heart grew cold.

1866
02:46:41,190 --> 02:46:44,310
在被这个通敌者和他的海盗主子 冷笑着杀死之前…
Was my wife comforted before her execution...

1867
02:46:44,490 --> 02:46:48,550
…我的妻子有没有得到过慰籍？
... while this collaborator and his pirate masters sneered?

1868
02:46:48,990 --> 02:46:51,360
我被迫作出决定，但这并不难
My decision was hurried, but not difficult.

1869
02:46:51,530 --> 02:46:52,860
你是谁？干什么？
MAN: Who are you? What?

1870
02:46:55,500 --> 02:46:59,030
他的脑袋开了花 就如同他体内的罪孽炸开一般
His head burst, as if pressurized by the guilt within.

1871
02:47:08,580 --> 02:47:11,140
海盗的婊子不值得同情
A buccaneer's whore deserves no pity.

1872
02:47:15,290 --> 02:47:17,450
两个人骑马来了这儿
Two figures had ridden here.

1873
02:47:17,620 --> 02:47:20,450
回去的必须是两个人
Two must ride back.

1874
02:47:24,600 --> 02:47:27,000
海盗的哨兵
A pirate sentry.

1875
02:47:27,160 --> 02:47:31,260
我不急不忙地走以免怀疑
I trotted unhurriedly to avoid suspicion.

1876
02:47:32,200 --> 02:47:35,330
他们的暴行 不会因为戴维斯敦的好人而停止…
Their violation did not stop with the good people of Davidstown...

1877
02:47:35,510 --> 02:47:39,670
但却极深地伤害和影响了我热爱的家乡
... but had cut deeply, infecting my beloved homeland.

1878
02:47:39,840 --> 02:47:43,140
我的戴维斯敦已经和印象中的不一样了
My Davidstown was not as I last saw it.

1879
02:47:43,310 --> 02:47:47,250
它已经被黑货船的诅咒深深地折磨过
Already it was afflicted with the curse of the Black Freighter.

1880
02:47:47,420 --> 02:47:53,720
很快，我将会涉险走进这些住在我家里的 恶魔和刽子手中
Soon, I would venture amongst evil men, butchers who now reside in my home...

1881
02:47:53,890 --> 02:47:55,590
并让他们畏惧我
... and make them fear me.

1882
02:47:58,160 --> 02:48:03,070
当我到家时，我发现街道出奇地安静
Upon my return home, I found the streets conspicuously silent.

1883
02:48:05,100 --> 02:48:07,900
我静悄悄地进入我原本的住所
I entered my former residence noiselessly.

1884
02:48:08,610 --> 02:48:14,410
小小地避免把这些海盗屠夫们从他们 放纵的熟睡中惊醒
Careful not to rouse the pirate butchers occupying it from their debauched slumber.

1885
02:48:20,250 --> 02:48:22,240
毫无察觉死神已在他们身边
Unaware that death was amongst them...

1886
02:48:22,590 --> 02:48:27,680
他们还没明白个究竟 就已经尝到了死神的拥抱
... they would know its dark embrace without ever understanding why.

1887
02:48:27,860 --> 02:48:30,880
不过有一个人醒了，很慌张
One, however, was awake. Frantic.

1888
02:48:31,060 --> 02:48:32,460
为了避免他发出警报…
Lest he should raise alarms...

1889
02:48:32,630 --> 02:48:36,400
…我在他进入这被夜幕包围的房间时 就把他打倒了
... I set upon him as he entered the night-wrapped chamber.

1890
02:48:37,130 --> 02:48:39,160
没有海盗过来，但更糟的事情发生了
No pirates come, but something worse.

1891
02:48:40,840 --> 02:48:41,860
父亲
Father?

1892
02:48:42,040 --> 02:48:46,670
我抬头看着这些熟悉的脸庞 因她们脸上的恐惧而住手
I look up into faces familiar, save for their terror.

1893
02:48:46,980 --> 02:48:50,280
从那无力而带血的唇中 她说出了我的名字
Through puffed and bloodied lips, she mouthed my name.

1894
02:48:50,450 --> 02:48:53,750
我的爱人，为什么？
My love, why?

1895
02:48:58,260 --> 02:49:03,750
突然我明白了一件事情 甚至让我来不及恢复神智
There came an understanding so large it left no room for sanity.

1896
02:49:04,560 --> 02:49:06,260
于是我跑了
So I ran.

1897
02:49:06,760 --> 02:49:08,630
她怎么了？
MAN 1: What's happened to her?

1898
02:49:09,530 --> 02:49:10,970
是你
MAN 2: You.

1899
02:49:12,340 --> 02:49:18,070
了解到我的天谴已经占据了我 欢呼着庆祝它那可怕的胜利
The knowledge of my damnation paced me, shouting, celebrating its awful victory.

1900
02:49:18,240 --> 02:49:19,970
我的推论是完美的
My deduction was flawless.

1901
02:49:20,140 --> 02:49:22,240
黑货船的确是朝戴维斯敦航行的
The Black Freighter was heading to Davidstown.

1902
02:49:22,410 --> 02:49:25,280
- 它应该到了 - 他往这跑了
- It should have arrived. MAN 3: He went that way!

1903
02:49:26,080 --> 02:49:29,610
你就不能告诉我这怎么能够拯救世界吗？
LAURIE: Can't you just tell me how this ends and save us the trouble?

1904
02:49:30,590 --> 02:49:32,490
结束的时候，你会流泪
JON: It ends with you in tears.

1905
02:49:32,660 --> 02:49:36,250
眼泪？你不回地球了？
Tears? So you don't come back to Earth.

1906
02:49:36,430 --> 02:49:39,860
某种程度而言，是的
At some point, yes.

1907
02:49:40,930 --> 02:49:43,870
到处都会有死亡
The streets are filled with death.

1908
02:49:44,030 --> 02:49:46,090
乔，拜托
Jon, please.

1909
02:49:46,270 --> 02:49:50,830
你得阻止这一切，每个人都会死
You have to stop this. Everyone will die.

1910
02:49:51,010 --> 02:49:55,340
但是宇宙根本不会在意
And the universe will not even notice.

1911
02:49:57,780 --> 02:50:02,010
在我看来，生命的存在
In my opinion, the existence of life...

1912
02:50:02,890 --> 02:50:05,880
是一种成本过高的现象
...is a highly overrated phenomenon.

1913
02:50:07,790 --> 02:50:10,090
看看你的周围
Just look around you.

1914
02:50:12,830 --> 02:50:17,160
没有那么多微生物，火星是如此美丽
Mars gets along perfectly well without so much as a microorganism.

1915
02:50:17,800 --> 02:50:22,360
这儿，是一幅永远在变化的地形图
Here, it's a constantly changing topographical map...

1916
02:50:22,540 --> 02:50:28,480
10000年间都围绕着地级做着地壳运动
...flowing and shifting around the pole in ripples 10,000 years wide.

1917
02:50:29,310 --> 02:50:30,800
请告诉我
So tell me...

1918
02:50:30,980 --> 02:50:35,350
这一切怎能通过输油管道来美化呢？
...how would all of this be greatly improved by an oil pipeline?

1919
02:50:35,820 --> 02:50:37,810
或是购物中心？
By a shopping mall?

1920
02:50:42,160 --> 02:50:46,460
那就是说有奇迹发生是不可能的了？
So it's too much to ask for a miracle?

1921
02:50:46,630 --> 02:50:48,760
奇迹，按照他们的定义，是无意义的
Miracles, by their definition, are meaningless.

1922
02:50:48,930 --> 02:50:50,420
我的上帝，乔！
Oh, God, Jon!

1923
02:50:50,600 --> 02:50:55,660
- 只有将要发生的才会发生 - 别再胡说八道
- Only what can happen does happen. - Just stop your bullshit.

1924
02:50:56,740 --> 02:50:59,270
停下这玩意，就现在
Land this thing. Now.

1925
02:50:59,440 --> 02:51:02,000
如你所愿
JON: As you wish.

1926
02:51:07,620 --> 02:51:08,680
你知道吗？
LAURIE: You know what?

1927
02:51:08,850 --> 02:51:11,550
你可以把我送回地球，让我和丹 和我妈妈
You can send me back to Earth to fry with Dan and my mom...

1928
02:51:11,720 --> 02:51:14,090
还有其他无用的人类一起被烤焦
...and all the other worthless humans.

1929
02:51:14,260 --> 02:51:17,690
不过你还是错了 你说这最后会以我的眼泪结束
But know that you were wrong. You said this ended with me in tears...

1930
02:51:17,860 --> 02:51:22,030
看：没有，可能你都说错了
...and look: Nothing. Maybe you were wrong about everything.

1931
02:51:22,200 --> 02:51:27,470
你抱怨我不以生命的视角来看待生命
You complain that I refuse to see life on life's terms...

1932
02:51:28,210 --> 02:51:31,970
但你也不从我的视角去看待事情
...yet you continuously refuse to see things from my perspective.

1933
02:51:32,140 --> 02:51:36,550
- 你封锁一切使你感到惧怕的东西 - 我不怕
- You shut out what you're afraid of. - I'm not afraid.

1934
02:51:36,710 --> 02:51:41,740
你想我按你的视角认知世界？ 那做给我看看，按你的方法
You want me to see things your way? Go ahead, show me. Do that thing you do.

1935
02:51:48,890 --> 02:51:53,990
魔法，梦想，这都是我以前拥有的 我是个英雄，该死的
Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before. I was a hero, goddamn it!

1936
02:51:54,160 --> 02:51:57,220
你变老了并不是我的错 你又有什么好抱怨的？
It's not my fault you got old. What do you have to complain about?

1937
02:51:57,400 --> 02:51:59,530
我养活你，还有你的孩子
I put food on the table for you and your child.

1938
02:51:59,700 --> 02:52:02,500
你怎么不去找艾迪？ 或许他能给你更好的生活
Call your friend Eddie. Maybe he can give you a better life.

1939
02:52:03,240 --> 02:52:05,940
即使是最肮脏的部分
SALLY: Even the grimy parts of it...

1940
02:52:06,310 --> 02:52:08,540
也在朝着好的一面发展
...keep on getting brighter.

1941
02:52:08,880 --> 02:52:12,470
知道吗？你妈妈一直是最漂亮的
You know, your mom, she was one of the all-time champion beauties.

1942
02:52:12,650 --> 02:52:17,090
- 你有和她一样的眼睛，你有 - 把你手拿开
- You got her eyes, you know. You got... - Take your hands off her.

1943
02:52:17,250 --> 02:52:19,380
嘿，美人，好久不见
EDDIE: Hey, doll. Long time no see.

1944
02:52:19,560 --> 02:52:22,320
我不这样认为，艾迪 上车
Not long enough in my book, Eddie. Get in the car.

1945
02:52:22,830 --> 02:52:24,690
现在
Now.

1946
02:52:25,660 --> 02:52:27,650
你就没有点道德底线吗？
Are there no depths you won't sink to?

1947
02:52:27,830 --> 02:52:31,670
上帝啊，莎莉，难道
Jesus Christ, Sally. Can't a guy talk to his...

1948
02:52:32,370 --> 02:52:34,060
和老朋友的女儿说句话都不行？
...you know, old friend's daughter?

1949
02:52:36,370 --> 02:52:37,700
开车
Drive.

1950
02:52:43,710 --> 02:52:46,510
那是场误会，就那一次
SALLY: It was a mistake. One time.

1951
02:52:46,820 --> 02:52:49,980
那个人想强奸你，几年后 他怎么不帮你养孩子？
Guy tries to rape you, and years later, you let him finish the job?

1952
02:52:50,220 --> 02:52:52,920
怎么了？你是喝醉了还是怎么了？
What? Were you drunk or just Ionely?

1953
02:52:53,090 --> 02:52:56,030
难道我这辈子要这么度过？
Am I ever gonna live this down?

1954
02:52:59,400 --> 02:53:00,520
劳丽
Laurie.

1955
02:53:05,400 --> 02:53:06,730
不
No.

1956
02:53:08,740 --> 02:53:11,230
不，不是他
No, not him.

1957
02:53:11,410 --> 02:53:13,500
笑匠
The Comedian...

1958
02:53:13,910 --> 02:53:16,000
是你的父亲
...was your father.

1959
02:53:17,480 --> 02:53:19,180
不
No.

1960
02:53:22,490 --> 02:53:28,190
不！不！不！
No! No! No!

1961
02:54:00,790 --> 02:54:02,780
我的命运
My life is just...

1962
02:54:03,460 --> 02:54:05,590
简直就是个玩笑
...one big joke.

1963
02:54:05,760 --> 02:54:08,320
我不这样想
I don't think your life is a joke.

1964
02:54:09,970 --> 02:54:11,960
好吧
Yeah, well...

1965
02:54:13,800 --> 02:54:17,970
抱歉，我不相信你的幽默感
...I'm sorry if I don't trust your sense of humor.

1966
02:54:26,150 --> 02:54:27,810
我要是承认我错了
Will you smile...

1967
02:54:29,490 --> 02:54:31,950
你会笑个给我看吗？
...if I admit I was wrong?

1968
02:54:34,820 --> 02:54:36,820
关于什么了？
LAURIE: About what?

1969
02:54:38,830 --> 02:54:40,320
奇迹
Miracles.

1970
02:54:42,000 --> 02:54:45,160
就像发生了一些几率很小的事情
Events with astronomical odds of occurring...

1971
02:54:46,000 --> 02:54:48,490
就像是氧气变成了金子一样
...like oxygen turning into gold.

1972
02:54:48,670 --> 02:54:53,510
我一直都想目睹这样的事情发生
I've longed to witness such an event, and yet I neglect...

1973
02:54:54,180 --> 02:54:56,540
却一直忽视了，人类繁衍的力量
...that in human coupling...

1974
02:54:57,350 --> 02:55:01,220
数以百万的细胞组成了一个生命体
...millions upon millions of cells compete to create life...

1975
02:55:01,690 --> 02:55:04,480
一代又一代
...for generation after generation...

1976
02:55:05,360 --> 02:55:08,420
直到最后，你的母亲
...until finally, your mother...

1977
02:55:08,790 --> 02:55:09,990
爱上了一个男人
...Ioves a man...

1978
02:55:10,630 --> 02:55:14,220
艾德华·布莱克，就是那个笑匠 她有任何理由迁怒于他
...Edward Blake, the Comedian, a man she has every reason to hate...

1979
02:55:14,400 --> 02:55:18,390
出于对这种深不可测的几率的反叛
...and out of that contradiction, against unfathomable odds...

1980
02:55:19,070 --> 02:55:20,970
才有了你
...it's you...

1981
02:55:22,710 --> 02:55:24,040
独一无二的
Only...

1982
02:55:24,710 --> 02:55:26,200
你
...you.

1983
02:55:27,040 --> 02:55:28,310
出生在这个世界
- That emerged.

1984
02:55:28,880 --> 02:55:33,370
把如此与众不同的相貌
To distill so specific a form...

1985
02:55:33,550 --> 02:55:35,810
从所有错乱的基因中提取出来
...from all that chaos...

1986
02:55:37,720 --> 02:55:40,690
就像是把空气变成了金子
...is like turning air into gold.

1987
02:55:45,060 --> 02:55:47,050
就是奇迹
A miracle.

1988
02:55:50,570 --> 02:55:52,060
因此
And so...

1989
02:55:52,570 --> 02:55:54,400
我的确错了
...I was wrong.

1990
02:55:56,410 --> 02:56:00,240
擦干眼泪，我们回去吧
Now dry your eyes, and let's go home.

1991
02:56:27,770 --> 02:56:31,800
人造表层受压，温度上升
We got a bearing on that artificial structure. Heat signature's off the charts.

1992
02:56:32,780 --> 02:56:35,870
- 维特 - 我不喜欢阿基米德这样
- Veidt. - I don't like the way Archie's kicking.

1993
02:56:44,290 --> 02:56:47,120
- 引擎出毛病了 - 它们在结冰，抓牢了
- The engines. - They're icing up. Hold onto something.

1994
02:56:47,890 --> 02:56:49,920
丹尼尔，你飞得太低了
Daniel, you're coming in too low.

1995
02:56:52,800 --> 02:56:55,960
我不想打断你，但是也许我们需要飞高点
Don't wish to interfere, but perhaps should pull up sharply...

1996
02:56:56,130 --> 02:57:00,070
我知道，我正在尝试，该死的
I know! I'm trying. I'm trying to pull him up, goddamn it!

1997
02:57:27,330 --> 02:57:30,960
我正试着改变尾焰排出的路径 加快除冰
DAN: I'm gonna redirect the heat from the flamethrower to speed up deicing...

1998
02:57:31,130 --> 02:57:34,000
不过需要些时间，我们没有时间了
...but it's gonna take a while and we don't have time to wait.

1999
02:57:35,510 --> 02:57:36,970
你得多穿点
You need something warmer.

2000
02:57:37,510 --> 02:57:39,670
我穿这就行
Fine like this.

2001
02:58:09,170 --> 02:58:11,040
怎么了，宝贝？
What is it, girl?

2002
02:58:13,340 --> 02:58:15,040
唔
Mm.

2003
02:58:40,640 --> 02:58:42,900
阿德里安是和平主义者
DAN: Adrian's a pacifist.

2004
02:58:43,110 --> 02:58:47,740
他是个素食主义者 一生中都没有过杀生
He's a vegetarian, for chrissakes. He's never killed anyone in his life.

2005
02:58:47,910 --> 02:58:49,310
希特勒也是素食主义者
Hitler was vegetarian.

2006
02:58:49,480 --> 02:58:54,010
你太畏手畏脚了，把他交给我吧 我们不会有第二次机会了
You're squeamish, leave him to me. We won't get second chance.

2007
03:00:05,260 --> 03:00:06,590
先生们
Gentlemen.

2008
03:00:07,090 --> 03:00:11,030
- 欢迎你们 - 阿德里安，我们都知道了
- Welcome. - Adrian, we know everything.

2009
03:00:11,190 --> 03:00:12,960
那我们还有什么好说的，丹？
Then what's there to discuss, Dan?

2010
03:00:13,130 --> 03:00:16,120
多着呢，你杀了笑匠
Plenty. You killed Comedian.

2011
03:00:16,300 --> 03:00:17,820
希望他安息
May he rest in peace.

2012
03:00:18,330 --> 03:00:20,930
布莱克首先想明白的
Blake figured it out first.

2013
03:00:21,100 --> 03:00:25,170
尼克松派他监视我们，确保我们不搞破坏
Nixon had him keeping tabs on us, making sure we weren't rocking the boat.

2014
03:00:26,110 --> 03:00:28,370
布莱克发现了我在卡纳克做的事情
Blake found out what I was doing here in Karnak...

2015
03:00:28,550 --> 03:00:32,610
他去拜访可怜的死神的时候 已经快不行了
... and by the time he visited poor Moloch, he was cracking badly.

2016
03:00:32,780 --> 03:00:36,050
连我都无法想象他会改变主意
Even I couldn't predict he'd be the one to have a change of heart.

2017
03:00:36,790 --> 03:00:38,310
所以
So...

2018
03:00:39,360 --> 03:00:41,290
我不得不杀他灭口
...I had to kill him.

2019
03:00:41,860 --> 03:00:45,620
然后我摆平了乔，真不容易
Then I neutralized Jon. No easy task.

2020
03:00:45,800 --> 03:00:48,260
我花了20亿去研究超光速粒子
I put roughly $2 billion into tachyon research...

2021
03:00:48,430 --> 03:00:50,460
来阻断乔对未来的预测
...to block Jon's vision of the future.

2022
03:00:50,630 --> 03:00:52,900
你利用心理操纵了他
RORSCHACH: You used his psych profile to manipulate him.

2023
03:00:53,400 --> 03:00:54,870
让他离开了这个星球
Got him to leave the planet.

2024
03:00:55,040 --> 03:00:58,440
我认识乔很长时间了 知道他无法摆脱情绪的困扰
I've known Jon long enough to see he isn't devoid of emotion.

2025
03:00:58,610 --> 03:01:02,510
他微妙的面部变化，对外人来说可能可以瞒过去 不过对我来说
His subtle facial twitches wouldn't be noticed by the layman, but to me...

2026
03:01:02,680 --> 03:01:04,510
他并不是无敌的
... he might as well have been sobbing.

2027
03:01:04,880 --> 03:01:08,010
我所需要的就是继续干下去
All I needed to do was tug on the thread.

2028
03:01:08,180 --> 03:01:10,080
当他觉得是自己让心爱的人患上了癌症
The sudden flood of emotion Jon felt...

2029
03:01:10,250 --> 03:01:13,850
乔所感受到的那种突然的感情冲击
... when he came to believe he'd given cancer to the people he loved...

2030
03:01:14,020 --> 03:01:16,150
足以令他离开地球
... was all the excuse he needed to leave Earth.

2031
03:01:16,330 --> 03:01:20,160
你的混蛋杀手们，你雇他们想干掉我们
DAN: Your bullshit assassin. You paid him to throw us off.

2032
03:01:20,330 --> 03:01:24,990
切丝先生为了高贵的理由献出了自己的生命，丹
ADRIAN: Mr. Chess gave his life in the service of a higher cause, Dan.

2033
03:01:27,140 --> 03:01:30,230
我让他吃下去了个氰化物胶囊
I put a cyanide capsule in his mouth...

2034
03:01:30,410 --> 03:01:33,000
只留下一点
... leaving only one loose end:

2035
03:01:33,610 --> 03:01:37,050
那就是，你和你的面具杀手理论
You, and your mask-killer theory...

2036
03:01:37,210 --> 03:01:40,340
当你坚持跟踪一个真正的反社会人
... one you followed with the tenacity of a true sociopath.

2037
03:01:40,520 --> 03:01:42,210
我给警察提供了线索
I tipped off the police.

2038
03:01:42,390 --> 03:01:44,790
你入狱的时候，我才能更好的行动
Once you were in prison, I was able to move forward.

2039
03:01:44,950 --> 03:01:47,580
抱歉让你失望了
RORSCHACH: Sorry to disappoint you.

2040
03:02:00,770 --> 03:02:03,240
我们本该为地球谋福祉
DAN: We were supposed to make the world a better place.

2041
03:02:03,410 --> 03:02:05,140
丹，那正是我在做的
ADRIAN: Dan, that's exactly what I am doing.

2042
03:02:05,310 --> 03:02:06,640
核战？
DAN: Nuclear war?

2043
03:02:06,810 --> 03:02:08,970
灭绝人类？
Human extinction?

2044
03:02:18,620 --> 03:02:23,520
当然，我的道德底线保证了 我只做部分的牺牲
ADRIAN: Of course, my moral safeguards gave me pause at the necessary sacrifice.

2045
03:02:23,690 --> 03:02:26,660
全球的几个重要的地区
A few key regions around the globe...

2046
03:02:26,830 --> 03:02:32,290
纽约，洛杉矶，莫斯科，香港
New York, Los Angeles, Moscow, Hong Kong.

2047
03:02:32,470 --> 03:02:34,130
将会立即消失
- Disintegrated in an instant.

2048
03:02:34,870 --> 03:02:38,200
1500万人将死于非命
Fifteen million people killed...

2049
03:02:38,370 --> 03:02:40,430
这都是曼哈顿一手策划的
...by Dr. Manhattan himself.

2050
03:02:41,640 --> 03:02:44,440
这是第三次世界大战对地球的惩罚
The world's punishment for flirting with World War III.

2051
03:02:44,610 --> 03:02:45,740
乔不会这么做的
Jon wouldn't do that.

2052
03:02:46,320 --> 03:02:49,010
而事实只有我们知道
A fact no one outside this room ever has to know.

2053
03:02:49,650 --> 03:02:53,450
我一直致力的能源问题也已经初见成效了
The energy breakthrough I was working on just came to fruition.

2054
03:02:54,060 --> 03:02:58,050
这些年来，乔一直在帮我复制他的能量
All these years, Jon was helping me replicate his power...

2055
03:02:58,230 --> 03:03:00,750
却不知道我到底打算怎么利用这些能量
...unaware of how I planned to use it.

2056
03:03:00,930 --> 03:03:02,920
如你们所见
You see...

2057
03:03:03,830 --> 03:03:06,230
笑匠是对的
...the Comedian was right.

2058
03:03:06,940 --> 03:03:11,930
人性的残忍将不可避免地导致灭亡
Humanity's savage nature will inevitably lead to global annihilation.

2059
03:03:12,110 --> 03:03:14,910
所以为了拯救地球
So in order to save this planet...

2060
03:03:15,180 --> 03:03:17,240
我得用
...I had to trick it...

2061
03:03:17,610 --> 03:03:21,640
人类历史上最伟大的恶作剧来解决它
...with the greatest practical joke in human history.

2062
03:03:21,920 --> 03:03:25,320
- 杀上百万人 - 为了救更多的人
- Killing millions. - To save billions.

2063
03:03:25,860 --> 03:03:27,820
有必要的犯罪
A necessary crime.

2064
03:03:27,990 --> 03:03:30,150
你知道我们不会让你得逞的
RORSCHACH: You know we can't let you do that.

2065
03:03:31,590 --> 03:03:33,720
“得逞”？罗夏？
"Do that," Rorschach?

2066
03:03:33,900 --> 03:03:35,520
我不是连环画里的恶棍
I'm not a comic-book villain.

2067
03:03:36,370 --> 03:03:38,630
你们觉得我有必要给你们 解释我的伟大创作吗？
Do you think I'd explain my masterstroke to you...

2068
03:03:38,800 --> 03:03:42,970
如果你们能，哪怕一丁点，影响到我的计划
...if there were even the slightest possibility you could affect the outcome?

2069
03:03:45,710 --> 03:03:48,510
35分钟前我就启动了这一切
I triggered it 35 minutes ago.

2070
03:04:12,670 --> 03:04:18,110
最终，我来到了一片 在我面前无尽延伸的阴沉的黑色海洋
MARINER: Eventually, I came to a dismal black ocean stretching endlessly before me.

2071
03:04:18,840 --> 03:04:22,210
我怎么会让自己落到这样糟糕的境地 而我是以爱…
How had I reached this appalling position with love...

2072
03:04:22,380 --> 03:04:25,400
…我唯一的爱，作为我的指引
... only love, as my guide?

2073
03:04:27,020 --> 03:04:30,110
那个放债人漂到了我的脚边
The moneylender floated at my feet.

2074
03:04:30,290 --> 03:04:33,080
高贵的意图却将我引向了暴行
Noble intentions had led me to atrocity.

2075
03:04:33,260 --> 03:04:39,460
心中的义愤引发了我的幻想 那可怕的图谋只是我的妄想
The righteous anger fueling my ingenious, awful scheme was but delusion.

2076
03:04:39,630 --> 03:04:41,600
我哪里算错了？
Where was my error?

2077
03:04:42,000 --> 03:04:47,100
为了重新开始回想 我抬起了头并看到了她
Planning to resume my flight, I raised my head and saw her.

2078
03:04:49,370 --> 03:04:53,810
那艘船看起来正在等待 并不是在伺机进攻
The vessel seemed to be waiting, not hovering to strike.

2079
03:04:53,980 --> 03:04:58,140
然而逐渐地 我明白了这单纯的动机把我带向了什么
And, gradually, I understood what innocent intent had brought me to...

2080
03:04:59,050 --> 03:05:01,780
然后我不自觉地向前迈进
... and waded out beyond my depth.

2081
03:05:02,920 --> 03:05:05,950
当我游向那已下锚的黑货船时
The unspeakable truth loomed unavoidably before me...

2082
03:05:06,120 --> 03:05:08,990
那说不出口的事实无可避免地显现在我面前
... as I swam towards the anchored Freighter.

2083
03:05:09,160 --> 03:05:13,490
它那黑暗、摇摆不定的桅杆占据了我的视线
Its dark and lurching mast filled all my vision.

2084
03:05:13,660 --> 03:05:16,630
我所有善意的计划全都终结于此
All my well-meaning plans had come to this.

2085
03:05:16,800 --> 03:05:20,570
我已想不起来那个我想要拯救的世界
The world I tried to save was lost beyond recall.

2086
03:05:21,470 --> 03:05:23,300
一条绳索垂了下来
A rope snaked down.

2087
03:05:23,470 --> 03:05:25,630
从水中，我抓住了它
Sputtering, I grabbed it.

2088
03:05:25,810 --> 03:05:28,440
然后在上面的甲板上，欢呼声骤起
And from the decks above, a cheer went up...

2089
03:05:28,610 --> 03:05:33,010
二者同样的粗劣和黑暗 它的恶臭亵渎着上天
... both gross and black, its stench affronting heaven.

2090
03:05:35,820 --> 03:05:38,180
根本就没有要攻占戴维斯敦的计划
There had been no plan to capture Davidstown.

2091
03:05:39,020 --> 03:05:43,050
他们到这儿来是为了收取 他们唯一重视的宝贝
They'd come to wait until they could collect the only prize they valued.

2092
03:05:44,260 --> 03:05:47,390
获取他们唯一真正想要的灵魂
Claim the only soul they truly wanted.

2093
03:05:53,400 --> 03:05:55,500
我就是恐怖
I was a horror.

2094
03:05:56,340 --> 03:05:59,670
我只能在恐怖中容身
Amongst horrors must I dwell.

2095
03:06:09,150 --> 03:06:13,180
- 老兄，这破玩意儿太扯淡了 - 可不是吗
- Man, this shit don't make no sense. - You're telling me.

2096
03:06:14,520 --> 03:06:17,820
抱歉，你留着这本垃圾吧 真浪费我的时间
Sorry, but you can keep this garbage. Wasting all my damn time.

2097
03:06:17,990 --> 03:06:21,160
嘿，知道吗，你总是到这儿来
Hey, hey. You know, all this time you've been coming here...

2098
03:06:21,330 --> 03:06:22,820
可我还不知道你的名字
...I never caught your name.

2099
03:06:24,570 --> 03:06:27,560
- 伯纳德 - 伯纳德？你开玩笑吧
- Bernard. - Bernard? You're kidding.

2100
03:06:27,740 --> 03:06:31,800
这…这也是我的名字
That's... Heh. That's my name too.

2101
03:06:32,440 --> 03:06:35,670
没什么大不了的 很多人都叫伯纳德
Not that big a deal. There's lots of people called Bernard.

2102
03:07:11,080 --> 03:07:12,450
（纽约邮报：战争？）

2103
03:08:00,900 --> 03:08:03,890
我的上帝啊，亨利
Jesus Christ, Henry.

2104
03:08:04,070 --> 03:08:06,260
我们为什么一点都不知道要发射了？
Why the hell didn't we get a launch detection?

2105
03:08:08,170 --> 03:08:12,610
这不是苏联，先生
It's not the Soviets, sir.

2106
03:08:13,180 --> 03:08:16,340
情报显示这爆炸的能量特征…
Intel indicates the energy signature...

2107
03:08:16,510 --> 03:08:18,950
是由…
...was generated by...

2108
03:08:19,920 --> 03:08:22,350
曼哈顿博士发出的
...Dr. Manhattan.

2109
03:08:25,190 --> 03:08:26,750
乔
Jon.

2110
03:08:29,760 --> 03:08:30,890
干涉
Interference.

2111
03:08:31,490 --> 03:08:33,390
大范围干涉
Cataclysmic interference.

2112
03:08:43,110 --> 03:08:45,870
简直无法置信这真的发生了
LAURIE: I can't believe it happened.

2113
03:08:46,880 --> 03:08:50,370
这不是核战引发的
This wasn't caused by nuclear warheads.

2114
03:08:54,450 --> 03:08:55,750
是我
It was me.

2115
03:08:57,790 --> 03:08:59,380
我
I...

2116
03:08:59,960 --> 03:09:00,980
我一手造成的
...did this.

2117
03:09:01,620 --> 03:09:05,080
- 你什么意思？是你造成的？ - 间接造成的
- What do you mean, you did this? - Not directly.

2118
03:09:06,060 --> 03:09:08,760
看起来像是我造成的
It was made to look like I did it.

2119
03:09:11,800 --> 03:09:13,230
阿德里安
Adrian.

2120
03:09:19,510 --> 03:09:21,500
说曹操曹操到
Speak of the devil.

2121
03:09:24,650 --> 03:09:25,670
- 乔 - 我知道
DAN: Jon... JON: I know.

2122
03:09:25,850 --> 03:09:28,010
必须阻止他 他杀了布莱克，杀了数以百万的人
RORSCHACH: Must stop him. Killed Blake, killed millions.

2123
03:09:28,180 --> 03:09:29,520
在这等着
Wait here.

2124
03:09:40,660 --> 03:09:43,030
阿德里安，收手吧
Adrian, stop this.

2125
03:09:44,500 --> 03:09:46,370
超光速粒子那招很聪明
The tachyons were clever...

2126
03:09:47,500 --> 03:09:51,840
但即便我无法预测你在哪，我也能把这些墙弄碎
...but even if I can't predict where you are, I can turn the walls to glass.

2127
03:09:53,180 --> 03:09:55,640
我该谢谢你
I should thank you.

2128
03:09:56,810 --> 03:10:00,010
我差点忘了那种感觉
I'd almost forgotten the excitement of not knowing...

2129
03:10:01,020 --> 03:10:04,010
不确定带来的快乐
... the delights of uncertainty.

2130
03:10:08,190 --> 03:10:09,850
原谅我，宝贝
Forgive me, girl.

2131
03:10:32,820 --> 03:10:34,510
你就是个混蛋
You're such an asshole.

2132
03:11:08,450 --> 03:11:10,380
维特，你混蛋
DAN: Veidt, you bastard.

2133
03:11:10,550 --> 03:11:13,020
- 你要敢伤害她，我 - 丹
- Lf you've hurt her, I'Il... - Dan...

2134
03:11:14,760 --> 03:11:19,350
醒醒吧，我的新世界不需要英雄主义
...grow up. My new world demands less obvious heroism.

2135
03:11:19,530 --> 03:11:21,520
你的
Your...

2136
03:11:21,700 --> 03:11:26,660
小男生似的英雄主义太多余了 你们有什么成就吗？
...schoolboy heroics are redundant. What have they achieved?

2137
03:11:28,270 --> 03:11:31,140
还是没能拯救地球
Failing to prevent Earth's salvation...

2138
03:11:32,110 --> 03:11:34,510
这就是你们唯一的功绩
...is your only triumph.

2139
03:11:34,710 --> 03:11:36,610
我对你失望透顶了，阿德里安
JON: I'm disappointed in you, Adrian.

2140
03:11:37,410 --> 03:11:40,910
很失望
I'm very disappointed.

2141
03:11:53,300 --> 03:11:56,460
我学到的第一招，就是重组我自己
Reassembling myself was the first trick I learned.

2142
03:11:57,130 --> 03:11:59,530
那次事故没有杀死我
It didn't kill Osterman.

2143
03:12:02,140 --> 03:12:04,500
你真的觉得这次能置我于死地？
Did you really think it would kill me?

2144
03:12:05,810 --> 03:12:08,970
我在太阳表面都行走过
I have walked across the surface of the sun.

2145
03:12:09,480 --> 03:12:12,640
我目睹了许多渺小又如此迅速的事情
I have witnessed events so tiny and so fast...

2146
03:12:12,820 --> 03:12:15,880
很难说它们甚至存在过
...they can hardly be said to have occurred at all...

2147
03:12:16,050 --> 03:12:19,680
不过你，阿德里安，你只是个凡人而已
...but you, Adrian, you're just a man.

2148
03:12:20,820 --> 03:12:23,310
世上最智慧的人
The world's smartest man...

2149
03:12:23,630 --> 03:12:26,060
对我构成的威胁
...poses no more threat to me...

2150
03:12:26,230 --> 03:12:29,360
不会比最智慧的白蚁对我的威胁大
...than does its smartest termite.

2151
03:12:31,630 --> 03:12:33,100
这是什么？
What's that?

2152
03:12:33,500 --> 03:12:35,370
又一个终极武器？
Another ultimate weapon?

2153
03:12:36,010 --> 03:12:37,730
是的
Yes.

2154
03:12:39,340 --> 03:12:40,810
可以这么说
You could say that.

2155
03:12:44,350 --> 03:12:46,280
遭受攻击
- came under attack.

2156
03:12:47,120 --> 03:12:50,450
数以万计的人死于非命
Millions of lives were suddenly ended...

2157
03:12:50,790 --> 03:12:55,990
这是曼哈顿博士自己犯下的罪恶
... in an act of evil perpetrated by Dr. Manhattan himself.

2158
03:12:57,790 --> 03:13:01,730
自从攻击开始，我就一直和
Since the attacks, I have been in constant contact...

2159
03:13:01,900 --> 03:13:04,890
苏联保持联系
... with the premier of the U.S.S.R.

2160
03:13:05,300 --> 03:13:08,130
不计前嫌
Putting aside our past differences...

2161
03:13:08,470 --> 03:13:10,630
我们同意一起
... we have both pledged to unite...

2162
03:13:10,970 --> 03:13:14,310
来对付这个共同的敌人
... against this common enemy.

2163
03:13:14,810 --> 03:13:16,800
同世界所有人一起
With the rest of the world...

2164
03:13:17,250 --> 03:13:19,270
用团结取得胜利
... we will prevail.

2165
03:13:21,820 --> 03:13:24,810
我们将永远铭记今天
This is a day we shall never forget.

2166
03:13:24,990 --> 03:13:29,190
我们会继续保护人类
And yet we go forward to defend the human race...

2167
03:13:29,360 --> 03:13:33,990
保护所有正义和美好的事情
... and all that is good and just in our world.

2168
03:13:35,330 --> 03:13:39,560
谢谢，愿上帝保佑我们
Thank you. God bless us all.

2169
03:13:39,940 --> 03:13:41,730
看见没？
ADRIAN: Do you see?

2170
03:13:43,940 --> 03:13:46,410
两个超级大国，从冷战中撤离出来
Two superpowers retreating from war.

2171
03:13:48,010 --> 03:13:50,440
我把地球从地狱中救了出来
I've saved the earth from hell.

2172
03:13:50,610 --> 03:13:52,580
我们一起
We both have.

2173
03:13:53,050 --> 03:13:55,240
对你我来说，同是胜利
This is as much your victory as it is mine.

2174
03:14:00,060 --> 03:14:01,550
我们现在能重新回去
Now we can return...

2175
03:14:02,990 --> 03:14:04,550
干我们该干的事了
...do what we were meant to.

2176
03:14:04,830 --> 03:14:07,690
我们需要真正的正义
We were meant to exact justice.

2177
03:14:08,030 --> 03:14:11,360
- 人人都将知道你干了什么好事 - 是吗？
- Everyone's gonna know what you've done. - Will they?

2178
03:14:11,530 --> 03:14:16,330
揭发我，你就会葬送这么多的人死所带来的和平
By exposing me, you would sacrifice the peace so many died for today.

2179
03:14:16,510 --> 03:14:19,940
- 建立在谎言基础上的和平 - 也是和平
- Peace based on a lie. - But peace...

2180
03:14:20,110 --> 03:14:22,300
他说的对
...nonetheless. - He's right.

2181
03:14:22,880 --> 03:14:26,840
揭发阿德里安只会让世界重新陷入到核战中去
Exposing Adrian would only doom the world to nuclear destruction again.

2182
03:14:27,020 --> 03:14:29,880
我们不能这样做
No. We can't do this.

2183
03:14:30,050 --> 03:14:31,820
在火星上
On Mars...

2184
03:14:33,320 --> 03:14:35,150
你教会了我生命的意义
...you taught me the value of life.

2185
03:14:36,130 --> 03:14:38,560
如果我们想让生命在继续延续下去
If we hope to preserve it here...

2186
03:14:39,360 --> 03:14:41,390
就必须保持沉默
...we must remain silent.

2187
03:14:45,230 --> 03:14:47,170
自己保守好秘密
Keep your own secrets.

2188
03:14:54,040 --> 03:14:55,240
想都别再想
Don't even think about it.

2189
03:14:57,850 --> 03:14:59,580
罗夏
Rorschach.

2190
03:15:01,350 --> 03:15:02,870
等等
Wait.

2191
03:15:03,920 --> 03:15:06,010
永不妥协
Never compromise.

2192
03:15:06,390 --> 03:15:09,260
即便是在世界末日面前
Not even in the face of armageddon.

2193
03:15:09,660 --> 03:15:12,650
这是我们俩的区别，丹尼尔
That's always been the difference between us, Daniel.

2194
03:15:23,710 --> 03:15:27,230
我感受过死亡
I've made myself feel every death...

2195
03:15:28,710 --> 03:15:34,620
我看见所有我为了世界和平 而杀害的无辜的脸庞
...see every innocent face I've murdered to save humanity.

2196
03:15:40,190 --> 03:15:43,890
- 你都理解的，是吧？ - 没有谴责
- You understand, don't you? JON: Without condoning...

2197
03:15:45,560 --> 03:15:47,460
或责骂
...or condemning...

2198
03:15:51,870 --> 03:15:53,800
我理解
...I understand.

2199
03:16:01,210 --> 03:16:04,340
让开，人们应该知道真相
Out of my way. People have to be told.

2200
03:16:05,210 --> 03:16:07,150
你知道，我不会让你这么做的
You know I can't let you do that.

2201
03:16:08,380 --> 03:16:11,380
你突然间发现了人性？
Suddenly you discover humanity?

2202
03:16:12,820 --> 03:16:14,650
说变就变
Convenient.

2203
03:16:23,370 --> 03:16:27,930
如果你一开始就关心的话 这一切就都不会发生了
If you'd cared from the start, none of this would have happened.

2204
03:16:31,710 --> 03:16:34,680
我几乎能改变一切
I can change almost anything...

2205
03:16:39,250 --> 03:16:41,580
不过不能改变人类的本性
...but I can't change human nature.

2206
03:16:42,920 --> 03:16:46,320
当然了，你必须得保护维特新的乌托邦
Of course you must protect Veidt's new utopia.

2207
03:16:47,590 --> 03:16:50,920
为这个，多死一个人又怎样？
What's one more body amongst foundations?

2208
03:16:57,100 --> 03:16:58,960
你还等什么？
Well, what are you waiting for?

2209
03:17:02,440 --> 03:17:04,270
动手吧！
Do it.

2210
03:17:10,380 --> 03:17:11,400
动手啊！
Do it!

2211
03:17:14,120 --> 03:17:17,480
不！！！
No!

2212
03:17:34,970 --> 03:17:40,740
我要离开这个星系，去一个不这么复杂的地方
JON: I'm leaving this galaxy for one a little less complicated.

2213
03:17:40,910 --> 03:17:43,400
我以为你又开始在意生命了呢
LAURIE: I thought you said you cared about life again.

2214
03:17:43,580 --> 03:17:44,980
我是的
JON: I do.

2215
03:17:46,320 --> 03:17:49,220
或许我得再创造点生命
I think maybe I'll create some.

2216
03:17:53,320 --> 03:17:55,650
再见，劳丽
Goodbye, Laurie.

2217
03:18:30,890 --> 03:18:32,050
来啊
Come on.

2218
03:18:34,530 --> 03:18:36,120
还手啊
Come on!

2219
03:18:40,540 --> 03:18:41,870
丹
Dan...

2220
03:18:42,340 --> 03:18:45,100
一个团结又和平的世界
...a world united and at peace.

2221
03:18:45,970 --> 03:18:47,170
必须有人作出牺牲
There had to be sacrifice.

2222
03:18:47,340 --> 03:18:51,710
不！你没有把人类理想化，你毁了他们
No! You haven't idealized mankind, you've deformed it.

2223
03:18:51,880 --> 03:18:53,640
是你毁了它们！
You've mutilated it.

2224
03:18:54,020 --> 03:18:56,180
这是你的遗赠
That's your legacy.

2225
03:19:04,730 --> 03:19:07,520
这个真实的恶作剧
That's the real practical joke.

2226
03:20:00,120 --> 03:20:04,110
我们再说一次，您的电视机没有任何问题
MAN [ON TV]: We repeat, there is nothing wrong with your television set.

2227
03:20:04,290 --> 03:20:07,740
您即将经历一次神奇的历险历程
You are about to participate in a great adventure.

2228
03:20:07,920 --> 03:20:11,090
体验前所未有的恐惧和神秘
You are about to experience the awe and mystery...

2229
03:20:11,260 --> 03:20:17,060
从心灵的最深处一直到外界限
... which reaches from the inner mind to the outer limits.

2230
03:20:18,270 --> 03:20:20,460
不喝点什么吗？
SALLY: Sure you don't want a drink?

2231
03:20:21,470 --> 03:20:22,490
我不想喝
I'm okay.

2232
03:20:23,570 --> 03:20:24,800
干杯
Cheers.

2233
03:20:26,240 --> 03:20:29,370
我有些事情一定要和你说
There's something I need to get off my chest.

2234
03:20:30,650 --> 03:20:33,140
我知道艾迪·布莱克是我的亲生父亲
I know that Eddie Blake was my father.

2235
03:20:36,150 --> 03:20:37,910
劳丽
Laurel.

2236
03:20:38,920 --> 03:20:41,250
你肯定对我有想法
What you must think of me.

2237
03:20:42,090 --> 03:20:44,620
抱歉，我一直都瞒着你
I'm sorry I never told you.

2238
03:20:44,790 --> 03:20:46,590
我早该
I should have...

2239
03:20:46,760 --> 03:20:50,890
我不知道该怎么办，我觉得很丢人 很傻
...but I don't know, I just felt ashamed. I felt stupid.

2240
03:20:51,070 --> 03:20:53,000
没关系了
It doesn't matter.

2241
03:20:53,840 --> 03:20:59,100
是命运让人们去奇怪的地方 干奇怪的事情
People's lives take them strange places. They do strange things...

2242
03:20:59,670 --> 03:21:02,610
然后，有时候还无法诉说
...and, well, sometimes they can't talk about them.

2243
03:21:02,780 --> 03:21:05,110
我知道这回事
I know how that is...

2244
03:21:05,850 --> 03:21:08,440
不过我想让你知道
...but I just want you to know...

2245
03:21:09,020 --> 03:21:11,850
你对我却从来没做过错事
...that you never did anything wrong by me.

2246
03:21:16,020 --> 03:21:20,290
你问了我为什么我从来不生他的气
You asked me why I wasn't mad at him.

2247
03:21:21,860 --> 03:21:24,350
因为他让我生了你
Because he gave me you.

2248
03:21:29,370 --> 03:21:30,460
谢谢你，妈妈
Thanks, Mom.

2249
03:21:33,210 --> 03:21:35,010
我爱你
I love you.

2250
03:21:42,550 --> 03:21:46,750
- 你好，朱庇特 - 哦，莎莉
- Hello, Miss Jupiter. - Oh, Sally, please.

2251
03:21:48,390 --> 03:21:52,990
抱歉，我得去梳洗了 等下见
Excuse me. Gotta go freshen up. I'll be right back.

2252
03:22:03,510 --> 03:22:07,670
- 你这怎么样了？ - 好啊，你那呢？
- So how's it going up here? - Good. How's it going down there?

2253
03:22:07,840 --> 03:22:11,340
很好，我觉得一切都恢复正常了
Good. I think I've got everything working.

2254
03:22:11,510 --> 03:22:16,140
阿基米德的系统升级了 熔补也完成了
All of Archie's systems are upgraded. Finished the tinkering for now...

2255
03:22:16,320 --> 03:22:18,550
我们要做的是开它出去兜风
...so all we gotta do is take her out.

2256
03:22:18,720 --> 03:22:21,780
哇哦，听起来像是个约会
Well, that sounds like a date.

2257
03:22:33,100 --> 03:22:35,370
我们会没事的吗？
Are we gonna be all right?

2258
03:22:37,440 --> 03:22:41,740
只要大家还认为乔在看着我们 我们就不会有事
Long as people think Jon's still watching us, we'll be all right...

2259
03:22:41,940 --> 03:22:43,810
到最后
...in the end.

2260
03:22:45,450 --> 03:22:47,610
我知道乔会怎么说
I know what Jon would say:

2261
03:22:47,780 --> 03:22:49,810
事情是没有尽头的
Nothing ends.

2262
03:22:51,720 --> 03:22:54,310
总是没有尽头的
Nothing ever ends.

2263
03:23:41,670 --> 03:23:45,440
西摩尔，我们都没有题材可以写了
Seymour, we got nothing to write about anymore.

2264
03:23:45,610 --> 03:23:46,970
国家里的每个人
Everyone in the country...

2265
03:23:47,140 --> 03:23:49,410
世界上的每个国家的人都拉着手
...every country in the world are holding hands...

2266
03:23:49,580 --> 03:23:52,840
为和平和爱欢唱
...and singing songs about peace and love.

2267
03:23:53,350 --> 03:23:56,220
感觉像是住在一个该死的和平社区里
It's like living in a goddamn global hippie commune.

2268
03:23:56,380 --> 03:24:00,320
里根说他要在88岁时竞选总统
Well, Ronald Reagan says he's gonna be running for president in '88.

2269
03:24:00,490 --> 03:24:02,320
我们来报道这个吧
We could run a piece on that.

2270
03:24:02,490 --> 03:24:05,650
西摩尔，太荒谬的话我们是不能拿来做头条的
Seymour, we don't dignify absurdities with coverage.

2271
03:24:05,830 --> 03:24:09,660
这还是在美国，该死的 谁会想白宫里有个西部牛仔？
This is still America, damn it. Who wants a cowboy in the White House?

2272
03:24:10,400 --> 03:24:14,630
要不然我去奇异故事档案里再去找点别的？
Okay. I could look for something in the crank file.

2273
03:24:14,800 --> 03:24:16,400
奇异故事档案？
Crank file.

2274
03:24:16,570 --> 03:24:18,560
随便吧，找点原创的
Whatever. Take some initiative.

2275
03:24:18,740 --> 03:24:21,370
想写什么就写什么，全交给你了
Run whatever you like. I leave it entirely in your hands.

2276
03:24:27,880 --> 03:24:32,580
罗夏日记，1985年10月12号
Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.

2277
03:24:32,750 --> 03:24:37,210
今晚，笑匠死于纽约
Tonight, a comedian died in New York.

